233 /*
234  * pt_undef_names_pre () - Set error if name matching spec is found. Used in
235  * insert to make sure no "correlated" names are used
236  * in subqueries.
237  *
238  * return : Unchanged node argument.
239  * parser (in) : Parser context.
240  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
241  * arg (in) : Insert spec.
242  * continue_walk (in) : Continue walk.
243  *
244  * NOTE: Insert spec will store in etc the correlation level in regard with
245  * INSERT VALUE clause. Only if level is greater than 0, names should
246  * be undefined. INSERT INTO SET attr_i = EXPR (attr_j1, attr_j2, ...)
247  * is allowed.
248  * If etc is NULL, correlation level is ignored and all names are
249  * undefined.
250  */
251 static PT_NODE *
252 pt_undef_names_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
253 {
254  PT_NODE *spec = (PT_NODE *) arg;
255  short *level_p = NULL;
256 
257  if (spec == NULL)
258  {
259  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
260  return node;
261  }
262 
263  level_p = (short *) spec->etc;
264 
265  switch (node->node_type)
266  {
267  case PT_NAME:
268  if (level_p == NULL || *level_p > 0)
269  {
270  /* Using "correlated" names in INSERT VALUES clause is incorrect except when they are arguments of the
271  * DEFAULT() function. */
272  if (node->info.name.spec_id == spec->info.spec.id
273  && !PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT))
274  {
275  int save_custom_print = parser->custom_print;
276  parser->custom_print |= PT_SUPPRESS_RESOLVED;
277  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED,
278  pt_short_print (parser, node));
279  parser->custom_print = save_custom_print;
280  }
281  }
282  break;
283  case PT_SELECT:
284  case PT_UNION:
285  case PT_INTERSECTION:
286  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
287  case PT_INSERT:
288  if (level_p != NULL)
289  {
290  (*level_p)++;
291  }
292  break;
293  default:
294  break;
295  }
296 
297  return node;
298 }
299 
300 /*
301  * pt_undef_names_post () - Function to be used with pt_undef_names_pre. Helps
302  * with counting the correlation level.
303  *
304  * return : Unchanged node argument.
305  * parser (in) : Parser context.
306  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
307  * arg (in) : Insert spec.
308  * continue_walk (in) : Continue walk.
309  */
310 static PT_NODE *
311 pt_undef_names_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
312 {
313  PT_NODE *spec = (PT_NODE *) arg;
314  short *level_p = NULL;
315 
316  if (spec == NULL)
317  {
318  return node;
319  }
320 
321  level_p = (short *) spec->etc;
322  if (level_p == NULL)
323  {
324  return node;
325  }
326 
327  switch (node->node_type)
328  {
329  case PT_SELECT:
330  case PT_UNION:
331  case PT_INTERSECTION:
332  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
333  case PT_INSERT:
334  (*level_p)--;
335  break;
336  default:
337  break;
338  }
339 
340  return node;
341 }
342 
343 /*
344  * pt_resolved() - check if this path expr was previously resolved
345  * return: true if expr was previously resolved
346  * expr(in): a path expression
347  */
348 
349 int
350 pt_resolved (const PT_NODE * expr)
351 {
352  if (expr)
353  {
354  switch (expr->node_type)
355  {
356  case PT_NAME:
357  return (expr->info.name.spec_id != 0);
358  case PT_DOT_:
359  return (pt_resolved (expr->info.dot.arg1) && pt_resolved (expr->info.dot.arg2));
360  default:
361  break;
362  }
363  }
364  return 0;
365 }
366 
367 
368 /*
369  * pt_eval_value_path() -
370  * return: pt_value node if successful, NULL otherwise
371  * parser(in): the parser context
372  * path(in): a path expression anchored by a PT_VALUE node
373  */
374 
375 PT_NODE *
376 pt_eval_value_path (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * path)
377 {
378  DB_VALUE val;
379  PT_NODE *tmp;
380 
381  db_make_null (&val);
382 
383  if (pt_eval_path_expr (parser, path, &val))
384  {
385  /* make val into a PT_VALUE node */
386  tmp = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &val);
387  if (tmp)
388  {
389  tmp->line_number = path->line_number;
390  tmp->column_number = path->column_number;
391  /* NOTE node IS NO LONGER TYPE PT_NAME! */
392  pr_clear_value (&val);
393  }
394  return tmp;
395  }
396  else
397  {
398  return NULL; /* error set by pt_eval_path_expr */
399  }
400 } /* pt_eval_value_path */
401 
402 /*
403  * pt_bind_param_node() - try to bind parameter for a node
404  * return:
405  * parser(in):
406  * node(in):
407  * arg(in):
408  * continue_walk(in):
409  */
410 PT_NODE *
411 pt_bind_param_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
412 {
413  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME && node->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)
414  {
415  return pt_bind_parameter (parser, node);
416  }
417  return NULL;
418 }
419 
420 /*
421  * pt_bind_parameter() - try to resolve name as an interpreter
422  * parameter reference
423  * return: lbl's value if successful, NULL otherwise
424  * parser(in): the parser context
425  * parameter(in/out): a PT_NAME node
426  */
427 static PT_NODE *
428 pt_bind_parameter (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * parameter)
429 {
430  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
431  const char *name;
432  DB_VALUE *db_val;
433 
434  if (!parameter || parameter->node_type != PT_NAME)
435  {
436  return NULL; /* nothing doing */
437  }
438 
439  if (parameter->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NONE)
440  {
441  return parameter; /* is already resolved */
442  }
443 
444  /* look up as an interpreter parameter */
445  name = parameter->info.name.original;
446  db_val = pt_find_value_of_label (name);
447  if (db_val) /* parameter found, resolve to its matching DB_VALUE */
448  {
449  /* create a PT_VALUE image of the matching DB_VALUE */
450 
451  /* If type is object type, the referenced object may not exist. We need to first check its existence, then we
452  * can resolve the object.
453  */
454  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (db_val) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
455  {
456  MOP mop = db_get_object (db_val);
457  int does_exist = locator_does_exist_object (mop, DB_FETCH_READ);
458  if (does_exist == LC_ERROR || does_exist == LC_DOESNOT_EXIST)
459  {
460  assert (does_exist == LC_DOESNOT_EXIST || er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
461  return NULL;
462  }
463  assert (does_exist == LC_EXIST);
464  /* Fall through. */
465  }
466  node = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, db_val);
467  if (node == NULL)
468  {
469  return NULL;
470  }
471 
472  /* NOTE node IS NO LONGER TYPE PT_NAME! */
473  parameter->type_enum = node->type_enum;
474  if (parameter->data_type)
475  {
476  parser_free_tree (parser, parameter->data_type);
477  }
478  parameter->data_type = node->data_type;
479  node->data_type = NULL;
480  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
481  parameter->info.name.meta_class = PT_PARAMETER;
482  }
483 
484  if (parameter->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)
485  {
486  return parameter;
487  }
488  else
489  {
490  return NULL;
491  }
492 }
493 
494 /*
495  * pt_bind_parameter_path() - try to resolve name or path as an interpreter
496  * parameter reference or a path expression anchored by a path expression.
497  * return: path's value (evaluated) if successful, NULL otherwise
498  * parser(in): the parser context
499  * path(in/out): a PT_NAME or PT_DOT_ node
500  */
501 static PT_NODE *
502 pt_bind_parameter_path (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * path)
503 {
504  PT_NODE *arg1 = NULL;
505  PT_NODE *temp;
506 
507  if (!path)
508  {
509  return NULL; /* nothing doing */
510  }
511 
512  if (path->node_type == PT_NAME)
513  {
514  path = pt_bind_parameter (parser, path);
515  /* parameter paths must start with a parameter. */
516  if (!path || path->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER)
517  {
518  return NULL;
519  }
520  return path;
521  }
522 
523  if (path->node_type == PT_DOT_)
524  {
525  arg1 = pt_bind_parameter_path (parser, path->info.dot.arg1);
526  if (!arg1)
527  {
528  return NULL;
529  }
530  /* If we succesfully resolved the parameter, mark the right hand side as parameter too. This will be evaluated at
531  * run time. */
532  path->info.dot.arg1 = arg1;
533  path->info.dot.arg2->info.name.meta_class = PT_PARAMETER;
534 
535  /* We need to be able to evaluate it now, in order to get the type of the expression. */
536  temp = pt_eval_value_path (parser, path);
537  if (temp)
538  {
539  path->type_enum = temp->type_enum;
540  if (path->data_type)
541  {
542  parser_free_tree (parser, path->data_type);
543  }
544  path->data_type = temp->data_type;
545  temp->data_type = NULL;
546  parser_free_tree (parser, temp);
547 
548  return path;
549  }
550  }
551 
552  return NULL;
553 } /* pt_bind_parameter_path */
554 
555 /*
556  * pt_bind_reserved_name () - Try to resolve name to one of the reserved names
557  *
558  * return : Resolved reserved name or NULL.
559  * parser (in) : Parser context.
560  * in_node (in) : Original name node.
561  * spec (in) : The spec to which the reserved name will belong.
562  *
563  * NOTE: Reserved names are allowed only if used in the context of a SELECT
564  * statement on a single table and having certain hints that unlock
565  * reserved names.
566  */
567 static PT_NODE *
568 pt_bind_reserved_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * in_node, PT_NODE * spec)
569 {
570  int i = 0;
571  const char *name = NULL;
572  PT_NODE *reserved_name = NULL;
573 
574  assert (in_node != NULL && spec != NULL);
575 
576  /* get attribute name */
577  if (in_node->node_type == PT_NAME)
578  {
579  name = in_node->info.name.original;
580  }
581  else if (in_node->node_type == PT_DOT_)
582  {
583  /* we can only allow X.reserved_name where X is the name of spec */
584  if (in_node->info.dot.arg1->node_type != PT_NAME
585  || pt_str_compare (in_node->info.dot.arg1->info.name.original, spec->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original,
586  CASE_INSENSITIVE))
587  {
588  return NULL;
589  }
590  if (in_node->info.dot.arg2->node_type != PT_NAME)
591  {
592  return NULL;
593  }
594  name = in_node->info.dot.arg2->info.name.original;
595  }
596  else
597  {
598  /* not the scope of this function */
599  return NULL;
600  }
601 
602  /* look for the name in reserved name table */
603  for (i = 0; i < RESERVED_ATTR_COUNT; i++)
604  {
605  if (!pt_str_compare (name, pt_Reserved_name_table[i].name, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
606  {
607  /* the found reserved name should match the type of scan to which the spec is flagged... otherwise it is a
608  * wrong name */
609  if (!PT_CHECK_RESERVED_NAME_BIND (spec, i))
610  {
611  /* Unknown reserved name in current context */
612  return NULL;
613  }
614 
615  /* bind the reserved name */
616  if (in_node->node_type == PT_NAME)
617  {
618  reserved_name = in_node;
619  }
620  else /* PT_DOT_ */
621  {
622  reserved_name = in_node->info.dot.arg2;
623  in_node->info.dot.arg2 = NULL;
624  PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (reserved_name, in_node);
625  parser_free_tree (parser, in_node);
626  }
627  reserved_name->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
628  reserved_name->info.name.resolved = spec->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
629  reserved_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_RESERVED;
630  reserved_name->info.name.reserved_id = (PT_RESERVED_NAME_ID) i;
631  reserved_name->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (pt_Reserved_name_table[i].type);
632  if (reserved_name->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
633  {
634  reserved_name->data_type =
635  pt_domain_to_data_type (parser,
636  tp_domain_resolve (pt_Reserved_name_table[i].type,
637  spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object, 0, 0, NULL,
638  0));
639  }
640  return reserved_name;
641  }
642  }
643  /* this is not a reserved name */
644  return NULL;
645 }
646 
647 /*
648  * pt_bind_name_or_path_in_scope() - tries to resolve in_node using all the
649  * entity_spec_lists in scopes and returns in_node if successfully resolved
650  * return: in_node's resolution if successful, NULL if in_node is unresolved
651  * parser(in): the parser context
652  * bind_arg(in): a list of scopes for resolving names & path expressions
653  * in_node(in): an attribute reference or path expression to be resolved
654  *
655  * Note :
656  * Unfortunately, we can't push the check for naked parameters
657  * into pt_get_resolution() because parameters that have the
658  * name as an attribute of some (possibly enclosing) scope must be
659  * to the attribute and not the parameter (by our convention).
660  * when naked parameters are eliminated, this mickey mouse stuff
661  * will go away...
662  */
663 static PT_NODE *
664 pt_bind_name_or_path_in_scope (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg, PT_NODE * in_node)
665 {
666  PT_NODE *prev_entity = NULL;
667  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
668  SCOPES *scopes = bind_arg->scopes;
669  SCOPES *scope;
670  int level = 0;
671  PT_NODE *temp, *entity;
672  short scope_location;
673  bool error_saved = false;
674 
675  /* skip hint argument name, index name */
676  if (in_node->node_type == PT_NAME
677  && (in_node->info.name.meta_class == PT_HINT_NAME || in_node->info.name.meta_class == PT_INDEX_NAME))
678  {
679  return in_node;
680  }
681 
682  /* skip resolved nodes */
683  if (pt_resolved (in_node))
684  {
685  return in_node;
686  }
687 
688  if (er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
689  {
690  er_stack_push ();
691  error_saved = true;
692  }
693 
694  /* resolve all name nodes and path expressions */
695  if (scopes)
696  {
697  for (scope = scopes; scope != NULL; scope = scope->next)
698  {
699  node = pt_get_resolution (parser, bind_arg, scope->specs, in_node, &prev_entity, 1);
700  if (node)
701  {
702  node = pt_expand_external_path (parser, node, &prev_entity);
703  break;
704  }
705  if (is_pt_name_in_group_having (in_node))
706  {
707  /* give up; this kind of name should be in level 0 scopes */
708  break;
709  }
710  level++;
711  }
712  }
713  else
714  {
715  /* resolve class attributes and anything else that can be resolved without an enclosing scope. */
716  node = pt_get_resolution (parser, bind_arg, NULL, in_node, &prev_entity, 1);
717 
718  if (node)
719  {
720  node = pt_expand_external_path (parser, node, &prev_entity);
721  }
722  }
723 
724  if (node)
725  {
726  /* set the correlation of either the name or arg2 of the path */
727  /* expression. */
728  if (node->node_type == PT_DOT_)
729  {
730  node->info.dot.arg2->info.name.correlation_level = level;
731  }
732  else
733  {
734  node->info.name.correlation_level = level;
735  }
736 
737  /* all is well, name is resolved */
738  /* check correlation level of scope */
739  scope = scopes;
740  while (level > 0 && scope)
741  {
742  /* it was correlated. Choose the closest correlation scope. That is the same as choosing the smallest
743  * non-zero number. */
744  if (!scope->correlation_level || scope->correlation_level > (unsigned short) level)
745  {
746  scope->correlation_level = level;
747  }
748  level = level - 1;
749  scope = scope->next;
750  }
751  }
752  else
753  {
754  /* If pt_name in group by/ having, maybe it's alias. We will try to resolve it later. */
755  if (!is_pt_name_in_group_having (in_node))
756  {
757  /* it may be a naked parameter or a path expression anchored by a naked parameter. Try and resolve it as
758  * such. */
759  node = pt_bind_parameter_path (parser, in_node);
760 
761  if (node == NULL && !pt_has_error (parser))
762  {
763  if (er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
764  {
765  PT_ERRORc (parser, in_node, er_msg ());
766  }
767  else
768  {
769  PT_ERRORmf (parser, in_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED,
770  pt_short_print (parser, in_node));
771  }
772  }
773  }
774  }
775 
776  if (node != NULL)
777  {
778  /* outer join restriction check */
779  for (temp = node; temp->node_type == PT_DOT_; temp = temp->info.dot.arg2)
780  {
781  ;
782  }
783  if (temp->node_type == PT_NAME && temp->info.name.location > 0)
784  {
785  /* PT_NAME node within outer join condition */
786  if (temp != node)
787  {
788  /* node->node_type is PT_DOT_; that menas path expression */
789  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_PATH_EXPR,
790  pt_short_print (parser, node));
791  node = NULL;
792  }
793  else
794  {
795  /* check scope */
796  scope_location = temp->info.name.location;
797  entity = pt_find_outer_entity_in_scopes (parser, scopes, temp->info.name.spec_id, &scope_location);
798  if (!entity)
799  {
800  /* cannot resolve within the outer join scope */
801  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_SCOPE,
802  pt_short_print (parser, node));
803  node = NULL;
804  }
805  else if (entity->info.spec.location < 0 || (entity->info.spec.location > temp->info.name.location)
806  || scope_location > entity->info.spec.location)
807  {
808  /* cannot resolve within the outer join scope */
809  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_SCOPE,
810  pt_short_print (parser, node));
811  node = NULL;
812  }
813  }
814  }
815  }
816 
817  if (error_saved)
818  {
819  er_stack_pop ();
820  }
821 
822  return node;
823 }
824 
825 
826 /*
827  * pt_bind_type_of_host_var() - set the type of a host variable to
828  * the type of its DB_VALUE
829  * return: none
830  * parser(in/out): the parser context
831  * hv(in/out): an input host variable
832  */
833 static void
834 pt_bind_type_of_host_var (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * hv)
835 {
836  DB_VALUE *val = NULL;
837 
838  val = pt_host_var_db_value (parser, hv);
839  if (val)
840  {
841  hv = pt_bind_type_from_dbval (parser, hv, val);
842  }
843  /* else : There isn't a host var yet. This happens if someone does a db_compile_statement before doing
844  * db_push_values, as might happen in a dynamic esql PREPARE statement where the host vars might not be supplied
845  * until some later EXECUTE or OPEN CURSOR statement. In this case, we'll have to rely on pt_coerce_value and
846  * pt_value_to_dbval to fix things up later. */
847 }
848 
849 /*
850  * pt_bind_spec_attrs() - bind name types for a derived table.
851  * return: void
852  * parser(in/out): the parser context
853  * spec(in/out): an entity spec describing a derived table
854  *
855  * Note :
856  * if spec.derived_table_type is set expr then assert: spec.derived_table.type
857  * is a set type in any case, check that:
858  * the number of derived columns in spec.as_attr_list matches
859  * the number of attributes in spec.derived_table.select_list
860  * foreach column c in spec.as_attr_list and foreach attribute a
861  * in spec.derived_table.select_list do make c assume a's datatype and
862  * tag it with spec's id
863  */
864 static void
865 pt_bind_spec_attrs (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec)
866 {
867  PT_NODE *derived_table = NULL, *col, *attr, *cte = NULL;
868  PT_SPEC_INFO *spec_info;
869 
870  if (!parser || !spec || spec->node_type != PT_SPEC || PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec))
871  {
872  return;
873  }
874 
875  spec_info = &spec->info.spec;
876 
877  /* get aliases if they are not present */
878  if (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (spec))
879  {
880  derived_table = spec_info->derived_table;
881  if (spec_info->as_attr_list == NULL)
882  {
883  spec_info->as_attr_list =
884  pt_get_attr_list_of_derived_table (parser, spec_info->derived_table_type, derived_table,
885  spec_info->range_var);
886  }
887 
888  /* get types from derived table; */
889  pt_set_attr_list_types (parser, spec_info->as_attr_list, spec_info->derived_table_type, derived_table, spec);
890  }
891  else
892  {
893  assert (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec));
894  cte = spec_info->cte_pointer->info.pointer.node;
895 
896  /* copy cte as_attr_list to spec, to be used for binding */
897  if (spec_info->as_attr_list == NULL)
898  {
899  if (cte->info.cte.as_attr_list == NULL)
900  {
901  /* as_attr_list of cte should be previously computed in pt_bind_names_in_cte */
902  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "cte definition error");
903  return;
904  }
905  spec_info->as_attr_list = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, cte->info.cte.as_attr_list);
906  }
907  else
908  {
909  /* copy cte types from its as_attr_list */
910  if (pt_length_of_list (spec_info->as_attr_list) != pt_length_of_list (cte->info.cte.as_attr_list))
911  {
912  PT_ERRORmf3 (parser, spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_CNT_NE_DERIVED_C,
913  pt_short_print (parser, spec), pt_length_of_list (cte->info.cte.as_attr_list),
914  pt_length_of_list (spec_info->as_attr_list));
915  }
916 
917  col = spec_info->as_attr_list;
918  attr = cte->info.cte.as_attr_list;
919  for (; col != NULL && attr != NULL; col = col->next, attr = attr->next)
920  {
921  col->type_enum = attr->type_enum;
922  if (attr->data_type)
923  {
924  col->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, attr->data_type);
925  }
926  else
927  {
928  parser_free_tree (parser, col->data_type);
929  col->data_type = NULL;
930  }
931  }
932  assert (col == NULL && attr == NULL);
933  }
934  }
935 
936  for (col = spec->info.spec.as_attr_list; col != NULL; col = col->next)
937  {
938  /* tag it as resolved */
939  col->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
940  col->info.name.meta_class = PT_NORMAL;
941  }
942 }
943 
944 /*
945  * pt_bind_scope() - bind names and types of derived tables in current scope.
946  * return: void
947  * parser(in): the parser context
948  * bind_arg(in/out): a list of scopes with the current scope on "top"
949  *
950  * Note :
951  * this definition of a derived table's scope allows us to resolve the 3rd f in
952  * select f.ssn from faculty1 f, (select ssn from faculty g where f=g) h(ssn)
953  * and still catch the 1st illegal forward reference to f in
954  * select n from (select ssn from faculty g where f=g) h(n), faculty f
955  */
956 static void
957 pt_bind_scope (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg)
958 {
959  SCOPES *scopes = bind_arg->scopes;
960  PT_NODE *spec, *prev_spec = NULL;
961  bool save_donot_fold;
962 
963  spec = scopes->specs;
964  scopes->specs = NULL;
965  while (spec)
966  {
967 
968  if (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (spec))
969  {
970  /* evaluate the names of the current table. The name scope of the first spec, is only the outer level scopes. The
971  * outer scopes are pointed to by scopes->next. The null "scopes" spec is kept to maintain correlation level
972  * calculation.
973  */
974  PT_NODE *table;
975 
976  assert (!PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec) && !PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec));
977  table = spec->info.spec.derived_table;
978  table = parser_walk_tree (parser, table, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
979  spec->info.spec.derived_table = table;
980 
981  /* must bind any expr types in table. pt_bind_types requires it. */
982  save_donot_fold = bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold; /* save */
983  bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold = true; /* skip folding */
984  table = pt_semantic_type (parser, table, bind_arg->sc_info);
985  bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold = save_donot_fold; /* restore */
986  if (table != NULL)
987  {
988  spec->info.spec.derived_table = table;
989  /* table spec passed bind_names and semantic_type */
990  pt_bind_spec_attrs (parser, spec);
991  }
992  else
993  {
994  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
995  }
996  }
997  else if (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec))
998  {
999  /* types and names of CTE should be already evaluated by pt_bind_names_in_cte; bind them to spec */
1000  pt_bind_spec_attrs (parser, spec);
1001  }
1002 
1003  if (prev_spec)
1004  {
1005  prev_spec->next = spec;
1006  }
1007  else
1008  {
1009  scopes->specs = spec;
1010  }
1011  prev_spec = spec;
1012  spec = prev_spec->next;
1013  prev_spec->next = NULL;
1014  }
1015 }
1016 
1017 
1018 /*
1019  * pt_find_function_type () - function name to look up
1020  * return: function_type, or generic if not found
1021  * name(in):
1022  */
1023 static FUNC_TYPE
1024 pt_find_function_type (const char *name)
1025 {
1026  if (name)
1027  {
1028  if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "set") == 0)
1029  {
1030  return F_TABLE_SET;
1031  }
1032  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "multiset") == 0)
1033  {
1034  return F_TABLE_MULTISET;
1035  }
1036  else if (intl_mbs_casecmp (name, "sequence") == 0)
1037  {
1038  return F_TABLE_SEQUENCE;
1039  }
1040  }
1041  return PT_GENERIC;
1042 }
1043 
1044 
1045 /*
1046  * pt_mark_location () -
1047  * return:
1048  * parser(in):
1049  * node(in):
1050  * arg(in):
1051  * continue_walk(in):
1052  */
1053 static PT_NODE *
1054 pt_mark_location (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1055 {
1056  short *location = (short *) arg;
1057 
1058  switch (node->node_type)
1059  {
1060  case PT_EXPR:
1061  node->info.expr.location = *location;
1062  break;
1063  case PT_NAME:
1064  node->info.name.location = *location;
1065  break;
1066  case PT_VALUE:
1067  node->info.value.location = *location;
1068  break;
1069  default:
1070  break;
1071  }
1072 
1073  return node;
1074 } /* pt_mark_location() */
1075 
1076 /*
1077  * pt_set_is_view_spec () -
1078  * return:
1079  * parser(in):
1080  * node(in):
1081  * arg(in):
1082  * continue_walk(in):
1083  */
1084 PT_NODE *
1085 pt_set_is_view_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1086 {
1087  if (!node)
1088  {
1089  return node;
1090  }
1091 
1092  if (pt_is_query (node))
1093  {
1094  /* Reset query id # */
1095  node->info.query.id = (UINTPTR) node;
1096  node->info.query.is_view_spec = 1;
1097  }
1098 
1099  return node;
1100 } /* pt_set_is_view_spec */
1101 
1102 /*
1103  * pt_bind_names_post() - bind names & path expressions of this statement node
1104  * return: node
1105  * parser(in): the parser context
1106  * node(in): a parse tree node
1107  * arg(in): a list of scopes for resolving names & path expressions
1108  * continue_walk(in): flag that tells when to stop tree traversal
1109  */
1110 static PT_NODE *
1111 pt_bind_names_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1112 {
1113  PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *bind_arg = (PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *) arg;
1114 
1115  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
1116 
1117  if (!node)
1118  {
1119  return node;
1120  }
1121 
1122  switch (node->node_type)
1123  {
1124  case PT_UPDATE:
1125  case PT_MERGE:
1126  {
1127  PT_NODE *temp, *lhs, *assignments = NULL, *spec = NULL;
1128  int error = NO_ERROR;
1129 
1130  if (node->node_type == PT_UPDATE)
1131  {
1132  assignments = node->info.update.assignment;
1133  spec = node->info.update.spec;
1134  }
1135  else if (node->node_type == PT_MERGE)
1136  {
1137  assignments = node->info.merge.update.assignment;
1138  assert (node->info.merge.into->next == NULL);
1139  node->info.merge.into->next = node->info.merge.using_clause;
1140  spec = node->info.merge.into;
1141  }
1142 
1143  /* this is only to eliminate oid names from lhs of assignments per ANSI. This is because name resolution for
1144  * OID's conflicts with ANSI. */
1145  for (temp = assignments; temp && error == NO_ERROR; temp = temp->next)
1146  {
1147  lhs = temp->info.expr.arg1;
1148  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs))
1149  {
1150  lhs = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
1151  }
1152 
1153  for (; lhs && error == NO_ERROR; lhs = lhs->next)
1154  {
1155  if (lhs->node_type == PT_NAME)
1156  {
1157  /* make it print like ANSI */
1158  if (lhs->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR)
1159  {
1160  /* must re-resolve the name */
1161  lhs->info.name.original = lhs->info.name.resolved;
1162  lhs->info.name.spec_id = 0;
1163  if (!pt_find_name_in_spec (parser, spec, lhs))
1164  {
1165  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED;
1166  PT_ERRORmf (parser, lhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, pt_short_print (parser, lhs));
1167  }
1168  }
1169  }
1170  }
1171  }
1172  if (node->node_type == PT_MERGE)
1173  {
1174  node->info.merge.into->next = NULL;
1175  }
1176  }
1177 
1178  break;
1179 
1180  case PT_VALUE:
1181  {
1182  PT_NODE *elem;
1183  int is_function = 0;
1184 
1185  if (node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_STAR)
1186  {
1187  break;
1188  }
1189 
1190  if (node && pt_is_set_type (node))
1191  {
1192  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, bind_arg->sc_info);
1193  if (node == NULL)
1194  {
1195  return node;
1196  }
1197 
1198  elem = node->info.value.data_value.set;
1199  while (elem)
1200  {
1201  if (elem->node_type != PT_VALUE)
1202  {
1203  is_function = 1;
1204  break;
1205  }
1206  elem = elem->next;
1207  }
1208  }
1209 
1210  if (!is_function)
1211  {
1212  if (pt_value_to_db (parser, node) == NULL)
1213  {
1214  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1215  node = NULL;
1216  }
1217  else
1218  {
1219  /*
1220  * pt_value_to_db has already filled the contents
1221  * of node->info.value.db_value; we don't need to
1222  * repeat that work here.
1223  * The type info from "node" drove that process, and
1224  * is assumed to be good. If there was any touch-up
1225  * work required (e.g., adding a data_type node),
1226  * pt_value_to_db took care of it.
1227  */
1228  }
1229  }
1230  else
1231  {
1232  PT_NODE *arg_list = node->info.value.data_value.set;
1233  /* roll back error messages for set values. this is a set function reference, which we just realized, since
1234  * the syntax for constant sets and set functions is the same. Convert the node to a set function. */
1235  node->node_type = PT_FUNCTION;
1236  /* make info set up properly */
1237  memset (&(node->info), 0, sizeof (node->info));
1238  node->info.function.arg_list = arg_list;
1239  if (node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SET)
1240  {
1241  node->info.function.function_type = F_SET;
1242  }
1243  else if (node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MULTISET)
1244  {
1245  node->info.function.function_type = F_MULTISET;
1246  }
1247  else if (node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE)
1248  {
1249  node->info.function.function_type = F_SEQUENCE;
1250  }
1251  else
1252  {
1253  node->info.function.function_type = (FUNC_TYPE) 0;
1254  }
1255 
1256  /* now we need to type the innards of the set ... */
1257  /* first we tag this not typed so the type will be recomputed from scratch. */
1258  node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NONE;
1259  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, bind_arg->sc_info);
1260  }
1261 
1262  }
1263  break;
1264 
1265  case PT_EXPR:
1266  (void) pt_instnum_compatibility (node);
1267  pt_mark_function_index_expression (parser, node, bind_arg);
1268  break;
1269 
1270  case PT_SELECT:
1271  if (node->info.query.q.select.from != NULL && PT_SPEC_SPECIAL_INDEX_SCAN (node->info.query.q.select.from))
1272  {
1273  /* This is a hack to determine type for index key attributes which may be different index. Obtain index info
1274  * and update type_enum and data type for all references to index keys. */
1275  PT_NODE *spec = node->info.query.q.select.from;
1276  DB_OBJECT *obj = spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object;
1277  PT_NODE *index = node->info.query.q.select.using_index;
1278  SM_CLASS *class_ = NULL;
1279  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *cons = NULL;
1280  TP_DOMAIN *key_domain;
1281  PT_BIND_NAMES_DATA_TYPE key_type;
1282 
1283  /* Get class object */
1284  if (au_fetch_class_force (obj, &class_, AU_FETCH_READ) != NO_ERROR)
1285  {
1286  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Error obtaining SM_CLASS");
1287  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1288  return NULL;
1289  }
1290  /* Get index */
1291  cons = classobj_find_class_index (class_, index->info.name.original);
1292  if (cons == NULL)
1293  {
1294  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Hint argument should be the name of a" "valid index");
1295  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1296  return NULL;
1297  }
1298  /* Get key type for index */
1299  if (btree_get_index_key_type (cons->index_btid, &key_domain) != NO_ERROR)
1300  {
1301  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Error obtaining index key type");
1302  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1303  return NULL;
1304  }
1305 
1306  if (key_domain == NULL)
1307  {
1308  /* do nothing */
1309  return node;
1310  }
1311 
1312  /* Generate one data_type sample */
1313  key_type.type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (key_domain));
1314  key_type.data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, key_domain);
1315  if (key_type.data_type == NULL)
1316  {
1317  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
1318  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1319  return NULL;
1320  }
1321 
1322  /* Walk parse tree and change type enum for all RESERVED_KEY_KEY name nodes. */
1323  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_set_reserved_name_key_type, &key_type, NULL, NULL);
1324 
1325  parser_free_tree (parser, key_type.data_type);
1326  }
1327  break;
1328 
1329  default:
1330  break;
1331  }
1332 
1333  return node;
1334 }
1335 
1336 /*
1337  * pt_check_Oracle_outerjoin () -
1338  * return:
1339  * parser(in):
1340  * node(in):
1341  * arg(in):
1342  * continue_walk(in/out):
1343  */
1344 static PT_NODE *
1345 pt_check_Oracle_outerjoin (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1346 {
1347  PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *bind_arg = (PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *) arg;
1348  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO *sc_info;
1349 
1350  if (!node)
1351  {
1352  return node;
1353  }
1354 
1355  switch (node->node_type)
1356  {
1357  case PT_NAME:
1358  sc_info = bind_arg->sc_info;
1359 
1360  /* found node which is bound to the specified spec */
1361  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME && (node->info.name.spec_id == sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_spec->info.spec.id))
1362  {
1363  sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_attr_num++;
1364  }
1365 
1366  /* don't revisit leaves */
1367  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1368  break;
1369 
1370  case PT_SELECT:
1371  sc_info = bind_arg->sc_info;
1372 
1373  /* check for subquery in ON cond */
1374  sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_subq_num++;
1375  break;
1376 
1377  case PT_DOT_:
1378  sc_info = bind_arg->sc_info;
1379 
1380  /* check for path expression in ON cond */
1381  sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_path_num++;
1382  break;
1383 
1384  default:
1385  break;
1386  }
1387 
1388  return node;
1389 }
1390 
1391 /*
1392  * pt_clear_Oracle_outerjoin_spec_id () -
1393  * return:
1394  * parser(in):
1395  * node(in):
1396  * arg(in):
1397  * continue_walk(in/out):
1398  */
1399 static PT_NODE *
1400 pt_clear_Oracle_outerjoin_spec_id (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1401 {
1402  PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *bind_arg = (PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *) arg;
1403  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO *sc_info;
1404 
1405  if (!node)
1406  {
1407  return node;
1408  }
1409 
1410  switch (node->node_type)
1411  {
1412  case PT_NAME:
1413  sc_info = bind_arg->sc_info;
1414 
1415  /* found node which is bound to the specified spec */
1416  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME)
1417  {
1418  /* clear spec_id to re-check outer join semantic */
1419  node->info.name.spec_id = 0;
1420  }
1421 
1422  /* don't revisit leaves */
1423  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1424  break;
1425 
1426  default:
1427  break;
1428  }
1429 
1430  return node;
1431 }
1432 
1433 void
1434 pt_set_fill_default_in_path_expression (PT_NODE * node)
1435 {
1436  if (node == NULL)
1437  {
1438  return;
1439  }
1440  if (node->node_type == PT_DOT_)
1441  {
1442  pt_set_fill_default_in_path_expression (node->info.dot.arg1);
1443  pt_set_fill_default_in_path_expression (node->info.dot.arg2);
1444  }
1445  else if (node->node_type == PT_NAME)
1446  {
1447  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT);
1448 
1449  /* We also need to clear the spec id because this PT_NAME node might be a copy of a node that has been resolved
1450  * without filling in the default value. The parser_copy_tree() call in
1451  * fill_in_insert_default_function_arguments() is an example. We mark the current node as not resolved so that it
1452  * is resolved again, this time filling in the default value. */
1453  node->info.name.spec_id = 0;
1454  }
1455  else
1456  {
1457  assert (false);
1458  }
1459 }
1460 
1461 /*
1462  * fill_in_insert_default_function_arguments () - Fills in the argument of the
1463  * DEFAULT function when used
1464  * for INSERT, MERGE INSERT
1465  * parser(in):
1466  * node(in):
1467  * Note: When parsing statements such as "INSERT INTO tbl VALUES (1, DEFAULT)"
1468  * the column names corresponding to DEFAULT values are not yet known.
1469  * When performing name resolution the names and default values can be
1470  * filled in.
1471  */
1472 static void
1473 fill_in_insert_default_function_arguments (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * const node)
1474 {
1475  PT_NODE *crt_attr = NULL;
1476  PT_NODE *crt_value = NULL;
1477  PT_NODE *crt_list = NULL;
1478  SM_CLASS *smclass = NULL;
1479  SM_ATTRIBUTE *attr = NULL;
1480  PT_NODE *cls_name = NULL;
1481  PT_NODE *values_list = NULL;
1482  PT_NODE *attrs_list = NULL;
1483 
1484  assert (node->node_type == PT_INSERT || node->node_type == PT_MERGE);
1485 
1486  /* if an attribute has a default expression as default value and that expression refers to the current date and time,
1487  * then we make sure that we mark this statement as one that needs the system datetime from the server */
1488  if (node->node_type == PT_INSERT)
1489  {
1490  cls_name = node->info.insert.spec->info.spec.entity_name;
1491  values_list = node->info.insert.value_clauses;
1492  attrs_list = node->info.insert.attr_list;
1493  }
1494  else
1495  {
1496  cls_name = node->info.merge.into->info.spec.entity_name;
1497  values_list = node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses;
1498  attrs_list = node->info.merge.insert.attr_list;
1499  }
1500 
1501  au_fetch_class_force (cls_name->info.name.db_object, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ);
1502  if (smclass)
1503  {
1504  for (attr = smclass->attributes; attr != NULL; attr = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) attr->header.next)
1505  {
1506  if (DB_IS_DATETIME_DEFAULT_EXPR (attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type))
1507  {
1508  node->si_datetime = true;
1509  db_make_null (&parser->sys_datetime);
1510  break;
1511  }
1512  }
1513  }
1514 
1515  for (crt_list = values_list; crt_list != NULL; crt_list = crt_list->next)
1516  {
1517  /*
1518  * If the statement such as "INSERT INTO tbl DEFAULT" is given,
1519  * we rewrite it to "INSERT INTO tbl VALUES (DEFAULT, DEFAULT, ...)"
1520  * to support "server-side insertion" simply.
1521  * In this situation, the server will get "default value" from
1522  * "original_value" of the current representation, but sometimes
1523  * it is not the latest default value. (See the comment for sm_attribute
1524  * structure on class_object.h for more information.)
1525  * However, the client always knows it, so it's better for the server to
1526  * get the value from the client.
1527  */
1528  if (crt_list->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_DEFAULT_VALUE)
1529  {
1530  PT_NODE *crt_value_list = NULL;
1531 
1532  assert ((node->node_type == PT_INSERT && node->info.node_list.list == NULL)
1533  || (node->node_type == PT_MERGE && crt_list->info.node_list.list == NULL));
1534 
1535  for (crt_attr = attrs_list; crt_attr != NULL; crt_attr = crt_attr->next)
1536  {
1537  crt_value = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
1538 
1539  if (crt_value == NULL)
1540  {
1541  if (crt_value_list != NULL)
1542  {
1543  parser_free_tree (parser, crt_value_list);
1544  }
1545  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "allocation error");
1546  return;
1547  }
1548 
1549  crt_value->info.expr.op = PT_DEFAULTF;
1550  crt_value->info.expr.arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, crt_attr);
1551 
1552  if (crt_value->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
1553  {
1554  parser_free_node (parser, crt_value);
1555  if (crt_value_list != NULL)
1556  {
1557  parser_free_tree (parser, crt_value_list);
1558  }
1559  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "allocation error");
1560  return;
1561  }
1562 
1563  pt_set_fill_default_in_path_expression (crt_value->info.expr.arg1);
1564 
1565  if (crt_value_list == NULL)
1566  {
1567  crt_value_list = crt_value;
1568  }
1569  else
1570  {
1571  crt_value_list = parser_append_node (crt_value, crt_value_list);
1572  }
1573  }
1574  crt_list->info.node_list.list = crt_value_list;
1575  crt_list->info.node_list.list_type = PT_IS_VALUE;
1576  }
1577  else
1578  {
1579  for (crt_attr = attrs_list, crt_value = crt_list->info.node_list.list; crt_attr != NULL && crt_value != NULL;
1580  crt_attr = crt_attr->next, crt_value = crt_value->next)
1581  {
1582  PT_NODE *crt_arg = NULL;
1583 
1584  if (crt_value->node_type != PT_EXPR)
1585  {
1586  continue;
1587  }
1588  if (crt_value->info.expr.op != PT_DEFAULTF)
1589  {
1590  continue;
1591  }
1592  if (crt_value->info.expr.arg1 != NULL)
1593  {
1594  continue;
1595  }
1596  crt_arg = parser_copy_tree (parser, crt_attr);
1597  if (crt_arg == NULL)
1598  {
1599  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "allocation error");
1600  return;
1601  }
1602  crt_value->info.expr.arg1 = crt_arg;
1603  pt_set_fill_default_in_path_expression (crt_arg);
1604  }
1605  }
1606  }
1607 }
1608 
1609 /*
1610  * pt_bind_names () -
1611  * return:
1612  * parser(in):
1613  * node(in):
1614  * arg(in/out):
1615  * continue_walk(in/out):
1616  */
1617 static PT_NODE *
1618 pt_bind_names (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1619 {
1620  PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *bind_arg = (PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG *) arg;
1621  SCOPES scopestack;
1622  PT_NODE *node1 = NULL;
1623  PT_EXTRA_SPECS_FRAME spec_frame;
1624  PT_NODE *prev_attr = NULL, *attr = NULL, *next_attr = NULL, *as_attr = NULL;
1625  PT_NODE *resolved_attrs = NULL, *spec = NULL;
1626  PT_NODE *flat = NULL, *range_var = NULL;
1627  bool do_resolve = true;
1628  PT_NODE *seq = NULL;
1629  PT_NODE *cnf = NULL, *prev = NULL, *next = NULL, *last = NULL, *save = NULL;
1630  PT_NODE *lhs = NULL, *rhs = NULL, *lhs_spec = NULL, *rhs_spec = NULL;
1631  PT_NODE *p_spec = NULL;
1632  PT_NODE *result = NULL;
1633  short i, k, lhs_location, rhs_location, level;
1634  PT_JOIN_TYPE join_type;
1635  void *save_etc = NULL;
1636 
1637  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
1638 
1639  if (!node || !parser)
1640  {
1641  return node;
1642  }
1643 
1644  /* treat scopes as the next outermost scope */
1645  scopestack.next = bind_arg->scopes;
1646  scopestack.specs = NULL;
1647  scopestack.correlation_level = 0;
1648  scopestack.location = 0;
1649 
1650  /* prepend local scope to scopestack and then bind names */
1651  switch (node->node_type)
1652  {
1653  case PT_SELECT:
1654 
1655  scopestack.specs = node->info.query.q.select.from;
1656  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
1657  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
1658 
1659  /* break links to current scopes to bind_names in the WITH_CLAUSE */
1660  bind_arg->scopes = NULL;
1661  bind_arg->spec_frames = NULL;
1662  pt_bind_names_in_with_clause (parser, node, bind_arg);
1663 
1664  /* restore links to current scopes */
1665  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
1666  bind_arg->spec_frames = &spec_frame;
1667 
1668  if (pt_has_error (parser))
1669  {
1670  /* name binding in WITH_CLAUSE have failed; this node will be registered to orphan list and freed later */
1671  node = NULL;
1672  goto select_end;
1673  }
1674 
1675  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
1676 
1677  if (pt_has_error (parser))
1678  {
1679  /* this node will be registered to orphan list and freed later */
1680  node = NULL;
1681  goto select_end;
1682  }
1683 
1684  /* 0-step: check for hints that can affect name resolving. some hints are supposed to change the result type by
1685  * obtaining record information or page header information and so on. In these cases, names will be resolved to a
1686  * set of reserved names for each type of results. The query spec must be marked accordingly. NOTE: These hints
1687  * can be applied on single-spec queries. If this is a joined-spec query, just ignore the hints. */
1688  if (node->info.query.q.select.from != NULL && node->info.query.q.select.from->next == NULL)
1689  {
1690  if (node->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_SELECT_RECORD_INFO)
1691  {
1692  /* mark spec to scan for record info */
1693  node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag =
1694  (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_RECORD_INFO_SCAN);
1695  }
1696  else if (node->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_SELECT_PAGE_INFO)
1697  {
1698  /* mark spec to scan for heap page headers */
1699  node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag =
1700  (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_PAGE_INFO_SCAN);
1701  }
1702  else if (node->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_SELECT_KEY_INFO)
1703  {
1704  PT_NODE *using_index = node->info.query.q.select.using_index;
1705  if (using_index == NULL || !PT_IS_NAME_NODE (using_index))
1706  {
1707  assert (0);
1708  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Invalid usage of SELECT_KEY_INFO hint");
1709  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1710  node = NULL;
1711  goto select_end;
1712  }
1713  /* using_index is just a name, mark as index name */
1714  using_index->info.name.meta_class = PT_INDEX_NAME;
1715  using_index->etc = (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_FORCE;
1716 
1717  /* mark spec to scan for index key info */
1718  node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag =
1719  (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_KEY_INFO_SCAN);
1720  }
1721  else if (node->info.query.q.select.hint & PT_HINT_SELECT_BTREE_NODE_INFO)
1722  {
1723  PT_NODE *using_index = node->info.query.q.select.using_index;
1724  if (using_index == NULL || !PT_IS_NAME_NODE (using_index))
1725  {
1726  assert (0);
1727  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Invalid usage of SELECT_KEY_INFO hint");
1728  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1729  node = NULL;
1730  goto select_end;
1731  }
1732  /* using_index is just a name, mark as index name */
1733  using_index->info.name.meta_class = PT_INDEX_NAME;
1734  using_index->etc = (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_FORCE;
1735 
1736  /* mark spec to scan for index key info */
1737  node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag =
1738  (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (node->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_BTREE_NODE_INFO_SCAN);
1739  }
1740  }
1741 
1742  /* resolve '*' for rewritten multicolumn subquery during parsing STEP 1: remove sequence from select_list STEP 2:
1743  * resolve '*', if exists STEP 3: restore sequence */
1744 
1745  /* STEP 1 */
1746  seq = NULL;
1747  if (node->info.query.q.select.list->node_type == PT_VALUE
1748  && node->info.query.q.select.list->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE
1749  && pt_length_of_select_list (node->info.query.q.select.list, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS) == 1)
1750  {
1751  seq = node->info.query.q.select.list;
1752  node->info.query.q.select.list = seq->info.value.data_value.set;
1753  seq->info.value.data_value.set = NULL; /* cut-off link */
1754  }
1755 
1756  /* STEP 2 */
1757  if (node->info.query.q.select.list)
1758  { /* resolve "*" */
1759  if (node->info.query.q.select.list->node_type == PT_VALUE
1760  && node->info.query.q.select.list->type_enum == PT_TYPE_STAR)
1761  {
1762  PT_NODE *next = node->info.query.q.select.list->next;
1763 
1764  /* To consider 'select *, xxx ...', release "*" node only. */
1765  node->info.query.q.select.list->next = NULL;
1766  parser_free_node (parser, node->info.query.q.select.list);
1767 
1768  node->info.query.q.select.list = pt_resolve_star (parser, node->info.query.q.select.from, NULL);
1769 
1770  if (next != NULL)
1771  {
1772  parser_append_node (next, node->info.query.q.select.list);
1773  }
1774 
1775  if (!node->info.query.q.select.list)
1776  {
1777  unsigned int save_custom = parser->custom_print;
1778  PT_NODE *from = node->info.query.q.select.from;
1779 
1780  parser->custom_print = parser->custom_print | PT_SUPPRESS_RESOLVED;
1781  PT_ERRORmf (parser, from, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_ATTRIBUTES_IN_CLS,
1782  pt_short_print (parser, from));
1783  parser->custom_print = save_custom;
1784  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1785  node = NULL;
1786  goto select_end;
1787  }
1788  }
1789  else
1790  { /* resolve "class_name.*" */
1791  prev_attr = NULL;
1792  attr = node->info.query.q.select.list;
1793 
1794  while (attr && do_resolve)
1795  {
1796  do_resolve = false;
1797 
1798  /* STEP 2-1) find "class_name.*" */
1799  while (attr)
1800  {
1801  if (attr->node_type == PT_NAME && attr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_STAR)
1802  {
1803  /* find "class_name.*" */
1804  do_resolve = true;
1805  break;
1806  }
1807 
1808  prev_attr = attr; /* save previous attr */
1809  attr = attr->next;
1810  }
1811 
1812  if (attr == NULL) /* consume attr list */
1813  {
1814  break;
1815  }
1816 
1817  /* STEP 2-2) do resolve */
1818  if (do_resolve == true)
1819  {
1820  /* STEP 2-2-1) assign spec_id into PT_NAME */
1821  for (spec = node->info.query.q.select.from; spec; spec = spec->next)
1822  {
1823  if (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec))
1824  {
1825  /* entity spec */
1826  assert (!PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (spec) || !PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec));
1827  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
1828 
1829  if (pt_str_compare (attr->info.name.original, flat->info.name.resolved, CASE_INSENSITIVE)
1830  == 0)
1831  {
1832  /* find spec set attr's spec_id */
1833  attr->info.name.spec_id = flat->info.name.spec_id;
1834  break;
1835  }
1836  }
1837  else
1838  {
1839  /* derived table or cte */
1840  assert (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (spec) || PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec));
1841  range_var = spec->info.spec.range_var;
1842  if (pt_str_compare (attr->info.name.original, range_var->info.name.original,
1843  CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
1844  {
1845  break;
1846  }
1847  }
1848  } /* for */
1849 
1850  if (spec == NULL)
1851  { /* error */
1852  do_resolve = false;
1853  node->info.query.q.select.list = NULL;
1854  break;
1855  }
1856  else
1857  {
1858  /* STEP 2-2-2) recreate select_list */
1859  if (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec))
1860  {
1861  resolved_attrs =
1862  parser_append_node (attr->next,
1863  pt_resolve_star (parser, node->info.query.q.select.from, attr));
1864  }
1865  else
1866  {
1867  for (as_attr = spec->info.spec.as_attr_list; as_attr; as_attr = as_attr->next)
1868  {
1869  as_attr->info.name.resolved = range_var->info.name.original;
1870  }
1871  resolved_attrs =
1872  parser_append_node (attr->next,
1873  parser_copy_tree_list (parser, spec->info.spec.as_attr_list));
1874  }
1875 
1876  if (prev_attr == NULL)
1877  {
1878  node->info.query.q.select.list = resolved_attrs;
1879  }
1880  else
1881  {
1882  prev_attr->next = NULL;
1883  node->info.query.q.select.list =
1884  parser_append_node (resolved_attrs, node->info.query.q.select.list);
1885  }
1886 
1887  if (resolved_attrs == NULL || node->info.query.q.select.list == NULL)
1888  {
1889  node->info.query.q.select.list = NULL;
1890  break;
1891  }
1892  }
1893  } /* if (do_resolve) */
1894 
1895  next_attr = attr->next;
1896  attr->next = NULL;
1897  parser_free_tree (parser, attr);
1898  attr = next_attr;
1899 
1900  /* reposition prev_attr */
1901  for (prev_attr = resolved_attrs; prev_attr->next != attr; prev_attr = prev_attr->next)
1902  {
1903  ;
1904  }
1905  }
1906  }
1907 
1908  if (!node->info.query.q.select.list)
1909  {
1910  unsigned int save_custom = parser->custom_print;
1911 
1912  parser->custom_print = (parser->custom_print | PT_SUPPRESS_RESOLVED);
1913  PT_ERRORmf (parser, attr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED,
1914  pt_short_print (parser, attr));
1915  parser->custom_print = save_custom;
1916  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1917  node = NULL;
1918  goto select_end;
1919  }
1920  }
1921 
1922  /* STEP 3 */
1923  if (seq)
1924  {
1925  seq->info.value.data_value.set = node->info.query.q.select.list;
1926  node->info.query.q.select.list = seq;
1927  }
1928 
1929  (void) pt_resolve_hint (parser, node);
1930 
1931  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
1932 
1933  /* capture minimum correlation */
1934  if (!node->info.query.correlation_level)
1935  {
1936  node->info.query.correlation_level = scopestack.correlation_level;
1937  }
1938  else if (scopestack.correlation_level && (scopestack.correlation_level < node->info.query.correlation_level))
1939  {
1940  node->info.query.correlation_level = scopestack.correlation_level;
1941  }
1942 
1943  /* capture type enum and data_type from first column in select list */
1944  if (node && node->info.query.q.select.list)
1945  {
1946  node->type_enum = node->info.query.q.select.list->type_enum;
1947  if (node->info.query.q.select.list->data_type)
1948  {
1949  node->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, node->info.query.q.select.list->data_type);
1950  }
1951  }
1952 
1953  /* pop the extra spec frame and add any extra specs to the from list */
1954  node->info.query.q.select.from = parser_append_node (spec_frame.extra_specs, node->info.query.q.select.from);
1955 
1956  /*
1957  * Oracle style outer join support: convert to ANSI standard style
1958  * only permit the following predicate
1959  * 'single_column(+) op expression_'
1960  * 'expression_ op single_column(+)'
1961  * move outer join predicates from WHERE clause
1962  * to ON condition in FROM clause and set proper join type
1963  */
1964 
1965  if (!PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_ORACLE_OUTER))
1966  {
1967  /* not found */
1968  goto select_end;
1969  }
1970 
1971  if (PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_ANSI_JOIN))
1972  {
1973  /* can not specify the (+) operator in a query that also conatins FROM clause join syntax */
1974  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "can not specify '(+)' with ANSI join syntax");
1975  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1976  node = NULL;
1977  goto select_end;
1978  }
1979 
1980 #if 0
1981  /* By default, support oracle_style_outerjoin */
1982  if (!prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_ORACLE_STYLE_OUTERJOIN))
1983  {
1984  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "Oracle outer join conversion not supported");
1985  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
1986  node = NULL;
1987  goto select_end;
1988  }
1989 #endif /* 0 */
1990 
1991  /* convert to CNF and tag taggable terms */
1992  node->info.query.q.select.where = pt_cnf (parser, node->info.query.q.select.where);
1993 
1994  /* list search twice one-pass: set outer join type, edge two-pass: set outer join sarg outer join sarg matrix:
1995  * X.i=Y.i and Y.i=Z.i and Y.j=1 case 1: X right Y right Z -> put Y(+)-sarg to Z case 2: X right Y left Z ->
1996  * meaningless Y(+)-sarg case 3: X left Y right Z -> syntax error at one-pass case 4: X left Y left Z -> put
1997  * Y(+)-sarg to Y */
1998 
1999  for (k = 1; k <= 2; k++)
2000  {
2001  prev = NULL; /* init */
2002  for (cnf = node->info.query.q.select.where; cnf; cnf = next)
2003  {
2004  next = cnf->next; /* save link */
2005 
2006  if (cnf->node_type != PT_EXPR)
2007  {
2008  prev = cnf;
2009  continue;
2010  }
2011 
2012  if (PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (cnf, PT_EXPR_INFO_LEFT_OUTER))
2013  {
2014  join_type = PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER;
2015  }
2016  else if (PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (cnf, PT_EXPR_INFO_RIGHT_OUTER))
2017  {
2018  join_type = PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER;
2019  }
2020  else
2021  {
2022  prev = cnf;
2023  continue;
2024  }
2025 
2026  /* find left-hand side spec */
2027  lhs = cnf->info.expr.arg1;
2028  lhs_spec = NULL;
2029  lhs_location = 0; /* init */
2030  if (lhs)
2031  {
2032  if (pt_is_attr (lhs))
2033  {
2034  if (lhs->node_type == PT_DOT_)
2035  {
2036  /* check for path expression */
2037  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_PATH_EXPR,
2038  pt_short_print (parser, node));
2039  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2040  node = NULL;
2041  goto select_end;
2042  }
2043 
2044  /* find the class of the lhs from spec list */
2045  for (i = 0, spec = node->info.query.q.select.from; spec; i++, spec = spec->next)
2046  {
2047  /* found spec */
2048  if (spec->info.spec.id == lhs->info.name.spec_id)
2049  {
2050  lhs_spec = spec;
2051  lhs_location = i;
2052  break;
2053  }
2054  }
2055  }
2056  else if (!pt_is_const (lhs)) /* is_const : no nothing */
2057  {
2058  /* find the class of the lhs from spec list */
2059  last = save = NULL; /* init */
2060  do
2061  {
2062  for (i = -1, spec = node->info.query.q.select.from; spec && spec != last;
2063  i++, spec = spec->next)
2064  {
2065  save = spec;
2066  }
2067  last = save; /* set last spec */
2068 
2069  /* traverse tree to find spec */
2070  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_spec = last;
2071  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_attr_num = 0;
2072  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_subq_num = 0;
2073  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_path_num = 0;
2074  parser_walk_tree (parser, lhs, pt_check_Oracle_outerjoin, bind_arg, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
2075  if (bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_attr_num > 0)
2076  {
2077  lhs_spec = last;
2078  lhs_location = i;
2079  }
2080  /* check for subquery */
2081  if (bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_subq_num > 0)
2082  {
2083  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
2084  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_JOIN_COND_SUBQ);
2085  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2086  node = NULL;
2087  goto select_end;
2088  }
2089  /* check for path expression */
2090  if (bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_path_num > 0)
2091  {
2092  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_PATH_EXPR,
2093  pt_short_print (parser, node));
2094  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2095  node = NULL;
2096  goto select_end;
2097  }
2098  }
2099  while (lhs_spec == NULL && i > 0);
2100  }
2101  } /* if (lhs) */
2102 
2103  /* find right-hand side spec */
2104  rhs = cnf->info.expr.arg2;
2105  rhs_spec = NULL;
2106  rhs_location = 0; /* init */
2107  if (rhs)
2108  {
2109  if (pt_is_attr (rhs))
2110  {
2111  if (rhs->node_type == PT_DOT_)
2112  {
2113  /* check for path expression */
2114  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_PATH_EXPR,
2115  pt_short_print (parser, node));
2116  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2117  node = NULL;
2118  goto select_end;
2119  }
2120 
2121  /* find the class of the rhs from spec list */
2122  for (i = 0, spec = node->info.query.q.select.from; spec; i++, spec = spec->next)
2123  {
2124  /* found spec */
2125  if (spec->info.spec.id == rhs->info.name.spec_id)
2126  {
2127  rhs_spec = spec;
2128  rhs_location = i;
2129  break;
2130  }
2131  }
2132  }
2133  else if (!pt_is_const (rhs)) /* is_const : do nothing */
2134  {
2135  /* find the class of the rhs from spec list */
2136  last = save = NULL; /* init */
2137  do
2138  {
2139  for (i = -1, spec = node->info.query.q.select.from; spec && spec != last;
2140  i++, spec = spec->next)
2141  {
2142  save = spec;
2143  }
2144  last = save; /* set last spec */
2145 
2146  /* traverse tree to find spec */
2147  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_spec = last;
2148  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_attr_num = 0;
2149  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_subq_num = 0;
2150  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_path_num = 0;
2151  parser_walk_tree (parser, rhs, pt_check_Oracle_outerjoin, bind_arg, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
2152  if (bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_attr_num > 0)
2153  {
2154  rhs_spec = last;
2155  rhs_location = i;
2156  }
2157  /* check for subquery */
2158  if (bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_subq_num > 0)
2159  {
2160  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
2161  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_JOIN_COND_SUBQ);
2162  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2163  node = NULL;
2164  goto select_end;
2165  }
2166  /* check for path expression */
2167  if (bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_path_num > 0)
2168  {
2169  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUTERJOIN_PATH_EXPR,
2170  pt_short_print (parser, node));
2171  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2172  node = NULL;
2173  goto select_end;
2174  }
2175  }
2176  while (rhs_spec == NULL && i > 0);
2177  }
2178  } /* if (rhs) */
2179 
2180  if (k == 1)
2181  {
2182  /* first search: only consider edges and skip sargs */
2183  if (lhs_spec && rhs_spec && lhs_spec->info.spec.id != rhs_spec->info.spec.id)
2184  {
2185  /* found edge: set join type and spec */
2186  if (lhs_location < rhs_location)
2187  {
2188  p_spec = lhs_spec;
2189  spec = rhs_spec;
2190  }
2191  else
2192  {
2193  /* converse join type of edge for example SELECT... FROM x, y WHERE y.i = x.i(+) */
2194  join_type = (join_type == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER) ? PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER : PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER;
2195  p_spec = rhs_spec;
2196  spec = lhs_spec;
2197  }
2198  }
2199  else
2200  {
2201  prev = cnf;
2202  continue;
2203  }
2204  }
2205  else
2206  {
2207  p_spec = NULL; /* useless */
2208  spec = (lhs_location < rhs_location) ? rhs_spec : lhs_spec;
2209  }
2210 
2211  /* error check */
2212  if (spec == NULL)
2213  {
2214  /* give up */
2215  PT_ERRORf (parser, node, "check outer join syntax at '%s'", pt_short_print (parser, cnf));
2216  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2217  node = NULL;
2218  goto select_end;
2219  }
2220 
2221  if (k == 1)
2222  {
2223  /* first search: check outer join link set join type and edge */
2224 
2225  PT_NODE *tmp, *p_end, *s_end, *start, *end, *s_start;
2226 
2227  if (spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE)
2228  {
2229  /* case A, C */
2230  p_end = p_spec; /* init */
2231  for (tmp = p_end; tmp->next != spec; tmp = tmp->next)
2232  {
2233  /* found end of p_spec join_list */
2234  if (tmp->next->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE)
2235  {
2236  p_end = tmp;
2237  break;
2238  }
2239  else
2240  {
2241  p_end = tmp->next;
2242  }
2243  }
2244  for (tmp = p_end; tmp->next != spec; tmp = tmp->next)
2245  {
2246  ;
2247  }
2248  /* found before node of spec join list: cut-off link */
2249  tmp->next = NULL;
2250 
2251  for (tmp = spec; tmp->next; tmp = tmp->next)
2252  {
2253  ;
2254  }
2255  /* found end of spec list */
2256  s_end = tmp;
2257 
2258  s_end->next = p_end->next;
2259  p_end->next = spec;
2260  }
2261  else
2262  {
2263  for (tmp = p_spec->next; tmp != spec; tmp = tmp->next)
2264  {
2265  /* join_list disconnected */
2266  if (tmp->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE)
2267  {
2268  break;
2269  }
2270  }
2271  if (tmp != spec)
2272  { /* p_spec to spec join_list not exists */
2273  if (p_spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE)
2274  {
2275  /* case B */
2276  s_start = NULL; /* init */
2277  start = tmp; /* init */
2278  end = spec; /* init */
2279  do
2280  {
2281  for (tmp = start; tmp->next != end; tmp = tmp->next)
2282  {
2283  ;
2284  }
2285  if (tmp->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE)
2286  {
2287  /* found spec join_link start */
2288  s_start = tmp;
2289  for (tmp = node->info.query.q.select.from; tmp->next != s_start; tmp = tmp->next)
2290  {
2291  ;
2292  }
2293  /* found before node of spec join_list: cut-off link */
2294  tmp->next = NULL;
2295  }
2296  else
2297  {
2298  end = tmp;
2299  }
2300  }
2301  while (s_start == NULL); /* end do */
2302 
2303  for (tmp = spec; tmp->next; tmp = tmp->next)
2304  {
2305  ;
2306  }
2307  /* found end of spec list */
2308  s_end = tmp;
2309 
2310  s_end->next = node->info.query.q.select.from;
2311  node->info.query.q.select.from = s_start;
2312 
2313  /* swap p_spec, spec */
2314  save = p_spec;
2315  p_spec = spec;
2316  spec = save;
2317 
2318  /* converse join type */
2319  join_type = (join_type == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER) ? PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER : PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER;
2320  }
2321  else
2322  {
2323  /* case D: give up */
2324  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "a class may be outer joined to" " at most one other class");
2325  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2326  node = NULL;
2327  goto select_end;
2328  }
2329  }
2330  }
2331  /* outer join_link handling end */
2332 
2333  /* set join type */
2334  if ((spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER
2335  || spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER) && spec->info.spec.join_type != join_type)
2336  {
2337  /* give up */
2338  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "two classes cannot be " "outer-joined to each other");
2339  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2340  node = NULL;
2341  goto select_end;
2342  }
2343  spec->info.spec.join_type = join_type;
2344  }
2345  else
2346  { /* k == 2 */
2347  /* second search: set sarg */
2348  if (spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER && spec->next)
2349  {
2350  if (spec->next->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER)
2351  {
2352  /* check for case 1: */
2353  spec = spec->next;
2354  }
2355  else if (spec->next->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER)
2356  {
2357  /* check for case 2: meaningless outer join sargs */
2358  prev = cnf;
2359  continue;
2360  }
2361  }
2362 
2363  /* check for case 4: do nothing and go ahead */
2364  }
2365 
2366  /* cut-off cnf from WHERE clause */
2367  if (prev == NULL)
2368  { /* the first cnf */
2369  node->info.query.q.select.where = next;
2370  }
2371  else
2372  {
2373  prev->next = next;
2374  }
2375  cnf->next = NULL; /* cut-off link */
2376 
2377  /* put cnf to the ON cond */
2378  spec->info.spec.on_cond = parser_append_node (cnf, spec->info.spec.on_cond);
2379  }
2380  }
2381 
2382  for (spec = node->info.query.q.select.from; spec; spec = spec->next)
2383  {
2384  if (spec->info.spec.on_cond)
2385  {
2386  /* check for case 3: */
2387  if (spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER && spec->next
2388  && spec->next->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER)
2389  {
2390  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "a class may be outer joined to " "at most one other class");
2391  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2392  node = NULL;
2393  goto select_end;
2394  }
2395  else if (spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER)
2396  {
2397  for (save = node->info.query.q.select.from; save; save = save->next)
2398  {
2399  if (save->next == spec)
2400  {
2401  if (save->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER)
2402  {
2403  PT_ERROR (parser, node, "a class may be outer joined to " "at most one other class");
2404  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
2405  node = NULL;
2406  goto select_end;
2407  }
2408  }
2409  } /* for */
2410  }
2411 
2412 
2413  /* clear spec_id to re-check outer join semantic */
2414  bind_arg->sc_info->Oracle_outerjoin_spec = spec;
2415  parser_walk_tree (parser, spec->info.spec.on_cond, pt_clear_Oracle_outerjoin_spec_id, bind_arg,
2416  pt_continue_walk, NULL);
2417  }
2418  }
2419 
2420  /* check outer join semantic of ON cond */
2421  bind_arg->scopes->specs = node->info.query.q.select.from; /* init */
2422  bind_arg->scopes->location = 0; /* init */
2423  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.from, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2424 
2425  /* meaningless outer join check */
2426  for (spec = node->info.query.q.select.from; spec; spec = spec->next)
2427  {
2428  if (spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE && spec->info.spec.on_cond)
2429  {
2430  /* meaningless outer join predicate for example SELECT... FROM x, y WHERE x.i(+) = 1 recover to WHERE
2431  * clause */
2432  node->info.query.q.select.where =
2433  parser_append_node (spec->info.spec.on_cond, node->info.query.q.select.where);
2434  spec->info.spec.on_cond = NULL;
2435  }
2436  } /* for */
2437 
2438  select_end:
2439  bind_arg->spec_frames = bind_arg->spec_frames->next;
2440 
2441  /* remove this level's scope */
2442  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2443 
2444  /* don't revisit leaves */
2445  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2446  break;
2447 
2448  case PT_UNION:
2449  case PT_INTERSECTION:
2450  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
2451  {
2452  int arg1_corr, arg2_corr, corr;
2453  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2;
2454  PT_NODE *select_node = NULL, *order_by_link = NULL;
2455  int index_of_order_by_link = -1;
2456 
2457  /* treat this just like a select with no from, so that we can properly get correlation level of sub-queries. */
2458  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
2459 
2460  pt_bind_names_in_with_clause (parser, node, bind_arg);
2461 
2462  /* change order by link in UNION/INTERSECTION/DIFFERENCE query into the tail of first select query's order by
2463  * list for bind names (It will be restored after bind names.) */
2464 
2465  if (node->info.query.order_by)
2466  {
2467  index_of_order_by_link = 0;
2468 
2469  select_node = node;
2470  while (select_node)
2471  {
2472  switch (select_node->node_type)
2473  {
2474  case PT_SELECT:
2475  goto l_select_node;
2476  break;
2477  case PT_UNION:
2478  case PT_INTERSECTION:
2479  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
2480  select_node = select_node->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
2481  break;
2482  default:
2483  select_node = NULL;
2484  break;
2485  }
2486  }
2487 
2488  l_select_node:
2489  if (select_node)
2490  {
2491  if (!select_node->info.query.order_by)
2492  {
2493  select_node->info.query.order_by = node->info.query.order_by;
2494  }
2495  else
2496  {
2497  index_of_order_by_link++;
2498  order_by_link = select_node->info.query.order_by;
2499  while (order_by_link->next)
2500  {
2501  order_by_link = order_by_link->next;
2502  index_of_order_by_link++;
2503  }
2504 
2505  order_by_link->next = node->info.query.order_by;
2506  }
2507 
2508  node->info.query.order_by = NULL;
2509  }
2510  }
2511 
2512  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2513 
2514  arg1 = node->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
2515  arg2 = node->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
2516 
2517  if (arg1 && arg2)
2518  {
2519  arg1_corr = arg1->info.query.correlation_level;
2520  arg2_corr = arg2->info.query.correlation_level;
2521  if (arg1_corr)
2522  {
2523  corr = arg1_corr;
2524  if (arg2_corr)
2525  {
2526  if (arg2_corr < corr)
2527  corr = arg2_corr;
2528  }
2529  }
2530  else
2531  {
2532  corr = arg2_corr;
2533  }
2534  /* must reduce the correlation level 1, for this level of scoping */
2535  if (corr)
2536  {
2537  corr--;
2538  }
2539  node->info.query.correlation_level = corr;
2540 
2541  /* capture type enum and data_type from arg1 */
2542  node->type_enum = arg1->type_enum;
2543  if (arg1->data_type)
2544  node->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, arg1->data_type);
2545  }
2546 
2547  /* Restore order by link */
2548  if (index_of_order_by_link >= 0)
2549  {
2550  if (order_by_link)
2551  {
2552  node->info.query.order_by = order_by_link->next;
2553  order_by_link->next = NULL;
2554  }
2555  else
2556  {
2557  node->info.query.order_by = select_node->info.query.order_by;
2558  select_node->info.query.order_by = NULL;
2559  }
2560  }
2561  }
2562 
2563  /* remove this level's scope */
2564  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2565 
2566  /* don't revisit leaves */
2567  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2568  break;
2569 
2570  case PT_UPDATE:
2571  scopestack.specs = node->info.update.spec;
2572  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
2573  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
2574 
2575  /* break links to current scopes to bind_names in the WITH_CLAUSE */
2576  bind_arg->scopes = NULL;
2577  bind_arg->spec_frames = NULL;
2578  pt_bind_names_in_with_clause (parser, node, bind_arg);
2579 
2580  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame.next;
2581 
2582  /* restore links to current scopes */
2583  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
2584  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
2585  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
2586  bind_arg->spec_frames = &spec_frame;
2587  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
2588 
2589  (void) pt_resolve_hint (parser, node);
2590 
2591  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2592 
2593  /* pop the extra spec frame and add any extra specs to the from list */
2594  bind_arg->spec_frames = bind_arg->spec_frames->next;
2595  node->info.update.class_specs = parser_append_node (spec_frame.extra_specs, node->info.update.class_specs);
2596 
2597  /* remove this level's scope */
2598  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2599 
2600  /* don't revisit leaves */
2601  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2602  break;
2603 
2604  case PT_DELETE:
2605  scopestack.specs = node->info.delete_.spec;
2606  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
2607  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
2608 
2609  /* break links to current scopes to bind_names in the WITH_CLAUSE */
2610  bind_arg->scopes = NULL;
2611  bind_arg->spec_frames = NULL;
2612  pt_bind_names_in_with_clause (parser, node, bind_arg);
2613 
2614  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame.next;
2615 
2616  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
2617  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
2618  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
2619  bind_arg->spec_frames = &spec_frame;
2620  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
2621 
2622  (void) pt_resolve_hint (parser, node);
2623 
2624  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2625 
2626  /* pop the extra spec frame and add any extra specs to the from list */
2627  bind_arg->spec_frames = bind_arg->spec_frames->next;
2628  node->info.delete_.class_specs = parser_append_node (spec_frame.extra_specs, node->info.delete_.class_specs);
2629 
2630  /* remove this level's scope */
2631  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2632 
2633  /* don't revisit leaves */
2634  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2635  break;
2636 
2637  case PT_INSERT:
2638  scopestack.specs = node->info.insert.spec;
2639  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
2640  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
2641  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
2642  bind_arg->spec_frames = &spec_frame;
2643  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
2644 
2645  result = pt_resolve_vclass_args (parser, node);
2646  if (!result)
2647  {
2648  /* error is handled */
2649  goto insert_end;
2650  }
2651  node = result;
2652 
2653  if (!node->info.insert.attr_list)
2654  {
2655  node->info.insert.attr_list = pt_resolve_star (parser, node->info.insert.spec, NULL);
2656  }
2657 
2658  fill_in_insert_default_function_arguments (parser, node);
2659 
2660  /* Do not handle ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE yet, we need to resolve the other nodes first. */
2661  save = node->info.insert.odku_assignments;
2662  node->info.insert.odku_assignments = NULL;
2663 
2664  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2665 
2666  /* Check for double assignments */
2667  pt_no_double_insert_assignments (parser, node);
2668  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2669  {
2670  goto insert_end;
2671  }
2672 
2673  /* flag any "correlated" names as undefined. only names in subqueries and sub-inserts should be undefined. use
2674  * spec->etc to store the correlation level in value_clauses. */
2675  save_etc = node->info.insert.spec->etc;
2676  level = 0;
2677  node->info.insert.spec->etc = &level;
2678  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.insert.value_clauses, pt_undef_names_pre, node->info.insert.spec,
2679  pt_undef_names_post, node->info.insert.spec);
2680  node->info.insert.spec->etc = save_etc;
2681 
2682  if (save != NULL)
2683  {
2684  SCOPES extended_scope;
2685  PT_NODE *value_list = node->info.insert.value_clauses->info.node_list.list;
2686  extended_scope.next = NULL;
2687 
2688  /* restore ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE node */
2689  node->info.insert.odku_assignments = save;
2690 
2691  /* pt_undef_names_pre may have generated an error */
2692  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2693  {
2694  goto insert_end;
2695  }
2696 
2697  if (PT_IS_SELECT (value_list))
2698  {
2699  /* Some assignments may reference attributes from the select query that need to be resolved too. Add the
2700  * specs from the select statement as a scope in the stack. */
2701  extended_scope.next = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2702  extended_scope.specs = value_list->info.query.q.select.from;
2703  scopestack.correlation_level = 0;
2704  scopestack.location = 0;
2705  bind_arg->scopes->next = &extended_scope;
2706  }
2707 
2708  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.insert.odku_assignments, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post,
2709  bind_arg);
2710 
2711  if (PT_IS_SELECT (value_list))
2712  {
2713  /* restore original scopes */
2714  bind_arg->scopes->next = extended_scope.next;
2715  }
2716  }
2717 
2718  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
2719  {
2720  /* make sure attributes were not bound to parameters */
2721  for (attr = node->info.insert.attr_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
2722  {
2723  if (attr->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)
2724  {
2725  /* this is not an attribute of insert spec */
2726  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, attr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_ATTRIBUTE_OF,
2727  attr->info.name.original,
2728  node->info.insert.spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original);
2729  }
2730  }
2731  }
2732 
2733  insert_end:
2734  /* pop the extra spec frame and add any extra specs to the from list */
2735  bind_arg->spec_frames = bind_arg->spec_frames->next;
2736  node->info.insert.class_specs = parser_append_node (spec_frame.extra_specs, node->info.insert.class_specs);
2737 
2738  /* remove this level's scope */
2739  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2740 
2741  /* don't revisit leaves */
2742  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2743  break;
2744 
2745  case PT_MERGE:
2746  if (node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
2747  {
2748  /* resolve missing attr_list as star */
2749  if (!node->info.merge.insert.attr_list)
2750  {
2751  node->info.merge.insert.attr_list = pt_resolve_star (parser, node->info.merge.into, NULL);
2752  }
2753  /* resolve DEFAULT clauses */
2754  if (node->info.merge.into->info.spec.entity_name)
2755  {
2756  fill_in_insert_default_function_arguments (parser, node);
2757  }
2758  /* resolve insert attributes, values */
2759  pt_bind_names_merge_insert (parser, node, bind_arg, &scopestack, &spec_frame);
2760  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2761  {
2762  node = NULL;
2763  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2764  break;
2765  }
2766  }
2767 
2768  if (node->info.merge.update.assignment)
2769  {
2770  /* resolved update assignment list */
2771  pt_bind_names_merge_update (parser, node, bind_arg, &scopestack, &spec_frame);
2772  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2773  {
2774  node = NULL;
2775  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2776  break;
2777  }
2778  }
2779 
2780  assert (node->info.merge.into->next == NULL);
2781  node->info.merge.into->next = node->info.merge.using_clause;
2782 
2783  scopestack.specs = node->info.merge.into;
2784  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
2785  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
2786  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
2787  bind_arg->spec_frames = &spec_frame;
2788  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
2789  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2790  {
2791  node = NULL;
2792  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2793  break;
2794  }
2795 
2796  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2797  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2798  {
2799  node = NULL;
2800  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2801  break;
2802  }
2803 
2804  /* flag any "correlated" names as undefined. make sure etc is NULL. */
2805  save_etc = node->info.merge.into->etc;
2806  node->info.merge.into->etc = NULL;
2807  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses, pt_undef_names_pre, node->info.merge.into, NULL,
2808  NULL);
2809  node->info.merge.into->etc = save_etc;
2810  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2811  {
2812  node = NULL;
2813  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2814  break;
2815  }
2816 
2817  bind_arg->spec_frames = bind_arg->spec_frames->next;
2818  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2819 
2820  /* don't revisit leaves */
2821  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2822 
2823  node->info.merge.into->next = NULL;
2824  break;
2825 
2826  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
2827  case PT_ALTER_INDEX:
2828  case PT_DROP_INDEX:
2829  scopestack.specs = node->info.index.indexed_class;
2830  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
2831  spec_frame.next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
2832  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
2833  bind_arg->spec_frames = &spec_frame;
2834  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
2835 
2836  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2837 
2838  bind_arg->spec_frames = bind_arg->spec_frames->next;
2839  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
2840 
2841  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2842  break;
2843 
2844  case PT_METHOD_CALL:
2845  /*
2846  * We accept two different method call syntax:
2847  * 1) method_name(...) on target
2848  * 2) method_name(target, ...)
2849  * We need to normalize the second to the first so that we can do
2850  * resolution without special cases. We do this by moving the
2851  * first parameter to the on_call_target. If there is no parameter,
2852  * it will be caught in pt_semantic_check_local()
2853  */
2854  if (!node->info.method_call.on_call_target
