2855  && jsp_is_exist_stored_procedure (node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original))
2856  {
2857  node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id = (UINTPTR) node->info.method_call.method_name;
2858  node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_METHOD;
2859  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2860  /* don't revisit leaves */
2861  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2862  }
2863  else
2864  {
2865  if (!node->info.method_call.on_call_target && node->info.method_call.arg_list)
2866  {
2867  node->info.method_call.on_call_target = node->info.method_call.arg_list;
2868  node->info.method_call.arg_list = node->info.method_call.arg_list->next;
2869  node->info.method_call.on_call_target->next = NULL;
2870  }
2871 
2872  /* make method name look resolved */
2873  node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id = (UINTPTR) node->info.method_call.method_name;
2874  node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_METHOD;
2875 
2876  /*
2877  * bind the names in the method arguments and target, their
2878  * scope will be the same as the method node's scope
2879  */
2880  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
2881  /* don't revisit leaves */
2882  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2883 
2884  /* find the type of the method here */
2885  if (!pt_resolve_method_type (parser, node) && (node->info.method_call.call_or_expr != PT_IS_CALL_STMT))
2886  {
2887  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_DOESNT_EXIST,
2888  node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original);
2889  break;
2890  }
2891 
2892  /* if it is a call statement, we don't want to resolve method_name. also, if scopes is NULL we assume this
2893  * came from an evaluate call and we treat it like a call statement */
2894  if ((node->info.method_call.call_or_expr == PT_IS_CALL_STMT) || (bind_arg->scopes == NULL))
2895  {
2896  break;
2897  }
2898 
2899  /* resolve method name to entity where expansion will take place */
2900  if (node->info.method_call.on_call_target->node_type == PT_NAME
2901  && (node->info.method_call.on_call_target->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER))
2902  {
2903  PT_NODE *entity = pt_find_entity_in_scopes (parser, bind_arg->scopes,
2904  node->info.method_call.on_call_target->info.name.spec_id);
2905  /* no entity found will be caught as an error later. Probably an unresolvable target. */
2906  if (entity)
2907  {
2908  node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
2909  }
2910  }
2911 
2912  }
2913 
2914  break;
2915 
2916  case PT_DATA_TYPE:
2917  /* don't visit leaves unless this is an object which might contain a name (i.e. CAST(value AS name) ) */
2918  if (node->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
2919  {
2920  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2921  }
2922  break;
2923 
2924  case PT_NAME:
2925  {
2926  PT_NODE *temp;
2927 
2928  if (node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MAYBE)
2929  {
2930  /* reset spec_id to rebind the name/type */
2931  node->info.name.spec_id = 0;
2932  }
2933 
2934  temp = pt_bind_name_or_path_in_scope (parser, bind_arg, node);
2935  if (temp)
2936  {
2937  node = temp;
2938  /* don't visit leaves */
2939  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2940  }
2941  else
2942  {
2943  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2944  }
2945  }
2946  break;
2947 
2948  case PT_DOT_:
2949  {
2950  PT_NODE *temp;
2951  temp = pt_bind_name_or_path_in_scope (parser, bind_arg, node);
2952  if (temp)
2953  {
2954  node = temp;
2955  }
2956  else if (pt_has_error (parser))
2957  {
2958  return NULL;
2959  }
2960 
2961  if (!(node->node_type == PT_DOT_
2962  && (node->info.dot.arg2->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL || node->info.dot.arg2->node_type == PT_FUNCTION)))
2963  {
2964  /* don't revisit leaves */
2965  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
2966  }
2967 
2968  /* handle dot print format; do not print resolved name for arg2. for example: (CLASS_A, CLASS_B, CLASS_C is
2969  * class) CLASS_A.b.CLASS_B.c.CLASS_C.name; -> CLASS_A.b.c.name; */
2970  if (node->node_type == PT_DOT_)
2971  {
2972  PT_NODE *arg2;
2973 
2974  for (temp = node; temp->node_type == PT_DOT_; temp = temp->info.dot.arg1)
2975  {
2976  /* arg2 is PT_NAME node */
2977  arg2 = temp->info.dot.arg2;
2978  if (arg2 && arg2->node_type == PT_NAME)
2979  {
2980  arg2->info.name.custom_print |= PT_SUPPRESS_RESOLVED;
2981  }
2982  } /* for (temp = ...) */
2983  }
2984  }
2985  break;
2986 
2987  case PT_FUNCTION:
2988  if (node->info.function.function_type == PT_GENERIC)
2989  {
2990  node->info.function.function_type = pt_find_function_type (node->info.function.generic_name);
2991 
2992  if (node->info.function.function_type == PT_GENERIC)
2993  {
2994  /*
2995  * It may be a method call since they are parsed as
2996  * nodes PT_FUNCTION. If so, pt_make_method_call() will
2997  * translate it into a method_call.
2998  */
2999  node1 = pt_make_method_call (parser, node, bind_arg);
3000 
3001  if (node1->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL)
3002  {
3003  PT_NODE_INIT_OUTERLINK (node);
3004  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
3005  node = node1; /* return the new node */
3006  /* don't revisit leaves */
3007  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
3008  }
3009  else
3010  {
3011  /* It may be a generic function supported on the server. We put this case last so that user written
3012  * methods will resolve before trying to make it a server function. */
3013  if (!pt_type_generic_func (parser, node))
3014  {
3015  PT_NODE *top_node = NULL;
3016  int is_spec_attr = 0;
3017 
3018  /* get top node */
3019  if (bind_arg != NULL && bind_arg->sc_info != NULL)
3020  {
3021  top_node = bind_arg->sc_info->top_node;
3022  }
3023 
3024  if (top_node != NULL
3025  && (top_node->node_type == PT_CREATE_INDEX || top_node->node_type == PT_ALTER_INDEX
3026  || (top_node->node_type == PT_ALTER && (top_node->info.alter.create_index != NULL))))
3027  {
3028  /* check if function name is a spec attribute */
3029  if (pt_function_name_is_spec_attr (parser, node, bind_arg, &is_spec_attr) != NO_ERROR)
3030  {
3031  return NULL;
3032  }
3033  }
3034 
3035  /* show appropriate error message */
3036  if (is_spec_attr)
3037  {
3038  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
3039  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PREFIX_IN_FUNC_INDX_NOT_ALLOWED);
3040  }
3041  else if (parser_function_code != PT_EMPTY)
3042  {
3043  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
3044  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_INTERNAL_FUNCTION, node->info.function.generic_name);
3045  }
3046  else
3047  {
3048  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNKNOWN_FUNCTION,
3049  node->info.function.generic_name);
3050  }
3051 
3052  }
3053  }
3054  }
3055  else if (node->info.function.function_type < F_TOP_TABLE_FUNC)
3056  {
3057  PT_NODE *arg_list = node->info.function.arg_list;
3058 
3059  /* arg list must be a single subquery */
3060 
3061  if (arg_list->next
3062  || (arg_list->node_type != PT_SELECT && arg_list->node_type != PT_UNION
3063  && arg_list->node_type != PT_DIFFERENCE && arg_list->node_type != PT_INTERSECTION))
3064  {
3065  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_SINGLE_TABLE_IN,
3066  pt_short_print (parser, node));
3067  }
3068  }
3069  }
3070  break;
3071 
3072  case PT_SPEC:
3073  if (bind_arg->scopes)
3074  {
3075  node->info.spec.location = bind_arg->scopes->location++;
3076  }
3077  if (node->info.spec.on_cond)
3078  {
3079  switch (node->info.spec.join_type)
3080  {
3081  case PT_JOIN_INNER:
3082  case PT_JOIN_LEFT_OUTER:
3083  case PT_JOIN_RIGHT_OUTER:
3084  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.spec.on_cond, pt_mark_location, &(node->info.spec.location), NULL,
3085  NULL);
3086  break;
3087  /* case PT_JOIN_FULL_OUTER: *//* not supported */
3088 
3089  case PT_JOIN_NONE:
3090  default:
3091  break;
3092  } /* switch (node->info.spec.join_type) */
3093  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.spec.on_cond, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
3094  }
3095  {
3096  PT_NODE *entity_name = node->info.spec.entity_name;
3097  if (entity_name && entity_name->node_type == PT_NAME)
3098  {
3099  entity_name->info.name.location = node->info.spec.location;
3100  if (entity_name->info.name.db_object && db_is_system_class (entity_name->info.name.db_object) > 0)
3101  {
3102  bind_arg->sc_info->system_class = true;
3103  }
3104  }
3105  }
3106 
3107  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
3108  break;
3109 
3110  case PT_HOST_VAR:
3111  pt_bind_type_of_host_var (parser, node);
3112  break;
3113 
3114  case PT_SCOPE:
3115  scopestack.specs = node->info.scope.from;
3116  bind_arg->scopes = &scopestack;
3117  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
3118  parser_walk_leaves (parser, node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
3119 
3120  /* remove this level's scope */
3121  bind_arg->scopes = bind_arg->scopes->next;
3122 
3123  /* don't revisit leaves */
3124  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
3125  break;
3126 
3127  case PT_EXPR:
3128  if (node->info.expr.op == PT_NEXT_VALUE || node->info.expr.op == PT_CURRENT_VALUE)
3129  {
3130  /* don't walk leaves */
3131  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
3132  }
3133  break;
3134 
3135  case PT_WITH_CLAUSE:
3136  /* WITH clause should be resolved from SELECT; don't walk leaves(cte_list) */
3137  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
3138  break;
3139 
3140  case PT_CTE:
3141  pt_bind_names_in_cte (parser, node, bind_arg);
3142  if (pt_has_error (parser))
3143  {
3144  node = NULL;
3145  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
3146  }
3147  else
3148  {
3149  /* don't walk leaves */
3150  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
3151  }
3152  break;
3153 
3154  default:
3155  break;
3156  }
3157 
3158  return node;
3159 }

3161 /*
3162  * pt_bind_value_to_hostvar_local () -
3163  * return:
3164  * parser(in):
3165  * node(in):
3166  * arg(in):
3167  * continue_walk(in):
3168  */
3169 static PT_NODE *
3170 pt_bind_value_to_hostvar_local (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
3171 {
3172  DB_VALUE *value;
3173 
3174  if (node)
3175  {
3176  switch (node->node_type)
3177  {
3178  case PT_HOST_VAR:
3179  if (node->info.host_var.var_type != PT_HOST_IN)
3180  {
3181  break;
3182  }
3183 
3184  value = pt_value_to_db (parser, node);
3185  if (value && prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_HOSTVAR_LATE_BINDING))
3186  {
3187  /* change PT_NAME to PT_VALUE in order to optimize */
3188  /* return node ptr */
3189 
3190  PT_NODE *value_node;
3191 
3192  value_node = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, value);
3193  if (value_node)
3194  {
3195  PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (value_node, node);
3196 
3197  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
3198 
3199  node = value_node;
3200  }
3201  }
3202  break;
3203  default:
3204  break;
3205  }
3206  }
3207 
3208  return node;
3209 } /* pt_bind_value_to_hostvar_local */

3233 /*
3234  * pt_resolve_default_value () - Fills PT_NAME node with default value
3235  *
3236  * return : error code
3237  * parser (in) : parser context
3238  * name (in) : PT_NAME node
3239  *
3240  * NOTE: Filling with default value is forced. After setting default value,
3241  * PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT flag is set.
3242  * Name must be resolved first.
3243  */
3244 int
3245 pt_resolve_default_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * name)
3246 {
3247  DB_ATTRIBUTE *att = NULL;
3248  const char *lang_str;
3249  int flag = 0;
3250  bool has_user_format;
3251 
3252  if (name->node_type != PT_NAME)
3253  {
3254  return NO_ERROR;
3255  }
3256 
3257  if (name->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS || name->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR)
3258  {
3259  return NO_ERROR;
3260  }
3261 
3262  if (name->info.name.original == NULL || name->info.name.resolved == NULL)
3263  {
3264  /* cannot resolve */
3265  return NO_ERROR;
3266  }
3267 
3268  if (name->info.name.default_value != NULL)
3269  {
3270  /* default value was already set */
3271  return NO_ERROR;
3272  }
3273 
3274  att = db_get_attribute_by_name (name->info.name.resolved, name->info.name.original);
3275  if (att == NULL)
3276  {
3277  /* cannot resolve */
3278  return ER_FAILED;
3279  }
3280 
3281  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type != DB_DEFAULT_NONE)
3282  {
3283  /* if the default value is an expression, make a node for it */
3284  PT_OP_TYPE op;
3285  PT_NODE *default_op_value_node;
3286 
3287  op = pt_op_type_from_default_expr_type (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type);
3288  assert (op != (PT_OP_TYPE) 0);
3289  default_op_value_node = pt_expression_0 (parser, op);
3290 
3291  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_op == NULL_DEFAULT_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR)
3292  {
3293  name->info.name.default_value = default_op_value_node;
3294  }
3295  else
3296  {
3297  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2, *arg3;
3298  arg1 = default_op_value_node;
3299  has_user_format = att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format ? 1 : 0;
3300  arg2 = pt_make_string_value (parser, att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format);
3301  if (arg2 == NULL)
3302  {
3303  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value_node);
3304  PT_ERRORm (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3305  return ER_FAILED;
3306  }
3307 
3308  arg3 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
3309  if (arg3 == NULL)
3310  {
3311  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value_node);
3312  parser_free_tree (parser, arg2);
3313  PT_ERRORm (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3314  return ER_FAILED;
3315  }
3316  arg3->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
3317  lang_str = prm_get_string_value (PRM_ID_INTL_DATE_LANG);
3318  lang_set_flag_from_lang (lang_str, has_user_format, 0, &flag);
3319  arg3->info.value.data_value.i = (long) flag;
3320 
3321  name->info.name.default_value = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_TO_CHAR, arg1, arg2, arg3);
3322  if (name->info.name.default_value == NULL)
3323  {
3324  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value_node);
3325  parser_free_tree (parser, arg2);
3326  parser_free_tree (parser, arg3);
3327  return ER_FAILED;
3328  }
3329  }
3330  }
3331  else
3332  {
3333  /* just set the default value */
3334  name->info.name.default_value = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &att->default_value.value);
3335  if (name->info.name.default_value == NULL)
3336  {
3337  PT_ERRORm (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3338  return ER_FAILED;
3339  }
3340  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (att->domain) == DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
3341  {
3342  name->info.name.default_value->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, att->domain);
3343  }
3344  }
3345 
3346  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (name, PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT);
3347  return NO_ERROR;
3348 }

3350 /*
3351  * pt_find_attr_in_class_list () - trying to resolve X.attr
3352  * return: returns a PT_NAME list or NULL
3353  * parser(in):
3354  * flat(in): list of PT_NAME nodes (class names)
3355  * attr(in): a PT_NAME (an attribute name)
3356  */
3357 static int
3358 pt_find_attr_in_class_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * flat, PT_NODE * attr)
3359 {
3360  DB_ATTRIBUTE *att = 0;
3361  DB_OBJECT *db = 0;
3362  PT_NODE *cname = flat;
3363  const char *lang_str;
3364  int flag = 0;
3365  bool has_user_format;
3366 
3367  if (!flat || !attr)
3368  {
3369  return 0;
3370  }
3371 
3372  if (attr->node_type != PT_NAME)
3373  {
3374  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
3375  return 0;
3376  }
3377 
3378  /* For Each class name on the list */
3379  while (cname)
3380  {
3381  if (cname->node_type != PT_NAME)
3382  {
3383  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
3384  return 0;
3385  }
3386 
3387  /* Get the object */
3388  db = cname->info.name.db_object;
3389  if (!db)
3390  {
3391  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
3392  return 0;
3393  }
3394 
3395  /* Does db have an attribute named 'name'? */
3396  att = (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) db_get_attribute_force (db, attr->info.name.original);
3397 
3398  if (!att || attr->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS || attr->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR)
3399  {
3400  int db_err;
3401  db_err = er_errid ();
3402  if (db_err == ER_AU_SELECT_FAILURE || db_err == ER_AU_AUTHORIZATION_FAILURE)
3403  {
3404  PT_ERRORc (parser, attr, er_msg ());
3405  }
3406  return 0;
3407  }
3408 
3409  /* set its type */
3410  pt_get_attr_data_type (parser, att, attr);
3411 
3412  if (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (attr, PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT))
3413  {
3414  if (attr->info.name.default_value != NULL)
3415  {
3416  /* default value was already set */
3417  return 1;
3418  }
3419  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type != DB_DEFAULT_NONE)
3420  {
3421  /* if the default value is an expression, make a node for it */
3422  PT_OP_TYPE op;
3423  PT_NODE *default_op_value_node;
3424 
3425  op = pt_op_type_from_default_expr_type (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type);
3426  assert (op != (PT_OP_TYPE) 0);
3427  default_op_value_node = pt_expression_0 (parser, op);
3428 
3429  if (att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_op == NULL_DEFAULT_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR)
3430  {
3431  attr->info.name.default_value = default_op_value_node;
3432  }
3433  else
3434  {
3435  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2, *arg3;
3436  arg1 = default_op_value_node;
3437  has_user_format = att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format ? 1 : 0;
3438  arg2 = pt_make_string_value (parser, att->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format);
3439  if (arg2 == NULL)
3440  {
3441  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value_node);
3442  PT_ERRORm (parser, attr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3443  return 0;
3444  }
3445 
3446  arg3 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
3447  if (arg3 == NULL)
3448  {
3449  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value_node);
3450  parser_free_tree (parser, arg2);
3451  PT_ERRORm (parser, attr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3452  return 0;
3453  }
3454  arg3->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
3455  lang_str = prm_get_string_value (PRM_ID_INTL_DATE_LANG);
3456  lang_set_flag_from_lang (lang_str, has_user_format, 0, &flag);
3457  arg3->info.value.data_value.i = (long) flag;
3458 
3459  attr->info.name.default_value = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_TO_CHAR, arg1, arg2, arg3);
3460  if (attr->info.name.default_value == NULL)
3461  {
3462  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value_node);
3463  parser_free_tree (parser, arg2);
3464  parser_free_tree (parser, arg3);
3465  PT_ERRORm (parser, attr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3466  return 0;
3467  }
3468  }
3469  }
3470  else
3471  {
3472  /* just set the default value */
3473  attr->info.name.default_value = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &att->default_value.value);
3474  if (attr->info.name.default_value == NULL)
3475  {
3476  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
3477  return 0;
3478  }
3479  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (att->domain) == DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
3480  {
3481  attr->info.name.default_value->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, att->domain);
3482  }
3483  }
3484  }
3485 
3486  cname = cname->next;
3487  }
3488  attr->info.name.spec_id = flat->info.name.spec_id;
3489 
3490  return 1;
3491 }

3493 /*
3494  * pt_find_class_attribute() - try to resolve attr as a class attribute of cls
3495  * return: 1 if all OK, 0 otherwise.
3496  * parser(in): the parser context
3497  * cls(in): the name of a class
3498  * attr(in/out): the name of an attribute
3499  */
3500 static int
3501 pt_find_class_attribute (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * cls, PT_NODE * attr)
3502 {
3503  DB_ATTRIBUTE *att;
3504  DB_OBJECT *db;
3505 
3506  if (!parser || !cls || cls->node_type != PT_NAME || !attr || attr->node_type != PT_NAME)
3507  return 0;
3508 
3509  db = cls->info.name.db_object;
3510 
3511  /* Does db have a class attribute named 'name'? */
3512  att = (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) db_get_class_attribute (db, attr->info.name.original);
3513 
3514  if (!att)
3515  {
3516  int db_err;
3517 
3518  db_err = er_errid ();
3519  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
3520  {
3521  if (db_err == ER_AU_SELECT_FAILURE || db_err == ER_AU_AUTHORIZATION_FAILURE)
3522  {
3523  PT_ERRORc (parser, cls, er_msg ());
3524  }
3525  }
3526  return 0;
3527  }
3528 
3529  attr->info.name.db_object = db;
3530 
3531  /* set its type */
3532  pt_get_attr_data_type (parser, att, attr);
3533 
3534  /* mark it as resolved */
3535  attr->info.name.spec_id = cls->info.name.spec_id;
3536  /* mark it as a class attribute */
3537  attr->info.name.meta_class = PT_META_ATTR;

3542 /*
3543  * pt_find_name_in_spec () - Given a spec, see if name can be resolved to this
3544  * return: 0 if name is NOT an attribute of spec
3545  * parser(in):
3546  * spec(in):
3547  * name(in): a PT_NAME (an attribute name)
3548  */
3549 static int
3550 pt_find_name_in_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * name)
3551 {
3552  int ok;
3553  PT_NODE *col;
3554  PT_NODE *range_var;
3555  const char *resolved_name;
3556 
3557  if (spec == NULL)
3558  {
3559  return 0;
3560  }
3561 
3562  if (name->info.name.meta_class == PT_CLASS)
3563  {
3564  /* should resolve to a class name later, don't search attributes */
3565  return 0;
3566  }
3567 
3568  resolved_name = name->info.name.resolved;
3569  range_var = spec->info.spec.range_var;
3570  if (resolved_name && range_var)
3571  {
3572  if (pt_str_compare (resolved_name, range_var->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) != 0)
3573  {
3574  return 0;
3575  }
3576  }
3577 
3578  if (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec))
3579  {
3580  if (spec->info.spec.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS)
3581  {
3582  ok = pt_find_class_attribute (parser, spec->info.spec.entity_name, name);
3583  }
3584  else
3585  {
3586  ok = pt_find_attr_in_class_list (parser, spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list, name);
3587  }
3588  }
3589  else
3590  {
3591  assert (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec) || PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (spec));
3592  col = pt_is_on_list (parser, name, spec->info.spec.as_attr_list);
3593  ok = (col != NULL);
3594  if (col && !name->info.name.spec_id)
3595  {
3596  name->type_enum = col->type_enum;
3597  if (col->data_type)
3598  {
3599  name->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, col->data_type);
3600  }
3601  name->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
3602  name->info.name.meta_class = PT_NORMAL;
3603  }
3604  }
3605 
3606  return ok;
3607 }
3608 
3609 /*
3610  * pt_check_same_datatype() - All DATA_TYPE info fields are compared
3611  * SET_OF() types must match exactly
3612  * return: returns 1 if p & q have the same type
3613  * parser(in): the parser context
3614  * p(in): any PT_NODE
3615  * q(in): any PT_NODE
3616  *
3617  * Note :
3618  * OBJECT types must refer to the same class name.
3619  * Primitive types have to be IDENTICAL, not just compatible.
3620  */
3621 int
3622 pt_check_same_datatype (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * p, const PT_NODE * q)
3623 {
3624  PT_NODE *s, *t, *v;
3625  PT_NODE *dt1, *dt2;
3626 
3627  if (!p || !q || !parser)
3628  {
3629  return 0;
3630  }
3631 
3632  /* primitive type match */
3633  if (p->type_enum != q->type_enum)
3634  {
3635  return 0;
3636  }
3637 
3638  if (p->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE && q->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE)
3639  {
3640  dt1 = (PT_NODE *) p;
3641  dt2 = (PT_NODE *) q;
3642  }
3643  else
3644  {
3645  dt1 = p->data_type;
3646  dt2 = q->data_type;
3647 
3648  if (dt1 && dt1->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE)
3649  {
3650  return 0;
3651  }
3652  if (dt2 && dt2->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE)
3653  {
3654  return 0;
3655  }
3656  }
3657 
3658  switch (p->type_enum)
3659  {
3660  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT: /* if type is object, check the names */
3661  if (dt1 == dt2)
3662  {
3663  return 1;
3664  }
3665 
3666  /* if both are "annonymous" object type, its ok */
3667  if (dt1 == NULL && dt2 == NULL)
3668  {
3669  return 1;
3670  }
3671 
3672  /* of only one is anonymous its not ok */
3673  if (dt1 == NULL || dt2 == NULL)
3674  {
3675  return 0;
3676  }
3677 
3678  if (dt1->info.data_type.entity == NULL && dt2->info.data_type.entity == NULL)
3679  {
3680  return 1;
3681  }
3682 
3683  /* Can't mix annonymous and non-annonymous (guards null pointers) */
3684  if (dt1->info.data_type.entity == NULL || dt2->info.data_type.entity == NULL)
3685  {
3686  return 0;
3687  }
3688 
3689  /* class objects must be the same */
3690  if (dt1->info.data_type.entity->info.name.db_object != dt2->info.data_type.entity->info.name.db_object)
3691  {
3692  return 0;
3693  }
3694  break;
3695 
3696  case PT_TYPE_SET:
3697  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
3698  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
3699  s = dt1;
3700  t = dt2;
3701 
3702  /* if sizes are different, sets can't match */
3703  if (pt_length_of_list (s) != pt_length_of_list (t))
3704  {
3705  return 0;
3706  }
3707 
3708  /* element types must match */
3709  while (s)
3710  {
3711  v = t;
3712  while (v)
3713  {
3714  if (pt_check_same_datatype (parser, s, v))
3715  {
3716  break; /* got match */
3717  }
3718  v = v->next;
3719  }
3720  if (!v)
3721  {
3722  return 0; /* s didn't match anything on t */
3723  }
3724  s = s->next;
3725  }
3726  break;
3727 
3728  default:
3729  if (dt1 && dt2)
3730  {
3731  if (dt1->info.data_type.precision != dt2->info.data_type.precision
3732  || dt1->info.data_type.dec_precision != dt2->info.data_type.dec_precision
3733  || dt1->info.data_type.units != dt2->info.data_type.units
3734  || dt1->info.data_type.collation_id != dt2->info.data_type.collation_id)
3735  {
3736  return 0;
3737  }
3738  }
3739  break;
3740  }
3741 
3742  return 1;
3743 }
3744 
3745 /*
3746  * pt_check_unique_exposed () - make sure the exposed names in the
3747  * range_var field are all distinct
3748  * return: 1 if exposed names are all unique, 0 if duplicate name
3749  * parser(in):
3750  * p(in): a PT_SPEC node (list)
3751 
3752  * Note :
3753  * Assumes that the exposed name (range_var) is a PT_NAME node but
3754  * doesn't check this. Else, crash and burn.
3755  */
3756 static int
3757 pt_check_unique_exposed (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * p)
3758 {
3759  PT_NODE *q;
3760 
3761  while (p)
3762  {
3763  q = p->next; /* q = next spec */
3764  while (q)
3765  { /* check that p->range != q->range to the end of list */
3766  if (!pt_str_compare (p->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original, q->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original,
3767  CASE_INSENSITIVE))
3768  {
3769  PT_MISC_TYPE p_type = p->info.spec.range_var->info.name.meta_class;
3770  PT_MISC_TYPE q_type = q->info.spec.range_var->info.name.meta_class;
3771 
3772  if (p_type != q_type && (p_type == PT_META_CLASS || q_type == PT_META_CLASS))
3773  {
3774  /* this happens in statements like: SELECT class t, t.attr FROM t which are rewriten to: SELECT class
3775  * t, t.attr FROM t, class t In this context, t is different from class t and we should not flag an
3776  * error */
3777  q = q->next; /* check the next one inner loop */
3778  continue;
3779  }
3780 
3781  PT_ERRORmf (parser, q, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_AMBIGUOUS_EXPOSED_NM,
3782  q->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original);
3783  return 0;
3784  }
3785 
3786  q = q->next; /* check the next one inner loop */
3787  }
3788 
3789  p = p->next; /* go to next one outer loop */
3790  }
3791 
3792  return 1; /* OK */
3793 }
3794 
3795 /*
3796  * pt_check_unique_names () - make sure the spec names are different.
3797  *
3798  * return: 1 if names are all unique, 0 if duplicate name
3799  * parser(in):
3800  * p(in): a PT_SPEC node (list)
3801 
3802  * Note :
3803  * If names in range_var are resolved, use pt_check_unique_exposed () instead.
3804  * This was specially created for DELETE statement which needs to verify
3805  * that specs have unique names before calling pt_class_pre_fetch ();
3806  * otherwise it crashes.
3807  */
3808 int
3809 pt_check_unique_names (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * p)
3810 {
3811  PT_NODE *q;
3812 
3813  while (p)
3814  {
3815  const char *p_name = NULL;
3816  if (p->node_type != PT_SPEC)
3817  {
3818  p = p->next;
3819  continue;
3820  }
3821  if (p->info.spec.range_var && PT_IS_NAME_NODE (p->info.spec.range_var))
3822  {
3823  p_name = p->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
3824  }
3825  else if (p->info.spec.entity_name && PT_IS_NAME_NODE (p->info.spec.entity_name))
3826  {
3827  p_name = p->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original;
3828  }
3829  else
3830  {
3831  p = p->next;
3832  continue;
3833  }
3834  q = p->next; /* q = next spec */
3835  while (q)
3836  { /* check that p->range != q->range to the end of list */
3837  const char *q_name = NULL;
3838  if (q->node_type != PT_SPEC)
3839  {
3840  q = q->next;
3841  continue;
3842  }
3843  if (q->info.spec.range_var && PT_IS_NAME_NODE (q->info.spec.range_var))
3844  {
3845  q_name = q->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
3846  }
3847  else if (q->info.spec.entity_name && PT_IS_NAME_NODE (q->info.spec.entity_name))
3848  {
3849  q_name = q->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original;
3850  }
3851  else
3852  {
3853  q = q->next;
3854  continue;
3855  }
3856  if (!pt_str_compare (p_name, q_name, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
3857  {
3858  PT_ERRORmf (parser, q, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_CLASS_OR_ALIAS, q_name);
3859  return 0;
3860  }
3861  q = q->next; /* check the next one inner loop */
3862  }
3863  p = p->next; /* go to next one outer loop */
3864  }
3865  return 1; /* OK */
3866 }
3867 
3868 /*
3869  * pt_common_attribute () - find the attributes that are identical
3870  * on both lists (i.e. the intersection)
3871  * return: returns a modified version of p
3872  * parser(in):
3873  * p(in/out): a list of PT_NAME nodes representing attributes
3874  * q(in): a list of PT_NAME nodes representing attributes
3875  *
3876  * Note :
3877  * This routine is called only from pt_resolve_star() above and should
3878  * not be used to take 'intersections' of general lists of names since
3879  * it modifies its argument.
3880  * WARNING: this routine must maintain the order of p.
3881  */
3882 static PT_NODE *
3883 pt_common_attribute (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * p, PT_NODE * q)
3884 {
3885  PT_NODE *temp, *result, *w;
3886 
3887  if (!p || !q)
3888  {
3889  return 0;
3890  }
3891  result = 0;
3892  while (p)
3893  {
3894  /* does the name match something on q? */
3895  w = pt_is_on_list (parser, p, q);
3896 
3897  /* if so, check that the data_types match */
3898  if (w && pt_check_same_datatype (parser, p, w))
3899  {
3900  /* OK, attach to result */
3901  temp = p->next;
3902  p->next = NULL;
3903  result = parser_append_node (p, result);
3904  p = temp;
3905  continue;
3906  }
3907  p = p->next;
3908  }
3909 
3910  return result;
3911 }

3913 /*
3914  * pt_add_class_to_entity_list () -
3915  * return:
3916  * parser(in):
3917  * class(in):
3918  * entity(in):
3919  * parent(in):
3920  * id(in):
3921  * meta_class(in):
3922  */
3923 PT_NODE *
3924 pt_add_class_to_entity_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OBJECT * class_, PT_NODE * entity, const PT_NODE * parent,
3925  UINTPTR id, PT_MISC_TYPE meta_class)
3926 {
3927  PT_NODE *flat_list;
3928 
3929  flat_list = pt_make_subclass_list (parser, class_, parent->line_number, parent->column_number, id, meta_class, NULL);
3930  if (flat_list == NULL)
3931  {
3932  return NULL;
3933  }
3934 
3935  return pt_name_list_union (parser, entity, flat_list);
3936 }

3938 /*
3939  * pt_domain_to_data_type () - create and return a PT_DATA_TYPE node that
3940  * corresponds to a DB_DOMAIN dom
3941  * return: PT_NODE * to a data_type node
3942  * parser(in):
3943  * domain(in/out):
3944  *
3945  * Note : Won't work if type is OBJECT and class name is NULL
3946  */
3947 PT_NODE *
3948 pt_domain_to_data_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_DOMAIN * domain)
3949 {
3950  DB_DOMAIN *dom;
3951  DB_OBJECT *db;
3952  PT_NODE *result = NULL, *s, *result_last_node = NULL, *entity = NULL;
3953  PT_TYPE_ENUM t;
3954 
3955  t = pt_db_to_type_enum (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (domain));
3956  switch (t)
3957  {
3958  case PT_TYPE_JSON:
3959  result = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
3960  if (result == NULL)
3961  {
3962  return NULL;
3963  }
3964  result->type_enum = t;
3965  if (domain->json_validator != NULL)
3966  {
3967  result->info.data_type.json_schema =
3968  pt_append_bytes (parser, NULL, db_json_get_schema_raw_from_validator (domain->json_validator),
3969  (int) strlen (db_json_get_schema_raw_from_validator (domain->json_validator)));
3970  }
3971  else
3972  {
3973  result->info.data_type.json_schema = NULL;
3974  }
3975  break;
3976 
3977  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
3978  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
3979  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
3980  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
3981  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
3982  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
3983  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
3984  result = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
3985  if (result == NULL)
3986  {
3987  return NULL;
3988  }
3989  result->type_enum = t;
3990  /* some of these types won't have all of the three, but that's okay */
3991  result->info.data_type.precision = db_domain_precision (domain);
3992  result->info.data_type.dec_precision = db_domain_scale (domain);
3993  result->info.data_type.units = db_domain_codeset (domain);
3994  result->info.data_type.collation_id = db_domain_collation_id (domain);
3995  result->info.data_type.collation_flag = domain->collation_flag;
3996  assert (!PT_IS_CHAR_STRING_TYPE (t) || result->info.data_type.collation_id >= 0);
3997  break;
3998 
3999  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
4000  /* get the object */
4001  result = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
4002  if (result == NULL)
4003  {
4004  return NULL;
4005  }
4006  result->type_enum = t;
4007  result->info.data_type.entity = NULL;
4008  result->info.data_type.virt_type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
4009  while (domain)
4010  {
4011  db = db_domain_class (domain);
4012  if (db)
4013  {
4014  /* prim_type = PT_TYPE_OBJECT, attach db_object, attach name */
4015  entity =
4016  pt_add_class_to_entity_list (parser, db, result->info.data_type.entity, result, (UINTPTR) result,
4017  PT_CLASS);
4018  if (entity == NULL)
4019  {
4020  return NULL;
4021  }
4022  result->info.data_type.entity = entity;
4023  }
4024  domain = (DB_DOMAIN *) db_domain_next (domain);
4025  }
4026  break;
4027 
4028  case PT_TYPE_SET:
4029  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
4030  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
4031  case PT_TYPE_MIDXKEY:
4032  /* set of what? */
4033  dom = (DB_DOMAIN *) db_domain_set (domain);
4034  /* make list of types in set */
4035  while (dom)
4036  {
4037  s = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, dom); /* recursion here */
4038 
4039  if (s)
4040  {
4041  if (result)
4042  {
4043  /*
4044  * We want to make sure that the flat name list
4045  * hanging off of the first PT_DATA_TYPE node is the
4046  * union of all flat name lists from all nodes in
4047  * this list; this makes certain things much easier
4048  * later on.
4049  * PRESERVE THE ORDER OF THESE LISTS!
4050  */
4051  result->info.data_type.entity =
4052  pt_name_list_union (parser, result->info.data_type.entity, s->info.data_type.entity);
4053  s->info.data_type.entity = NULL;
4054  result_last_node->next = s;
4055  result_last_node = s;
4056  }
4057  else
4058  {
4059  result = result_last_node = s;
4060  }
4061  }
4062 
4063  dom = (DB_DOMAIN *) db_domain_next (dom);
4064  }
4065  result_last_node = NULL;
4066 
4067  /*
4068  * Now run back over the flattened name list and ensure that
4069  * they all have the same spec id.
4070  */
4071  if (result)
4072  for (s = result->info.data_type.entity; s; s = s->next)
4073  {
4074  s->info.name.spec_id = (UINTPTR) result;
4075  }
4076  break;
4077 
4078  case PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION:
4079  {
4080  DB_ENUM_ELEMENT *db_enum = NULL;
4081  int idx;
4082 
4083  result = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
4084  if (result == NULL)
4085  {
4086  return NULL;
4087  }
4088 
4089  result->type_enum = t;
4090  result->info.data_type.enumeration = NULL;
4091  for (idx = 1; idx <= DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEMS_COUNT (domain); idx++)
4092  {
4093  db_enum = &DOM_GET_ENUM_ELEM (domain, idx);
4094  s = pt_make_string_value (parser, DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_STRING (db_enum));
4095  DB_SET_ENUM_ELEM_CODESET (&(DB_GET_ENUMERATION (&(s->info.value.db_value))),
4096  DB_GET_ENUM_ELEM_CODESET (db_enum));
4097  if (s == NULL)
4098  {
4099  return NULL;
4100  }
4101  result->info.data_type.enumeration = parser_append_node (s, result->info.data_type.enumeration);
4102  }
4103 
4104  result->info.data_type.units = TP_DOMAIN_CODESET (domain);
4105  result->info.data_type.collation_id = TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION (domain);
4106  assert (result->info.data_type.collation_id >= 0);
4107  }
4108  break;
4109 
4110  default:
4111  result = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
4112  if (result == NULL)
4113  {
4114  return NULL;
4115  }
4116  result->type_enum = t;
4117  break;
4118  }
4119 
4120  return result;
4121 }

4123 /*
4124  * pt_flat_spec_pre () - resolve the entity spec into a flat name list
4125  * and attach it
4126  * return:
4127  * parser(in):
4128  * node(in/out):
4129  * chk_parent(in):
4130  * continue_walk(in/out):
4131  */
4132 PT_NODE *
4133 pt_flat_spec_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
4134 {
4135  PT_NODE *q;
4136  PT_NODE *result = node;
4137  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO *info = (PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO *) arg;
4138 
4139  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
4140 
4141  if (!node)
4142  {
4143  return 0;
4144  }
4145 
4146  /* if node type is entity_spec(list) process the list */
4147 
4148  switch (node->node_type)
4149  {
4150  case PT_INSERT:
4151  case PT_SELECT:
4152  case PT_UPDATE:
4153  case PT_DELETE:
4154  case PT_GRANT:
4155  case PT_REVOKE:
4156  case PT_MERGE:
4157  info->spec_parent = node;
4158  break;
4159  default:
4160  break;
4161  }
4162 
4163  if (node->node_type == PT_SPEC)
4164  {
4165  /* don't let parser_walk_tree go to rest of list. List is handled here */
4166  *continue_walk = PT_LEAF_WALK;
4167  while (node)
4168  {
4169  /* if a flat list has not been calculated, calculate it. */
4170  if (!node->info.spec.flat_entity_list && PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (node))
4171  {
4172  /* this sets the persistent entity_spec id. the address of the node may be changed through copying, but
4173  * this id won't. The number used is the address, just as an easy way to generate a unique number. */
4174  node->info.spec.id = (UINTPTR) node;
4175 
4176  q = pt_make_flat_name_list (parser, node, info->spec_parent, info->for_update);
4177 
4178  node->info.spec.flat_entity_list = q;
4179  }
4180 
4181  if (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (node))
4182  {
4183  /* entity_spec list are not allowed to have derived column names (for now) */
4184  if (node->info.spec.as_attr_list)
4185  {
4186  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_NO_DERIVED_COLS,
4187  pt_short_print_l (parser, node->info.spec.as_attr_list));
4188  }
4189  }
4190  else if (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (node))
4191  {
4192  PT_NODE *derived_table = node->info.spec.derived_table;
4193  if (!node->info.spec.id)
4194  {
4195  node->info.spec.id = (UINTPTR) node;
4196  }
4197 
4198  parser_walk_tree (parser, derived_table, pt_flat_spec_pre, info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
4199  }
4200  else
4201  {
4202  PT_NODE *cte_def = NULL, *non_recursive_cte = NULL;
4203 
4204  assert (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (node));
4205  cte_def = node->info.spec.cte_pointer->info.pointer.node;
4206  if (cte_def)
4207  {
4208  non_recursive_cte = cte_def->info.cte.non_recursive_part;
4209  }
4210 
4211  if (non_recursive_cte)
4212  {
4213  if (!node->info.spec.id)
4214  {
4215  node->info.spec.id = (UINTPTR) node;
4216  }
4217 
4218  parser_walk_tree (parser, non_recursive_cte, pt_flat_spec_pre, info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
4219  }
4220  }
4221 
4222  node = node->next; /* next item on spec list */
4223  }
4224 
4225  /* and then do additional checks */
4226  if (result->node_type == PT_SPEC)
4227  {
4228  if (!pt_must_have_exposed_name (parser, result))
4229  {
4230  return 0;
4231  }
4232  if (!pt_check_unique_exposed (parser, result))
4233  {
4234  return 0;
4235  }
4236  }
4237  }
4238 
4239  return result;
4240 }
4241 
4242 /*
4243  * pt_get_all_attributes_and_types() -
4244  * return: cls' list of attributes if all OK, NULL otherwise.
4245  * parser(in): handle to parser context
4246  * cls(in): a PT_NAME node naming a class in the database
4247  * from(in): the entity_spec from which cls was derived
4248  * as a flat_entity_list item
4249  */
4250 static PT_NODE *
4251 pt_get_all_attributes_and_types (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * cls, PT_NODE * from)
4252 {
4253  PT_NODE *result = NULL, *tail, *node;
4254  DB_ATTRIBUTE *att;
4255  DB_OBJECT *object;
4256  bool class_atts_only;
4257 
4258  if (cls == NULL || cls->node_type != PT_NAME || (object = cls->info.name.db_object) == NULL || from == NULL
4259  || from->node_type != PT_SPEC)
4260  {
4261  return NULL;
4262  }
4263 
4264  class_atts_only = (from->info.spec.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS);
4265  att = NULL;
4266  if (class_atts_only)
4267  {
4268  att = (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) db_get_class_attributes (object);
4269  }
4270  else
4271  {
4272  att = (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) db_get_attributes_force (object);
4273  }
4274 
4275  if (att != NULL)
4276  {
4277  /* make result anchor the list */
4278  result = tail = pt_name (parser, db_attribute_name (att));
4279  if (result == NULL)
4280  {
4281  return NULL;
4282  }
4283  result->line_number = from->line_number;
4284  result->column_number = from->column_number;
4285 
4286  /* set its type */
4287  pt_get_attr_data_type (parser, att, result);
4288  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4289  {
4290  goto on_error;
4291  }
4292 
4293  result->info.name.spec_id = from->info.spec.id;
4294  if (class_atts_only)
4295  {
4296  result->info.name.meta_class = PT_META_ATTR;
4297  result->info.name.db_object = from->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object;
4298  }
4299 
4300  /* advance to next attribute */
4301  att = db_attribute_next (att);
4302 
4303  /* for the rest of the attributes do */
4304  while (att != NULL)
4305  {
4306  /* make new node & copy attribute name into it */
4307  node = pt_name (parser, db_attribute_name (att));
4308  if (node == NULL)
4309  {
4310  goto on_error;
4311  }
4312  node->line_number = from->line_number;
4313  node->column_number = from->column_number;
4314 
4315  /* set its type */
4316  pt_get_attr_data_type (parser, att, node);
4317  if (pt_has_error (parser))
4318  {
4319  goto on_error;
4320  }
4321 
4322  node->info.name.spec_id = from->info.spec.id;
4323  if (class_atts_only)
4324  {
4325  node->info.name.meta_class = PT_META_ATTR;
4326  node->info.name.db_object = from->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object;
4327  }
4328 
4329  /* append to list */
4330  tail->next = node;
4331  tail = node;
4332 
4333  /* advance to next attribute */
4334  att = db_attribute_next (att);
4335  }
4336  }
4337 
4338  return result;
4339 
4340 on_error:
4341  if (result != NULL)
4342  {
4343  parser_free_tree (parser, result);
4344  }
4345 
4346  return NULL;
4347 }
4348 
4349 /*
4350  * pt_get_all_showstmt_attributes_and_types () -
4351  * return: show list attributes list if all OK, NULL otherwise.
4352  * parser(in): handle to parser context
4353  * derived_table(in): the entity_spec from which cls was derived
4354  * as a flat_entity_list item
4355  */
4356 static PT_NODE *
4357 pt_get_all_showstmt_attributes_and_types (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * derived_table)
4358 {
4359  PT_NODE *result = NULL, *node;
4360  DB_ATTRIBUTE *att;
4361 
4362  if (derived_table == NULL || derived_table->node_type != PT_SHOWSTMT)
4363  {
4364  return NULL;
4365  }
4366 
4367  att = (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) showstmt_get_attributes (derived_table->info.showstmt.show_type);
4368  while (att != NULL)
4369  {
4370  /* make result anchor the list */
4371  node = pt_name (parser, db_attribute_name (att));
4372  if (node == NULL)
4373  {
4374  goto on_error;
4375  }
4376 
4377  /* set its type */
4378  pt_get_attr_data_type (parser, att, node);
4379 
4380  result = parser_append_node (node, result);
4381 
4382  /* advance to next attribute */
4383  att = db_attribute_next (att);
4384  }
4385 
4386  return result;
4387 
4388 on_error:
4389  if (result != NULL)
4390  {
4391  parser_free_tree (parser, result);
4392  }
4393  return NULL;
4394 }
4395 
4396 /*
4397  * pt_get_attr_data_type () - Given an attribute(att) whose name is in p,
4398  * find its data_type and attach the data-type to the name
4399  * return:
4400  * parser(in):
4401  * att(in): a db_attribute
4402  * attr(in/out): a PT_NAME node corresponding to att
4403  * db(in):
4404  */
4405 static void
4406 pt_get_attr_data_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_ATTRIBUTE * att, PT_NODE * attr)
4407 {
4408  DB_DOMAIN *dom;
4409  if (!attr || !att)
4410  {
4411  return;
4412  }
4413 
4414  dom = db_attribute_domain (att);
4415  attr->etc = dom; /* used for getting additional db-specific domain information in the Versant driver */
4416  attr->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (dom));
4417  switch (attr->type_enum)
4418  {
4419  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
4420  case PT_TYPE_SET:
4421  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
4422  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
4423  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
4424  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
4425  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
4426  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
4427  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
4428  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
4429  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
4430  case PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION:
4431  case PT_TYPE_JSON:
4432  attr->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, dom);
4433  break;
4434  default:
4435  break;
4436  }
4437 
4438  attr->info.name.meta_class = PT_NORMAL;
4439 
4440  /* set its shared attribute flag */
4441  if (db_attribute_is_shared (att))
4442  {
4443  attr->info.name.meta_class = PT_SHARED;
4444  }
4445 }
4446 
4447 
4448 /*
4449  * pt_unwhacked_spec () - Map to the real spec. Either identity,
4450  * or lookup of selector's path spec.
4451  * return:
4452  * parser(in):
4453  * scope(in):
4454  * spec(in):
4455  */
4456 static PT_NODE *
4457 pt_unwhacked_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * scope, PT_NODE * spec)
4458 {
4459  if (spec && spec->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_WHACKED_SPEC)
4460  {
4461  spec = pt_find_path_entity (parser, scope, spec);
4462  if (spec)
4463  {
4464  spec->info.spec.meta_class = PT_PATH_INNER;
4465  }
4466  }
4467  return spec;
4468 }
4469 
4470 
4471 /*
4472  * pt_resolve_correlation () - Given an exposed spec, return the name node
4473  * of its oid.
4474  * return:
4475  * parser(in):
4476  * in_node(in):
4477  * scope(in):
4478  * exposed_spec(in):
4479  * col_name(in):
4480  * p_entity(in):
4481  *
4482  * Note:
4483  * Also check for some semantic errors
4484  * - disallow OIDs of derived spec
4485  * - disallow selectors except inside path expression
4486  */
4487 static PT_NODE *
4488 pt_resolve_correlation (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * in_node, PT_NODE * scope, PT_NODE * exposed_spec,
4489  int col_name, PT_NODE ** p_entity)
4490 {
4491  PT_NODE *corr_name = NULL;
4492 
4493  exposed_spec = pt_unwhacked_spec (parser, scope, exposed_spec);
4494 
4495  /* If so, name resolves to scope's flat list of entities */
4496  if (exposed_spec)
4497  {
4498  /* the exposed name of a derived table or a CTE may not be used alone, ie, "select e from (select a from c) e"
4499  * is disallowed. */
4500  if (col_name && (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (exposed_spec) || PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (exposed_spec))
4501  && exposed_spec->info.spec.range_var != in_node)
4502  {
4503  if (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (in_node, PT_NAME_FOR_UPDATE))
4504  {
4505  in_node->info.name.spec_id = exposed_spec->info.spec.id;
4506  return in_node;
4507  }
4508  else
4509  {
4510  PT_ERRORmf (parser, in_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_NO_REF_TO_DRVTB,
4511  pt_short_print (parser, in_node));
4512  return NULL;
4513  }
4514  }
4515 
4516  /* check for a selector variable in a perverse place */
4517  if ((in_node->node_type == PT_NAME && in_node->info.name.path_correlation)
4518  || (in_node->node_type == PT_DOT_
4519  && ((in_node->info.dot.arg1->node_type == PT_NAME && in_node->info.dot.arg2->info.name.path_correlation)
4520  || (in_node->info.dot.arg1->node_type == PT_NAME
4521  && in_node->info.dot.arg1->info.name.path_correlation))))
4522  {
4523  PT_ERRORmf (parser, in_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PATH_CORR_OUTSIDE,
4524  pt_short_print (parser, in_node));
4525  return NULL;
4526  }
4527 
4528  if (!exposed_spec->info.spec.range_var)
4529  {
4530  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
4531  return NULL;
4532  }
4533 
4534  corr_name = pt_name (parser, "");
4535  PT_NODE_COPY_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (corr_name, in_node);
4536  in_node->next = NULL;
4537  in_node->or_next = NULL;
4538  if (in_node->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS)
4539  {
4540  corr_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_META_CLASS;
4541  }
4542  else
4543  {
4544  corr_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_OID_ATTR;
4545  if (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (in_node, PT_NAME_INFO_GENERATED_OID))
4546  {
4547  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (corr_name, PT_NAME_INFO_GENERATED_OID);
4548  }
4549  }
4550  if (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (in_node, PT_NAME_ALLOW_REUSABLE_OID))
4551  {
4552  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (corr_name, PT_NAME_ALLOW_REUSABLE_OID);
4553  }
4554  if (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (in_node, PT_NAME_FOR_UPDATE))
4555  {
4556  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (corr_name, PT_NAME_FOR_UPDATE);
4557  }
4558 
4559  parser_free_tree (parser, in_node);
4560 
4561  corr_name->info.name.spec_id = exposed_spec->info.spec.id;
4562  corr_name->info.name.resolved = exposed_spec->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
4563  if (PT_IS_SPEC_REAL_TABLE (exposed_spec))
4564  {
4565  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (corr_name, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
4566  }
4567 
4568  /* attach the data type */
4569  corr_name->type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
4570  if (exposed_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list)
4571  {
4572  corr_name->data_type = pt_object_to_data_type (parser, exposed_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list);
4573  }
4574 
4575  *p_entity = exposed_spec;
4576  }
4577 
4578  return corr_name;
4579 }
4580 
4581 /*
4582  * pt_spec_in_domain() - determine if cls is in the domain specified by lst
4583  * return: true if cls is in the domain specified by lst
4584  * cls(in): a PT_SPEC node representing a class
4585  * lst(in): a list of PT_NAME nodes representing a data_type domain
4586  *
4587  * Note :
4588  * This function is used to check for well-formed selector variables. For
4589  * example, given the query
4590  * select room[x].size_in_sq_ft
4591  * from hotel, (all quarters (except cabin)) x, table(rooms) as t(room)
4592  * the selector variable 'x' is well-formed if the exposed spec 'x'
4593  * intersects the domain of attribute 'room'.
4594  */
4595 
4596 static int
4597 pt_spec_in_domain (PT_NODE * cls, PT_NODE * lst)
4598 {
4599  PT_NODE *c;
4600 
4601  if (!cls || cls->node_type != PT_SPEC || !lst)
4602  {
4603  return 0; /* preconditions not met, so nothing doing. */
4604  }
4605 
4606  while (lst && lst->node_type == PT_NAME)
4607  {
4608  /* BEWARE! Do not use and assume that cls->info.spec.entity_name is a PT_NAME node because the code in sq.g
4609  * class_specification() and elsewhere uses cls->info.spec.entity_name to hold a list of PT_SPEC nodes. Instead,
4610  * use cls->info.spec.flat_entity_list as the parse tree representation of class_specs of the form 'select ...
4611  * from (c1 c2 ...) x' */
4612  c = cls->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
4613 
4614  /* cls is of the form '(c1 c2 ...) x' and we need to determine if any class in the hierarchy of (c1 c2 ...) is a
4615  * subclass of any class in lst. */
4616  while (c && c->node_type == PT_NAME && c->info.name.db_object)
4617  {
4618  if (c->info.name.db_object == lst->info.name.db_object)
4619  {
4620  return 1; /* cls is a subclass of a class in lst */
4621  }
4622  else
4623  {
4624  c = c->next; /* try the next c */
4625  }
4626  }
4627  lst = lst->next; /* try the next class in lst */
4628  }
4629  return 0; /* cls is not a subclass of any class in lst */
4630 }
4631 
4632 /*
4633  * pt_get_resolution() - try to resolve a name or path expr using this scope
4634  * return: if in_node is an X.Z with X an exposed name,
4635  * collapse it into Z, return Z
4636  * if in_node is an X that resolves to scope, return X
4637  * if in_node has no resolution in this scope, return NULL
4638  * parser(in): the parser context
4639  * bind_arg(in): a list of scopes for resolving method calls
4640  * scope(in): a list of PT_SPEC nodes (ie, a 'from' clause)
4641  * in_node(in/out): an attribute reference or path expression to be resolved
4642  * p_entity(out): entity_spec of X if in_node is an X.Z
4643  * col_name(in): true on top level call.
4644  */
4645 static PT_NODE *
4646 pt_get_resolution (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg, PT_NODE * scope, PT_NODE * in_node,
4647  PT_NODE ** p_entity, int col_name)
4648 {
4649  PT_NODE *exposed_spec, *spec, *savespec, *arg1, *arg2, *arg1_name;
4650  PT_NODE *unique_entity, *path_correlation;
4651  PT_NODE *temp;
4652  PT_NODE *reserved_name = NULL;
4653  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO info;
4654 
4655  if (!in_node)
4656  {
4657  return NULL;
4658  }
4659 
4660  if (PT_SHOULD_BIND_RESERVED_NAME (scope))
4661  {
4662  /* Attempt to bind to reserved name */
4663  /* If scope should bind for record information, binding to table attribute is also allowed, so shouldn't stop if
4664  * binding to reserved names fails. */
4665  reserved_name = pt_bind_reserved_name (parser, in_node, scope);
4666  if (!PT_IS_SPEC_FLAG_SET (scope, PT_SPEC_FLAG_RECORD_INFO_SCAN) || reserved_name != NULL)
4667  {
4668  return reserved_name;
4669  }
4670  /* Couldn't bind to record info, attempt to bind to table attributes */
4671  /* Fall through */
4672  }
4673 
4674  if (in_node->node_type == PT_NAME)
4675  {
4676  /* Has this name been resolved? */
4677  if (in_node->info.name.spec_id)
4678  {
4679  *p_entity = NULL;
4680  if (in_node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT && in_node->data_type)
4681  {
4682  temp = scope;
4683  while (temp && temp->info.spec.id != in_node->info.name.spec_id)
4684  {
4685  temp = temp->next;
4686  }
4687  if (temp)
4688  {
4689  *p_entity = temp;
4690  return in_node;
4691  }
4692  }
4693  return NULL;
4694  }
4695 
4696  /* Let's see if it is a parameter, possibly anchoring a path expr */
4697  if (in_node->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)
4698  {
4699  *p_entity = NULL;
4700  return pt_bind_parameter (parser, in_node);
4701  }
4702 
4703  if (col_name)
4704  {
4705  if (in_node->info.name.path_correlation)
4706  {
4707  PT_ERRORmf (parser, in_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PATH_CORR_OUTSIDE,
4708  pt_short_print (parser, in_node));
4709  return NULL;
4710  }
4711  }
4712  else
4713  {
4714  /* We are on the left of a dot node. (because we are recursing) Here, correlation names have precedence over
4715  * column names. (for ANSI compatibility). For unqualified names, column names have precedence. For qualifier
4716  * names, correlation names have precedence. */
4717  exposed_spec = pt_is_correlation_name (parser, scope, in_node);
4718  if (exposed_spec)
4719  {
4720  return pt_resolve_correlation (parser, in_node, scope, exposed_spec, col_name, p_entity);
4721  }
4722  }
4723 
4724  /* Else, is this an attribute of a unique entity within scope? */
4725  for (savespec = NULL, spec = scope; spec; spec = spec->next)
4726  {
4727  if (pt_find_name_in_spec (parser, spec, in_node))
4728  {
4729  if (savespec)
4730  {
4731  PT_ERRORmf (parser, in_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_AMBIGUOUS_REF_TO,
4732  in_node->info.name.original);
4733  return NULL;
4734  }
4735  savespec = spec;
4736  }
4737  }
4738 
4739  if (savespec)
4740  {
4741  /* if yes, set the resolution and the resolved name */
4742  in_node->info.name.resolved = savespec->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
4743  in_node->info.name.partition = savespec->info.spec.range_var->info.name.partition;
4744 
4745  if (PT_IS_SPEC_REAL_TABLE (savespec))
4746  {
4747  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (in_node, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
4748  }
4749 
4750  savespec = pt_unwhacked_spec (parser, scope, savespec);
4751 
4752  *p_entity = savespec;
4753  return in_node;
4754  }
4755 
4756  if (col_name)
4757  {
4758  /* Failing finding a column name for a name NOT on the left of a dot, try and resolve it as a correlation
4759  * name (oid). For unqualified names, column names have precedence. For qualifier names, correlation names
4760  * have precedence. */
4761  exposed_spec = pt_is_correlation_name (parser, scope, in_node);
4762  if (exposed_spec)
4763  {
4764  return pt_resolve_correlation (parser, in_node, scope, exposed_spec, col_name, p_entity);
4765  }
4766  }
4767 
4768  if (in_node->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS)
4769  {
4770  DB_OBJECT *object;
4771  object = pt_find_users_class (parser, in_node);
4772  if (object == NULL)
4773  {
4774  return NULL; /* not an valid class */
4775  }
4776  in_node->info.name.db_object = object;
4777  if (bind_arg->spec_frames)
4778  {
4779  PT_NODE *class_spec, *node, *entity, *found = NULL;
4780  for (node = bind_arg->spec_frames->extra_specs; node != NULL; node = node->next)
4781  {
4782  if (node->node_type == PT_SPEC && (entity = node->info.spec.entity_name)
4783  && (entity->info.name.db_object == in_node->info.name.db_object))
4784  {
4785  found = node;
4786  break;
4787  }
4788  }
4789 
4790  if (found)
4791  {
4792  class_spec = found;
4793  }
4794  else
4795  {
4796  /* add the new spec to the extra scope */
4797  if ((class_spec = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SPEC)) == NULL)
4798  {
4799  return NULL;
4800  }
4801  class_spec->info.spec.id = (UINTPTR) class_spec;
4802  class_spec->info.spec.only_all = PT_ONLY;
4803  class_spec->info.spec.meta_class = PT_META_CLASS;
4804  if ((class_spec->info.spec.entity_name = pt_name (parser, in_node->info.name.original)) == NULL)
4805  {
4806  return NULL;
4807  }
4808  info.spec_parent = NULL;
4809  info.for_update = false;
4810  class_spec = parser_walk_tree (parser, class_spec, pt_flat_spec_pre, &info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
4811  bind_arg->spec_frames->extra_specs =
4812  parser_append_node (class_spec, bind_arg->spec_frames->extra_specs);
4813  }
4814 
4815  in_node->info.name.meta_class = PT_META_CLASS;
4816  in_node->info.name.spec_id = class_spec->info.spec.id;
4817  in_node->info.name.resolved = class_spec->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
4818  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (in_node, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
4819  /* attach the data type */
4820  in_node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
4821  if (class_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list)
4822  {
4823  in_node->data_type = pt_object_to_data_type (parser, class_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list);
4824  }
4825  *p_entity = class_spec;
4826  return in_node;
4827  }
4828  else
4829  {
4830  /* This is an object reference outside of a query */
4831  if (!in_node->info.name.resolved)
4832  {
4833  in_node->info.name.resolved = "";
4834  }
4835  in_node->info.name.spec_id = (UINTPTR) in_node->info.name.db_object;
4836  in_node->info.name.meta_class = PT_META_CLASS;
4837  in_node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
4838  in_node->data_type = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
4839 
4840  if (in_node->data_type == NULL)
4841  {
4842  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
4843  return NULL;
4844  }
4845 
4846  in_node->data_type->type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
4847  in_node->data_type->info.data_type.entity = parser_copy_tree (parser, in_node);
4848  in_node->data_type->info.data_type.virt_type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
4849  *p_entity = NULL; /* got no entity! */
4850  return in_node;
4851  }
4852  }
4853 
4854  /* no resolution in this scope */
4855  return NULL;
4856  }
4857 
4858  /* Is it a DOT expression X.Z? */
4859  if (in_node->node_type == PT_DOT_)
4860  {
4861  arg1 = in_node->info.dot.arg1;
4862  arg2 = in_node->info.dot.arg2;
4863  /* if bad arg2, OR if already resolved, then return same node */
4864  if (!arg2 || arg2->info.name.spec_id || arg2->node_type != PT_NAME)
4865  {
4866  *p_entity = NULL;
4867  return in_node;
4868  }
4869 
4870  if (col_name)
4871  {
4872  if (arg2->info.name.path_correlation)
4873  {
4874  PT_ERRORmf (parser, arg2, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PATH_CORR_OUTSIDE,
4875  pt_short_print (parser, in_node));
4876  return NULL;
4877  }
4878  }
4879 
4880  /* Check if this is an exposed name in the current scope. */
4881  exposed_spec = pt_is_correlation_name (parser, scope, in_node);
4882  if (exposed_spec)
4883  {
4884  return pt_resolve_correlation (parser, in_node, scope, exposed_spec, col_name, p_entity);
4885  }
4886 
4887  /* if arg1 not in scope, return NULL to indicate not in scope. */
4888  if (!(arg1 = pt_get_resolution (parser, bind_arg, scope, arg1, p_entity, 0)))
4889  {
4890  *p_entity = NULL;
4891  return NULL;
4892  }
4893 
4894  if (arg1->node_type == PT_NAME)
4895  {
4896  arg1_name = arg1;
4897  }
4898  else if (arg1->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL)
4899  {
4900  arg1_name = arg1->info.method_call.method_name;
4901  }
4902  else
4903  {
4904  arg1_name = arg1->info.dot.arg2;
4905  }
4906  /* given X.Z, resolve (X) */
4907  in_node->info.dot.arg1 = arg1;
4908  /* Note : this should not get run, now that parameters are evaluated at run time, instead of converted to values
4909  * at compile time. We need to be careful here. We may have a path expression anchored by a parameter (PT_VALUE
4910  * node) or a class attribute object. If so, we evaluate the path expression here and return the appropriate
4911  * PT_VALUE node. */
4912  if (arg1->node_type == PT_VALUE && arg1->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
4913  {
4914  temp = pt_eval_value_path (parser, in_node);
4915  if (!temp)
4916  {
4917  return NULL;
4918  }
4919  temp->next = in_node->next;
4920  in_node->next = NULL;
4921  parser_free_tree (parser, temp);
4922  }
4923 
4924  if (arg1_name->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)
4925  {
4926  /* if Parameter was undefined, we would already have raised an error in recursion on arg1 */
4927  return pt_bind_parameter_path (parser, in_node);
4928  }
4929 
4930  /* If arg1 is an exposed name, replace expr with resolved arg2 */
4931  if (arg1->node_type == PT_NAME && (arg1->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR))
4932  {
4933  /* Arg1 was an exposed name */
4934  if (pt_find_name_in_spec (parser, *p_entity, arg2))
4935  {
4936  /* only mark it resolved if it was found! transfer the info from arg1 to arg2 */
4937  arg2->info.name.resolved = arg1->info.name.resolved;
4938  if (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (arg1, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE))
4939  {
4940  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (arg2, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
4941  }
4942  /* don't loose list */
4943  arg2->next = in_node->next;
4944  /* save alias */
4945  arg2->alias_print = in_node->alias_print;
4946  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (arg2, PT_NAME_INFO_DOT_NAME);
4947  /* replace expr with resolved arg2 */
4948  in_node->info.dot.arg2 = NULL;
4949  in_node->next = NULL;
4950  parser_free_tree (parser, in_node);
4951  in_node = arg2;
4952  }
4953  else
4954  {
4955  temp = arg1->data_type;
4956  if (temp)
4957  {
4958  temp = temp->info.data_type.entity;
4959  }
4960  if (!temp)
4961  {
4962  /* resolution error */
4963  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_HAS_NO_ATTR,
4964  pt_short_print (parser, arg1), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
4965  }
4966  else if (temp->next)
4967  {
4968  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASSES_HAVE_NO_ATTR,
4969  pt_short_print_l (parser, temp), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
4970  }
4971  else
4972  {
4973  temp->info.name.resolved = NULL;
4974  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_HAVE,
4975  pt_short_print_l (parser, temp), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
4976  }
4977  /* signal as not resolved */
4978  return NULL;
4979  }
4980  }
4981  else if (arg1_name->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS)
4982  {
4983  if (arg1->data_type == NULL)
4984  {
4985  return NULL;
4986  }
4987 
4988  /* Arg1 was a meta class name */
4989  if (pt_find_class_attribute (parser, arg1->data_type->info.data_type.entity, arg2))
4990  {
4991  /* only mark it resolved if it was found! */
4992 
4993  /* A meta class attribute, transfer the class info from arg1 to arg2 */
4994  arg2->info.name.resolved = arg1->info.name.resolved;
4995  if (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (arg1, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE))
4996  {
4997  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (arg2, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
4998  }
4999  /* don't lose list */
5000  arg2->next = in_node->next;
5001  /* save alias */
5002  arg2->alias_print = in_node->alias_print;
5003  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (arg2, PT_NAME_INFO_DOT_NAME);
5004  /* replace expr with resolved arg2 */
5005  in_node->info.dot.arg2 = NULL;
5006  in_node->next = NULL;
5007  parser_free_tree (parser, in_node);
5008  in_node = arg2;
5009  }
5010  else
5011  {
5012  temp = arg1->data_type;
5013  if (temp)
5014  {
5015  temp = temp->info.data_type.entity;
5016  }
5017  if (!temp)
5018  {
5019  /* resolution error */
5020  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_HAS_NO_ATTR,
5021  pt_short_print (parser, arg1), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
5022  }
5023  else
5024  {
5025  temp->info.name.resolved = NULL;
5026  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_HAVE,
5027  pt_short_print_l (parser, temp), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
5028  }
5029  /* signal as not resolved */
5030  return NULL;
5031  }
5032  }
5033  else
5034  {
5035  /* This is NOT an exposed name, it must be an object attribute. It must also be a legitimate root for this
5036  * path expression. */
5037  if (arg1->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
5038  {
5039  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_OBJECT_TYPE,
5040  pt_short_print (parser, arg1), pt_show_type_enum (arg1->type_enum));
5041  return NULL;
5042  }
5043  else if (!arg1->data_type)
5044  {
5045  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Resolution");
5046  return NULL;
5047  }
5048  else if (arg1_name->info.name.path_correlation)
5049  {
5050  path_correlation = arg1_name->info.name.path_correlation;
5051  /* there must be an exposed class spec in this scope */
5052  exposed_spec = pt_is_correlation_name (parser, scope, path_correlation);
5053  if (!exposed_spec)
5054  {
5055  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, path_correlation, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5056  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SELECTOR_UNRESOLVED, path_correlation->info.name.original,
5057  pt_short_print (parser, scope));
5058  return NULL;
5059  }
5060  else if (exposed_spec->info.spec.derived_table)
5061  {
5062  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, path_correlation, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5063  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SELECTOR_TO_NON_CLS, path_correlation->info.name.original,
5064  pt_short_print (parser, exposed_spec));
5065  return NULL;
5066  }
5067  else
5068  {
5069  PT_NODE *test = arg1;
5070  PT_NODE *root_spec;
5071  PT_NODE *arg1dt;
5072  while (test->node_type == PT_DOT_)
5073  {
5074  test = test->info.dot.arg1;
5075  }
5076  if (exposed_spec->info.spec.id == test->info.name.spec_id)
5077  {
5078  PT_ERRORmf (parser, path_correlation, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5079  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SELECTOR_DEFINE_SELF, path_correlation->info.name.original);
5080  return NULL;
5081  }
5082 
5083  /* test for circularly defined selectors */
5084  root_spec = scope;
5085  while (root_spec && (root_spec->info.spec.id != test->info.name.spec_id))
5086  {
5087  root_spec = root_spec->next;
5088  }
5089  if (root_spec)
5090  {
5091  temp = pt_find_entity (parser, exposed_spec->info.spec.path_entities, root_spec->info.spec.id);
5092  if (temp)
5093  {
5094  /* the selectors circularly define each other because this [sel] is the root of the
5095  * definition of the root of this selector. eg select x.a[y].b, y.a[x].b from x,y */
5096  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, path_correlation, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5097  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CYCLIC_SELECTOR, path_correlation->info.name.original,
5098  test->info.name.resolved);
5099  return NULL;
5100  }
5101 
5102  if (exposed_spec->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_WHACKED_SPEC)
5103  {
5104  /* make sure the exposed spec is already on the root spec path entities. Otherwise we are
5105  * redefining it. */
5106  temp = pt_unwhacked_spec (parser, scope, exposed_spec);
5107  if (temp)
5108  {
5109  temp = temp->info.spec.path_conjuncts;
5110  if (temp)
5111  {
5112  temp = temp->info.expr.arg1;
5113  }
5114  if (temp && !pt_name_equal (parser, temp, arg1_name))
5115  {
5116  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, path_correlation, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5117  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SELECTOR_REDEFINED, path_correlation->info.name.original,
5118  pt_short_print (parser, arg1));
5119  }
5120  }
5121  }
5122  }
5123  /* make sure the selector variable refers to an entity spec that is a subclass of the arg1->data_type
5124  * class. */
5125  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && arg1->data_type && arg1->data_type->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE
5126  && (arg1dt = arg1->data_type->info.data_type.entity) && arg1dt->node_type == PT_NAME
5127  && !pt_spec_in_domain (exposed_spec, arg1dt))
5128  {
5129  PT_ERRORmf3 (parser, path_correlation, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5130  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SELECTOR_NOT_SUBCLASS, path_correlation->info.name.original,
5131  pt_short_print_l (parser, exposed_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list),
5132  pt_short_print_l (parser, arg1dt));
5133  return NULL;
5134  }
5135  }
5136 
5137  /* no cross product */
5138  exposed_spec->info.spec.derived_table_type = PT_IS_WHACKED_SPEC;
5139  parser_free_tree (parser, arg1->data_type->info.data_type.entity);
5140  arg1->data_type->info.data_type.entity =
5141  parser_copy_tree_list (parser, exposed_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list);
5142  path_correlation->info.name.resolved = path_correlation->info.name.original;
5143  path_correlation->info.name.original = "";
5144  path_correlation->info.name.spec_id = exposed_spec->info.spec.id;
5145  path_correlation->info.name.meta_class = PT_OID_ATTR;
5146  path_correlation->type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
5147  }
5148  else
5149  {
5150  exposed_spec = NULL;
5151  }
5152  if (!pt_find_attr_in_class_list (parser, arg1->data_type->info.data_type.entity, arg2))
5153  {
5154  temp = arg1->data_type;
5155  if (temp)
5156  {
5157  temp = temp->info.data_type.entity;
5158  }
5159  if (!temp)
5160  {
5161  /* resolution error */
5162  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DOM_OBJ_HASNO_ATT_X,
5163  pt_short_print (parser, arg1), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
5164  }
5165  else if (temp->next)
5166  {
5167  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASSES_HAVE_NO_ATTR,
5168  pt_short_print_l (parser, temp), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
5169  }
5170  else
5171  {
5172  temp->info.name.resolved = NULL;
5173  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_HAVE,
5174  pt_short_print_l (parser, temp), pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
5175  }
5176  *p_entity = NULL;
5177  return NULL; /* not bound */
5178  }
5179 
5180  /* we have a good path expression, find entity for arg2 in the path_entities of valid_entity, it may need to
5181  * be created */
5182 
5183  /* set the type of the dot node to the type of arg2 */
5184  in_node->type_enum = arg2->type_enum;
5185  if (arg2->data_type)
5186  {
5187  if (in_node->data_type)
5188  {
5189  parser_free_tree (parser, in_node->data_type);
5190  }
5191  in_node->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, arg2->data_type);
5192  }
5193 
5194  /* A normal path must be rooted in an entity spec However, we can have p_entity be NULL for some odd cases.
5195  * Eg insert into x values(meth(:p1).y) Don't get wigged out here, and it gets handled later. */
5196  if (*p_entity)
5197  {
5198  unique_entity = pt_insert_entity (parser, in_node, *p_entity, exposed_spec);
5199  *p_entity = unique_entity;
5200  }
5201  }
5202  return in_node;
5203  } /* end if-a-dot-expression */
5204 
5205  /* Is it a method call? Be careful, method calls that haven't been resolved masquerade as functions until we call
5206  * pt_bind_names() on the function node. */
5207  if ((in_node->node_type == PT_FUNCTION) || (in_node->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL))
5208  {
5209  PT_NODE *new_node;
5210  if (in_node->node_type == PT_FUNCTION)
5211  {
5212  /* call pt_bind_names() to convert the function node into a method node as well as binding its arguments and
5213  * its target. */
5214  new_node = parser_walk_tree (parser, in_node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
5215  if (new_node->node_type != PT_METHOD_CALL)
5216  {
5217  return NULL;
5218  }
5219  else
5220  {
5221  /* remove wrong code this cause free memory(i.e., in_node) refer */
5222  in_node = new_node;
5223  }
5224  }
5225  /* Now, we have a PT_METHOD_CALL_NODE, and the target has been bound. */
5226  *p_entity = NULL;
5227  if (in_node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT && in_node->data_type)
5228  {
5229  temp = scope;
5230  while (temp && (temp->info.spec.id != in_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id))
5231  {
5232  temp = temp->next;
5233  }
5234  *p_entity = temp;
5235  return in_node;
5236  }
5237  return NULL;
5238  } /* end if PT_FUNCTION || PT_METHOD_CALL */
5239 
5240  /* Else got some node type we shouldn't have */
5241  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Resolution");
5242  return NULL;
5243 }
5244 
5245 /*
5246  * pt_expand_external_path() - expand an attr with a path expression
5247  * return: if in_node is an X.Z with Z a external type, return X.Z.tdata
5248  * parser(in): the parser context
5249  * in_node(in): an attribute reference or path expression to be resolved
5250  * p_entity(out): entity_spec of X if in_node is an X.Z
5251  */
5252 static PT_NODE *
5253 pt_expand_external_path (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * in_node, PT_NODE ** p_entity)
5254 {
5255 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
5256  PT_NODE *dot, *domain, *unique_entity;
5257 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
5258  PT_NODE *attr, *entity;
5259  DB_ATTRIBUTE *attr_obj;
5260 
5261  /* if in_node is a path expr, get last attr in the in_node */
5262  attr = ((PT_IS_DOT_NODE (in_node)) ? in_node->info.dot.arg2 : in_node);
5263  if (!PT_IS_NAME_NODE (attr))
5264  {
5265  return NULL;
5266  }
5267 
5268  if (attr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT && !PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (attr, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL))
5269  {
5270  entity = ((*p_entity) ? (*p_entity)->info.spec.entity_name : NULL);
5271  if (entity && entity->node_type == PT_NAME && entity->info.name.db_object)
5272  {
5273  attr_obj = (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) db_get_attribute_force (entity->info.name.db_object, attr->info.name.original);
5274 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
5275  /* check if the last attr is TEXT type */
5276  if (attr_obj && sm_has_text_domain (attr_obj, 0))
5277  {
5278  if ((domain = attr->data_type->info.data_type.entity) == NULL)
5279  {
5280  return NULL;
5281  }
5282  /* make a path expr like "attr.tdata" */
5283  if ((dot = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DOT_)) == NULL)
5284  {
5285  return NULL;
5286  }
5287  dot->info.dot.arg1 = attr;
5288  if ((dot->info.dot.arg2 = pt_name (parser, "tdata")) == NULL)
5289  {
5290  return NULL;
5291  }
5292  /* find "tdata" in the domain class, and attach the data type at "tdata" node */
5293  (void) pt_find_attr_in_class_list (parser, domain, dot->info.dot.arg2);
5294  dot->type_enum = dot->info.dot.arg2->type_enum;
5295  if ((dot->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, dot->info.dot.arg2->data_type)) == NULL)
5296  {
5297  return NULL;
5298  }
5299  /* insert the domain class into from class list */
5300  if (*p_entity)
5301  {
5302  unique_entity = pt_insert_entity (parser, dot, *p_entity, NULL);
5303  *p_entity = unique_entity;
5304  }
5305  /* merge in_node expr and "attr.tdata" */
5306  if (PT_IS_DOT_NODE (in_node))
5307  {
5308  dot->info.dot.arg1 = in_node->info.dot.arg1;
5309  }
5310  PT_NODE_COPY_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (dot, in_node);
5311  PT_NODE_INIT_OUTERLINK (in_node);
5312  dot->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, attr->info.name.original);
5313  if (!dot->alias_print)
5314  {
5315  return NULL;
5316  }
5317  return dot;
5318  }
5319 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
5320  }
5321  }
5322 
5323  return in_node;
5324 }
5325 
5326 /*
5327  * pt_is_correlation_name() - checks nam is an exposed name of some
5328  * entity_spec from scope
5329  * return: the entity spec of which nam is the correlation name.
5330  * Else 0 if not found or error.
5331  * parser(in/out): the parser context
5332  * scope(in): a list of PT_SPEC nodes
5333  * nam(in): a PT_NAME node
5334  */
5335 
5336 static PT_NODE *
5337 pt_is_correlation_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * scope, PT_NODE * nam)
5338 {
5339  PT_NODE *specs;
5340  PT_NODE *owner = NULL;
5341 
5342  assert (nam != NULL && (nam->node_type == PT_NAME || nam->node_type == PT_DOT_));
5343 
5344  if (nam->node_type == PT_DOT_)
5345  {
5346  owner = nam->info.dot.arg1;
5347  if (owner->node_type != PT_NAME)
5348  {
5349  /* could not be owner.correlation */
5350  return NULL;
5351  }
5352  nam = nam->info.dot.arg2;
5353  }
5354 
5355  if (nam->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)
5356  {
5357  return NULL;
5358  }
5359 
5360  for (specs = scope; specs; specs = specs->next)
5361  {
5362  if (specs->node_type != PT_SPEC)
5363  {
5364  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5365  return NULL;
5366  }
5367 
5368  if (specs->info.spec.range_var
5369  && ((nam->info.name.meta_class != PT_META_CLASS) || (specs->info.spec.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS))
5370  && pt_str_compare (nam->info.name.original, specs->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original,
5371  CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
5372  {
5373  if (!owner)
5374  {
5375  return specs;
5376  }
5377  else
5378  {
5379  PT_NODE *entity_name;
5380 
5381  entity_name = specs->info.spec.entity_name;
5382  if (entity_name && entity_name->node_type == PT_NAME && entity_name->info.name.resolved
5383  /* actual class ownership test is done for spec no need to repeat that here. */
5384  && (pt_str_compare (entity_name->info.name.resolved, owner->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) ==
5385  0))
5386  {
5387  return specs;
5388  }
5389  }
5390  }
5391  }
5392 
5393  return NULL;
5394 }
5395 
5396 /*
5397  * pt_find_entity () -
5398  * return: the entity spec of an entity of a spec in the scope with
5399  * an id matching the "match" spec
5400  * parser(in): the parser context
5401  * scope(in): a list of PT_SPEC nodes
5402  * id(in): of a PT_SPEC node
5403  */
5404 PT_NODE *
5405 pt_find_entity (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * scope, UINTPTR id)
5406 {
5407  PT_NODE *spec, *path_spec;
5408  for (spec = (PT_NODE *) scope; spec; spec = spec->next)
5409  {
5410  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
5411  {
5412  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5413  return NULL;
5414  }
5415  if (spec->info.spec.id == id)
5416  {
5417  return spec;
5418  }
5419  path_spec = pt_find_entity (parser, spec->info.spec.path_entities, id);
5420  if (path_spec)
5421  {
5422  return path_spec;
5423  }
5424  }
5425  return NULL;
5426 }
5427 
5428 /*
5429  * pt_find_path_entity () -
5430  * return: the entity spec of a path entity of a spec in the scope with
5431  * an id matching the whacked placeholder spec
5432  * parser(in): the parser context
5433  * scope(in): a list of PT_SPEC nodes
5434  * match(in): a PT_SPEC node that has been "whacked".
5435  */
5436 static PT_NODE *
5437 pt_find_path_entity (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * scope, PT_NODE * match)
5438 {
5439  PT_NODE *spec, *path_spec;
5440  UINTPTR id = match->info.spec.id;
5441 
5442  for (spec = scope; spec; spec = spec->next)
5443  {
5444  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
5445  {
5446  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5447  return NULL;
5448  }
5449 
5450  path_spec = pt_find_entity (parser, spec->info.spec.path_entities, id);
5451  if (path_spec)
5452  {
5453  return path_spec;
5454  }
5455  }
5456 
5457  return NULL;
5458 }
5459 
5460 /*
5461  * pt_is_on_list () - check whether name node p is equal to
