5462  * something on the list
5463  * return: Pointer to matching item or NULL
5464  * parser(in):
5465  * p(in): A PT_NAME node
5466  * list(in): A LIST of PT_NAME nodes
5467  *
5468  * Note :
5469  * two strings of length zero match
5470  * A NULL string does NOT match a zero length string
5471  */
5472 static PT_NODE *
5473 pt_is_on_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * p, const PT_NODE * list)
5474 {
5475  if (p == NULL)
5476  {
5477  return NULL;
5478  }
5479  if (p->node_type != PT_NAME)
5480  {
5481  return NULL;
5482  }
5483 
5484  while (list)
5485  {
5486  if (list->node_type != PT_NAME)
5487  {
5488  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5489  return NULL; /* this is an error */
5490  }
5491 
5492  if (pt_str_compare (p->info.name.original, list->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
5493  {
5494  return (PT_NODE *) list; /* found a match */
5495  }
5496  list = list->next;
5497  }
5498 
5499  return NULL; /* no match */
5500 }
5501 
5502 /*
5503  * pt_name_list_union () -
5504  * return:
5505  * parser(in):
5506  * list(in/out): A list of PT_NAME nodes
5507  * additions(in): A list of PT_NAME nodes
5508  *
5509  * Note :
5510  * PT_NAME lists ( list1 union list2 )
5511  * PRESERVING ORDER OF LIST!
5512  */
5513 static PT_NODE *
5514 pt_name_list_union (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * list, PT_NODE * additions)
5515 {
5516  PT_NODE *result, *temp;
5517 
5518  if (list == NULL)
5519  {
5520  return additions;
5521  }
5522  if (additions == NULL)
5523  {
5524  return list;
5525  }
5526 
5527  result = list;
5528  while (additions)
5529  {
5530  temp = additions;
5531  additions = additions->next;
5532  temp->next = NULL;
5533 
5534  if (!pt_is_on_list (parser, temp, list))
5535  {
5536  list = parser_append_node (temp, list);
5537  }
5538  else
5539  {
5540  parser_free_node (parser, temp);
5541  }
5542  }
5543 
5544  return result;
5545 }
5546 
5547 /*
5548  * pt_name_list_diff () -
5549  * return: Returns NULL if resulting list is empty
5550  * parser(in):
5551  * list(in): A list of PT_NAME nodes
5552  * deletions(in): A list of PT_NAME nodes
5553  *
5554  * Note :
5555  * PT_NAME lists (list1 - list2)
5556  * PRESERVING ORDER OF LIST!
5557  */
5558 static PT_NODE *
5559 pt_name_list_diff (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * list, PT_NODE * deletions)
5560 {
5561  PT_NODE *result = NULL;
5562  PT_NODE *temp;
5563 
5564  if (list == NULL)
5565  {
5566  return NULL;
5567  }
5568  if (deletions == NULL)
5569  {
5570  return list;
5571  }
5572 
5573  while (list)
5574  {
5575  temp = list;
5576  list = list->next;
5577  temp->next = NULL;
5578 
5579  if (!pt_is_on_list (parser, temp, deletions))
5580  {
5581  result = parser_append_node (temp, result);
5582  }
5583  else
5584  {
5585  parser_free_node (parser, temp);
5586  }
5587  }
5588 
5589  parser_free_tree (parser, deletions);
5590 
5591  return result;
5592 }
5593 
5594 /*
5595  * pt_make_flat_name_list () - create a list of its name and all of its
5596  * subclass names, recursively
5597  * return: Returns a pointer to (list of) PT_NAME node(s)
5598  * parser(in):
5599  * db(in): db_object to find subclasses for
5600  * line_num(in): input line_num (for error messages)
5601  * col_num(in): input column num (for error messages)
5602  * id(in):
5603  * meta_class(in): parent class for pt_name nodes we create
5604  * names_mht(in): memory hash table used to avoid duplicates
5605  */
5606 
5607 static PT_NODE *
5608 pt_make_subclass_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OBJECT * db, int line_num, int col_num, UINTPTR id,
5609  PT_MISC_TYPE meta_class, MHT_TABLE * names_mht)
5610 {
5611  PT_NODE *temp;
5612  const char *classname;
5613  PT_NODE *result = 0; /* will be returned */
5614  DB_OBJLIST *dbl; /* list of subclass objects */
5615  bool ismymht = false; /* Am I the one who created it? */
5616  SM_CLASS *smclass;
5617  int partition_skip;
5618 
5619 
5620  if (parser == NULL)
5621  {
5622  assert (parser != NULL);
5623  return NULL;
5624  }
5625 
5626  /* get the name of THIS class and put it in a PT_NAME node */
5627  if (db == NULL)
5628  {
5629  assert (db != NULL);
5630  return NULL;
5631  }
5632 
5633  classname = db_get_class_name (db);
5634  if (classname == NULL)
5635  {
5636  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5637  return NULL;
5638  } /* not a class name (error) */
5639 
5640  /* Check to see if this classname is already known, and only add a (name) node if we have never seen it before. Note:
5641  * Even if we have visited it, we still need to recursively check its subclasses (see dbl below) in order to maintain
5642  * the correct ordering of classnames found via our depth-first search. */
5643  if (names_mht == NULL || !mht_get (names_mht, classname))
5644  {
5645  result = pt_name (parser, classname);
5646  if (result == NULL)
5647  {
5648  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
5649  return NULL;
5650  }
5651  result->line_number = line_num;
5652  result->column_number = col_num;
5653  result->info.name.db_object = db;
5654  result->info.name.spec_id = id;
5655  result->info.name.meta_class = meta_class;
5656  result->info.name.partition = NULL;
5657 
5658  if ((au_fetch_class_force (db, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ) == NO_ERROR))
5659  {
5660  if (smclass->partition != NULL && smclass->partition->pname == NULL)
5661  {
5662  result->info.name.partition = smclass->partition;
5663  }
5664  }
5665  else
5666  {
5667  PT_ERRORc (parser, result, er_msg ());
5668  return NULL;
5669  }
5670 
5671  if (names_mht)
5672  {
5673  mht_put (names_mht, classname, (void *) true);
5674  }
5675  }
5676 
5677  /* get the list of immediate subclasses of db (may be NULL) */
5678  dbl = NULL;
5679  dbl = db_get_subclasses (db);
5680 
5681  /*
5682  * Build a hash table for all class and subclass names. This
5683  * helps us keep from building pt_name nodes for classes we
5684  * already know about. Also we only need to build the hash table if
5685  * there are in fact subclasses of the original class.
5686  */
5687  if (names_mht == NULL && dbl)
5688  {
5689  names_mht = mht_create ("Pt_Names_Hash_Table", PT_NAMES_HASH_SIZE, mht_4strhash, mht_compare_strings_are_equal);
5690  if (names_mht != NULL)
5691  {
5692  ismymht = true;
5693  /* Have to stick the first name node created above into the hash */
5694  mht_put (names_mht, classname, (void *) true);
5695  }
5696  else /* could not create hash table */
5697  {
5698  PT_ERRORc (parser, result, er_msg ());
5699  return NULL;
5700  }
5701  }
5702 
5703  /* for each subclass (dbl)...get the list(s) of its subclass names */
5704  while (dbl)
5705  {
5706  partition_skip = 0;
5707 
5708  if (au_fetch_class_force (dbl->op, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ) == NO_ERROR)
5709  {
5710  if (smclass->partition != NULL && smclass->partition->pname != NULL)
5711  {
5712  partition_skip = 1; /* partitioned sub class */
5713  }
5714  }
5715  else
5716  {
5717  PT_ERRORc (parser, result, er_msg ());
5718  result = NULL;
5719  goto end;
5720  }
5721 
5722  if (!partition_skip)
5723  {
5724  /* here is the recursion */
5725  temp = pt_make_subclass_list (parser, dbl->op, line_num, col_num, id, meta_class, names_mht);
5726  /* when names_mht != NULL, it is possible that temp is NULL while no error happen. Such as: diamond problem
5727  * of multiple inheritance. So, check pt_has_error() is needed. */
5728  if (temp == NULL && pt_has_error (parser))
5729  {
5730  result = NULL;
5731  goto end;
5732  }
5733  /* and attach s to the tail of result. NOTE: ORDER IS IMPORTANT and MUST be maintained. This used to call
5734  * pt_name_list_union, but since we only add unique ones, we no longer need to do a set union operation. */
5735  result = parser_append_node (temp, result);
5736  }
5737 
5738  /* go to the next subclass */
5739  dbl = dbl->next;
5740  }
5741 end:
5742  /* Delete it only if we created it */
5743  if (ismymht && names_mht)
5744  {
5745  mht_destroy (names_mht);
5746  }
5747 
5748  return result;
5749 }
5750 
5751 
5752 /*
5753  * pt_make_flat_name_list () - Create flat name list from entity spec
5754  * return: returns a list of PT_NAME nodes representing the class(es)
5755  * referred to by the entity spec
5756  * parser(in):
5757  * spec(in): A PT_SPEC node representing a single entity spec
5758  * spec_parent(in):
5759 
5760  * Note :
5761  * Case (A == 'sub-list (A,B,..)'):
5762  * Set list(A)= set-theoretic union of the names list(A), list(B), ...
5763  * (There is no ONLY or ALL in this case)
5764  * Case (A == 'ONLY X' || A == 'X' (only is implied)):
5765  * Set list(A) = the name 'X' which must be an existing class name.
5766  * Attach the db_object * to the db_object field in the name node.
5767  * Case (A == 'ALL X'):
5768  * Set list(A) = the name 'X' as above union the names of all
5769  * subclasses of X (recursively).
5770  * Case (A == 'ALL X EXCEPT Y'):
5771  * Set list(A) = list(ALL X) - list(Y)
5772  * (set-theoretic difference of the lists)
5773  * Additionally:
5774  * list(Y) must be a subset of list(X), else error.
5775  * list(X)-list(Y) must be non-empty, else error.
5776  */
5777 static PT_NODE *
5778 pt_make_flat_name_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * spec_parent, bool for_update)
5779 {
5780  PT_NODE *result = 0; /* the list of names to return */
5781  PT_NODE *temp, *temp1, *temp2, *name;
5782  DB_OBJECT *db; /* a temp for class object */
5783  const char *class_name = NULL; /* a temp to extract name from class */
5784  PT_NODE *e_node;
5785  DB_AUTH type;
5786  AU_FETCHMODE fetchmode;
5787 
5788  if (!spec)
5789  {
5790  return 0;
5791  }
5792  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
5793  {
5794  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5795  return NULL;
5796  }
5797 
5798  if (spec->info.spec.partition != NULL)
5799  {
5800  spec = pt_resolve_partition_spec (parser, spec, spec_parent, for_update);
5801  if (spec == NULL)
5802  {
5803  return spec;
5804  }
5805  return spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
5806  }
5807 
5808  name = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
5809  if (name == 0)
5810  {
5811  /* is a derived table */
5812  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5813  return NULL;
5814  } /* internal error */
5815 
5816  /* If name field points to a name node (i.e. is not a sublist ) then .. */
5817  if (name->node_type == PT_NAME)
5818  {
5819  DB_OBJECT *classop;
5820  SM_CLASS *class_;
5821 
5822  class_name = name->info.name.original;
5823  classop = db_find_class_with_purpose (class_name, for_update);
5824  if (classop != NULL)
5825  {
5826  if (for_update)
5827  {
5828  fetchmode = AU_FETCH_UPDATE;
5829  type = AU_ALTER;
5830  }
5831  else
5832  {
5833  fetchmode = AU_FETCH_READ;
5834  type = AU_SELECT;
5835  }
5836 
5837  if (au_fetch_class (classop, &class_, fetchmode, type) == NO_ERROR)
5838  {
5839  if (class_->partition != NULL)
5840  {
5841  if (class_->partition->pname == NULL)
5842  {
5843  /* parent partition class */
5844  name->info.name.partition = class_->partition;
5845  }
5846  else
5847  {
5848  if (spec_parent && spec_parent->node_type != PT_SELECT
5849  && spec_parent->node_type != PT_CREATE_INDEX && spec_parent->node_type != PT_DROP_INDEX
5850  && spec_parent->node_type != PT_ALTER_INDEX && spec_parent->node_type != PT_MERGE
5851  && spec_parent->node_type != PT_DELETE && spec_parent->node_type != PT_UPDATE
5852  && spec_parent->node_type != PT_INSERT)
5853  {
5854  /* partition not allowed */
5855  PT_ERRORm (parser, spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5856  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST);
5857  return NULL;
5858  }
5859  }
5860  }
5861  }
5862  }
5863  else
5864  {
5865  PT_ERRORc (parser, spec, db_error_string (3));
5866  return NULL;
5867  }
5868 
5869  /* if ONLY... */
5870  if (spec->info.spec.only_all == PT_ONLY)
5871  {
5872  /* Get the name */
5873  name->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
5874  name->info.name.meta_class = spec->info.spec.meta_class;
5875  /* Make sure this is the name of a class */
5876  db = pt_find_users_class (parser, name);
5877  name->info.name.db_object = db;
5878  if (!db)
5879  {
5880  return 0; /* error already set */
5881  }
5882  /* an error. Isn't a class name */
5883  /* create a new name node with this class name on it. Return it. */
5884  result = pt_name (parser, class_name);
5885  result->line_number = spec->line_number;
5886  result->column_number = spec->column_number;
5887  result->info.name.db_object = db;
5888  result->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
5889  result->info.name.meta_class = spec->info.spec.meta_class;
5890  result->info.name.partition = name->info.name.partition;
5891  return result; /* there can be no except part */
5892  }
5893 
5894  /* if ALL... */
5895  if (spec->info.spec.only_all == PT_ALL)
5896  {
5897  /* get the entity_name as a string */
5898  name->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
5899  name->info.name.meta_class = spec->info.spec.meta_class;
5900  /* get the DB_OBJECT of which it is the name */
5901  db = pt_find_users_class (parser, name);
5902  name->info.name.db_object = db;
5903  if (!db)
5904  {
5905  return 0;
5906  }
5907  /* get list of this class name and all its subclass names */
5908  temp =
5909  pt_make_subclass_list (parser, db, spec->line_number, spec->column_number, spec->info.spec.id,
5910  spec->info.spec.meta_class, NULL);
5911  if (temp == NULL)
5912  {
5913  return NULL;
5914  }
5915  /* do the EXCEPT part if present */
5916  if (spec->info.spec.except_list == 0)
5917  {
5918  temp1 = 0;
5919  }
5920  else
5921  {
5922  temp1 = NULL;
5923  for (e_node = spec->info.spec.except_list; e_node; e_node = e_node->next)
5924  {
5925  /* recursion */
5926  temp2 = pt_make_flat_name_list (parser, e_node, spec_parent, false);
5927  if (!temp2)
5928  {
5929  return NULL;
5930  }
5931  temp1 = parser_append_node (temp2, temp1);
5932  }
5933  }
5934 
5935  /* check that each item on the EXCEPT flat-list is, in fact, a subclass name that is on the 'ALL' flat-list */
5936  temp2 = temp1;
5937  while (temp2)
5938  {
5939  if (!pt_is_on_list (parser, temp2, temp))
5940  {
5941  PT_ERRORmf (parser, temp2, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_EXCEPTSPEC_NOT_HEIR,
5942  temp2->info.name.original);
5943  return 0;
5944  }
5945  temp2 = temp2->next;
5946  }
5947 
5948  /* return the difference of the two lists */
5949  result = pt_name_list_diff (parser, temp, temp1);
5950  if (!result)
5951  {
5952  PT_ERRORm (parser, temp, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SPEC_EXCLUDES_ALL);
5953  }
5954  return result;
5955  }
5956  /* end if ALL */
5957 
5958  /* parser internal error, wasn't ONLY or ALL */
5959  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5960  return 0;
5961  }
5962  /* end if not a sublist */
5963 
5964  /* If name field->ENTITY_SPEC node then we are dealing with a sublist: ( all A, B, all C except D, ...) There is no
5965  * ONLY/ALL/EXCEPT part for the sub-list as a whole. We take the union of all the names on the sub-list. */
5966  if (name->node_type == PT_SPEC)
5967  {
5968  result = 0;
5969  temp = name;
5970  /* for each (sub)entity_spec */
5971  while (temp)
5972  { /* recursion here */
5973  temp1 = pt_make_flat_name_list (parser, temp, spec_parent, for_update);
5974  result = pt_name_list_union (parser, result, temp1);
5975  temp = temp->next;
5976  }
5977 
5978  temp = result;
5979  while (temp)
5980  {
5981  temp->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
5982  temp->info.name.meta_class = spec->info.spec.meta_class;
5983  temp = temp->next;
5984  }
5985 
5986  return result;
5987  }
5988 
5989  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
5990  return 0; /* internal error, wasn't a name or a sublist */
5991 }
5992 
5993 
5994 /*
5995  * pt_must_have_exposed_name () - MUST assign a name (even a default one)
5996  * because later checks assume the range_var field is non-empty
5997  * return: 0 if error or can't assign a name. 1 if successful
5998  * parser(in):
5999  * p(in): a PT_SPEC node (list)
6000  *
6001  * Note :
6002  * For each item on the entity_spec list:
6003  * if not an entity spec, return 0
6004  * if .range_var already assigned, continue
6005  * if .range_var can be given the default (only class name) do it.
6006  * if can't assign name, return 0
6007  * Return 1 if every spec on list has a .range_var or can be given one
6008  * Set the .resolved field in each item in the flat list to
6009  * the corresponding exposed name. This is because in a query like:
6010  * select x.name,y.name from p x, p y both entity spec lists
6011  * generate the same flat list. We want to be able to tell them
6012  * apart later when we use them.
6013  */
6014 
6015 static int
6016 pt_must_have_exposed_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * p)
6017 {
6018  PT_NODE *q = 0, *r;
6019  PT_NODE *spec_first = p;
6020 
6021  while (p)
6022  {
6023  if (p->node_type == PT_SPEC)
6024  {
6025  /* if needs a name */
6026  if (p->info.spec.range_var == NULL)
6027  {
6028  q = p->info.spec.entity_name;
6029  /* if an exposed name is not given, then exposed name is itself. */
6030  if (q && q->node_type == PT_NAME)
6031  { /* not a sub list */
6032  q->info.name.spec_id = p->info.spec.id;
6033  q->info.name.meta_class = p->info.spec.meta_class;
6034  p->info.spec.range_var = parser_copy_tree (parser, q);
6035  p->info.spec.range_var->info.name.resolved = NULL;
6036  }
6037  else if (p->info.spec.cte_name)
6038  {
6039  /* The name of the spec should be the name of the CTE */
6040  p->info.spec.range_var = parser_copy_tree (parser, p->info.spec.cte_name);
6041  }
6042  else
6043  {
6044  const char *unique_exposed_name;
6045  /*
6046  * Was sublist, they didn't give a correlation variable name so We generate a unique name and attach
6047  * it. */
6048  r = parser_new_node (parser, PT_NAME);
6049 
6050  if (r == NULL)
6051  {
6052  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6053  return 0;
6054  }
6055 
6056  r->info.name.spec_id = p->info.spec.id;
6057  r->info.name.meta_class = p->info.spec.meta_class;
6058 
6059  unique_exposed_name = pt_get_unique_exposed_name (parser, spec_first);
6060 
6061  if (unique_exposed_name == NULL)
6062  {
6063  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new table name");
6064  return 0;
6065  }
6066 
6067  r->info.name.original = unique_exposed_name;
6068  r->line_number = p->line_number;
6069  r->column_number = p->column_number;
6070  p->info.spec.range_var = r;
6071  }
6072  }
6073  p->info.spec.range_var->info.name.meta_class = p->info.spec.meta_class;
6074  /* If we get here, the item has a name. Copy name-pointer to the resolved field of each item on flat entity
6075  * list */
6076  q = p->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
6077  while (q)
6078  {
6079  q->info.name.resolved = p->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
6080  if (PT_IS_SPEC_REAL_TABLE (p))
6081  {
6082  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (q, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
6083  }
6084  q = q->next;
6085  }
6086  p = p->next;
6087  }
6088  } /* continue while() */
6089 
6090  return 1;
6091 }
6092 
6093 
6094 /*
6095  * pt_object_to_data_type () - create a PT_DATA_TYPE node that corresponds
6096  * to it and return it
6097  * return: PT_NODE * to a data_type node
6098  * parser(in):
6099  * class_list(in):
6100  */
6101 static PT_NODE *
6102 pt_object_to_data_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * class_list)
6103 {
6104  PT_NODE *result;
6105  result = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
6106  if (result == NULL)
6107  {
6108  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6109  return NULL;
6110  }
6111 
6112  result->type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
6113  result->info.data_type.entity = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, class_list);
6114  result->info.data_type.virt_type_enum = PT_TYPE_OBJECT;
6115  result->line_number = class_list->line_number;
6116  result->column_number = class_list->column_number;
6117  return result;
6118 }
6119 
6120 /*
6121  * pt_resolve_star_reserved_names () - Resolves '*' value in select list
6122  * when a hint that activates reserved
6123  * names is used.
6124  *
6125  * return : List of reserved names.
6126  * parser (in) : Parser context.
6127  * from (in) : Query spec.
6128  *
6129  * NOTE: The reserved names depend on the scan type flag on from node.
6130  */
6131 static PT_NODE *
6132 pt_resolve_star_reserved_names (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * from)
6133 {
6134  PT_NODE *reserved_names = NULL;
6135  PT_NODE *new_name = NULL;
6136  int i, start, end;
6137  PT_RESERVED_NAME_TYPE reserved_name_type;
6138 
6139  if (parser == NULL || from == NULL || from->node_type != PT_SPEC)
6140  {
6141  assert (0);
6142  return NULL;
6143  }
6144 
6145  reserved_name_type = PT_SPEC_GET_RESERVED_NAME_TYPE (from);
6146  if (reserved_name_type == RESERVED_NAME_INVALID)
6147  {
6148  assert (0);
6149  return NULL;
6150  }
6151 
6152  PT_GET_RESERVED_NAME_FIRST_AND_LAST (reserved_name_type, start, end);
6153 
6154  for (i = start; i <= end; i++)
6155  {
6156  /* create a new node for each reserved name */
6157  new_name = pt_name (parser, pt_Reserved_name_table[i].name);
6158  if (new_name == NULL)
6159  {
6160  PT_ERRORm (parser, from, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
6161  parser_free_tree (parser, reserved_names);
6162  return NULL;
6163  }
6164  /* mark the node as reserved */
6165  new_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_RESERVED;
6166  new_name->info.name.reserved_id = pt_Reserved_name_table[i].id;
6167  /* resolve name */
6168  new_name->info.name.spec_id = from->info.spec.id;
6169  new_name->info.name.resolved = from->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
6170  /* set type enum to the expected type */
6171  new_name->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (pt_Reserved_name_table[i].type);
6172  if (new_name->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
6173  {
6174  new_name->data_type =
6175  pt_domain_to_data_type (parser,
6176  tp_domain_resolve (pt_Reserved_name_table[i].type,
6177  from->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object, 0, 0, NULL,
6178  0));
6179  }
6180  /* append to name list */
6181  reserved_names = parser_append_node (new_name, reserved_names);
6182  }
6183  /* return reserved name list */
6184  return reserved_names;
6185 }
6186 
6187 /*
6188  * pt_resolve_star () - resolve the '*' as in a query
6189  * Replace the star with an equivalent list x.a, x.b, y.a, y.d ...
6190  * return:
6191  * parser(in):
6192  * from(in): a PT_SELECT node
6193  * attr(in): NULL if "*", non-NULL if "class_name.*"
6194  *
6195  * Note :
6196  * ASSUMES
6197  * Flat entity lists in the 'from' clause have already been created.
6198  * Items in from list all have or have been given an exposed name.
6199  */
6200 PT_NODE *
6201 pt_resolve_star (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * from, PT_NODE * attr)
6202 {
6203  PT_NODE *flat_list;
6204  PT_NODE *flat, *spec_att, *class_att, *attr_name, *range, *result = NULL;
6205  PT_NODE *spec = from;
6206 
6207  if (PT_SHOULD_BIND_RESERVED_NAME (from))
6208  {
6209  return pt_resolve_star_reserved_names (parser, from);
6210  }
6211 
6212  while (spec)
6213  {
6214  if (attr)
6215  { /* resolve "class_name.*" */
6216  if (attr->info.name.spec_id != spec->info.spec.id)
6217  {
6218  spec = spec->next; /* skip to next spec */
6219  continue;
6220  }
6221  }
6222 
6223  /* spec_att := all attributes of this entity spec */
6224  spec_att = NULL;
6225 
6226  if (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (spec) || PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec))
6227  {
6228  spec_att = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, spec->info.spec.as_attr_list);
6229  }
6230  else
6231  {
6232  /* spec_att := intersection of all attributes of spec's subclasses */
6233  assert (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec));
6234  flat_list = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
6235  for (flat = flat_list; flat; flat = flat->next)
6236  {
6237  /* get attribute list for this class flat */
6238  class_att = pt_get_all_attributes_and_types (parser, flat, spec);
6239  /* take intersection except first time */
6240  spec_att = ((flat == flat_list) ? class_att : pt_common_attribute (parser, spec_att, class_att));
6241 
6242  if (pt_has_error (parser))
6243  {
6244  return NULL;
6245  }
6246  }
6247  }
6248 
6249  attr_name = spec_att;
6250  range = spec->info.spec.range_var;
6251  while (attr_name)
6252  {
6253  if (range)
6254  {
6255  attr_name->info.name.resolved = range->info.name.original;
6256  }
6257 
6258  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (attr_name, (attr) ? PT_NAME_INFO_DOT_STAR : PT_NAME_INFO_STAR);
6259  /* expand "attr" into "attr.tdata" if the attr is TEXT */
6260  if (attr_name->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT && !PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (attr_name, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL))
6261  {
6262  DB_ATTRIBUTE *att = NULL;
6263  PT_NODE *entity_name = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
6264  if (entity_name && entity_name->node_type == PT_NAME && entity_name->info.name.db_object)
6265  {
6266  att = db_get_attribute (entity_name->info.name.db_object, attr_name->info.name.original);
6267  }
6268 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
6269  if (att && sm_has_text_domain (att, 0))
6270  {
6271  PT_NODE *prev_entity;
6272  PT_NODE *save_next = attr_name->next;
6273  PT_NODE *dot_arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, attr_name);
6274  PT_NODE *dot_arg2 = pt_name (parser, "tdata");
6275  if (!dot_arg1 || !dot_arg2)
6276  {
6277  return NULL;
6278  }
6279  else
6280  {
6281  parser_init_node (attr_name);
6282  attr_name->node_type = PT_DOT_;
6283  attr_name->info.dot.arg1 = dot_arg1;
6284  attr_name->info.dot.arg2 = dot_arg2;
6285  attr_name->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, dot_arg1->info.name.original);
6286  if (!attr_name->alias_print)
6287  {
6288  return NULL;
6289  }
6290  attr_name = pt_get_resolution (parser, NULL, spec, attr_name, &prev_entity, 1);
6291  if (!attr_name)
6292  {
6293  return NULL;
6294  }
6295  attr_name->next = save_next;
6296  }
6297  }
6298 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
6299  }
6300  attr_name = attr_name->next;
6301  }
6302 
6303  if (result)
6304  {
6305  /* attach spec_att to end of result */
6306  attr_name = result;
6307  while (attr_name->next)
6308  {
6309  attr_name = attr_name->next;
6310  }
6311  attr_name->next = spec_att;
6312  }
6313  else
6314  {
6315  result = spec_att;
6316  }
6317 
6318  if (attr)
6319  {
6320  break;
6321  }
6322  spec = spec->next;
6323  }
6324 
6325  return result;
6326 }
6327 
6328 /*
6329  * pt_resolve_vclass_args () - modifies the attribute list in the insert
6330  * statement by adding to the specified attributes the ones missing with
6331  * their default values (if not null). is applied only to views.
6332  *
6333  * return: the modified statement
6334  * parser(in):
6335  * statement(in): insert statement
6336  *
6337  * NOTE: this step is needed because all information on the view is lost after
6338  * translate (including default values for the missing attributes).
6339  */
6340 static PT_NODE *
6341 pt_resolve_vclass_args (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
6342 {
6343  PT_NODE *spec;
6344  PT_NODE *entity_name;
6345  PT_NODE *attr_list, *attr;
6346  PT_NODE *value_clauses, *value_list;
6347  PT_NODE *crt_node;
6348  PT_NODE *rest_attrs, *rest_values;
6349  DB_OBJECT *db_obj;
6350  SM_ATTRIBUTE *db_attributes, *db_attr;
6351  int is_values, is_vclass = 0;
6352  int is_subqery;
6353 
6354  if (!statement || statement->node_type != PT_INSERT)
6355  {
6356  /* do nothing */
6357  return statement;
6358  }
6359 
6360  spec = statement->info.insert.spec;
6361  entity_name = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
6362  if (!entity_name || entity_name->node_type != PT_NAME)
6363  {
6364  /* enitity_name should be resolved before going further */
6365  return statement;
6366  }
6367  db_obj = entity_name->info.name.db_object;
6368  if (!db_obj)
6369  {
6370  /* this applies only for views */
6371  return statement;
6372  }
6373  is_vclass = db_is_vclass (db_obj);
6374  if (is_vclass < 0)
6375  {
6376  PT_ERRORc (parser, statement, er_msg ());
6377  goto error;
6378  }
6379  if (!is_vclass)
6380  {
6381  return statement;
6382  }
6383 
6384  value_clauses = statement->info.insert.value_clauses;
6385  value_list = value_clauses->info.node_list.list;
6386  attr_list = statement->info.insert.attr_list;
6387  if (!attr_list)
6388  {
6389  return statement;
6390  }
6391 
6392  is_values = (value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_VALUE);
6393  is_subqery = (value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY);
6394 
6395  db_attributes = db_get_attributes_force (db_obj);
6396  if (db_attributes == NULL)
6397  {
6398  return statement;
6399  }
6400 
6401  rest_attrs = NULL;
6402  rest_values = NULL;
6403 
6404  for (db_attr = db_attributes; db_attr; db_attr = db_attribute_next (db_attr))
6405  {
6406  const char *name = db_attr->header.name;
6407 
6408  if (db_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type == DB_DEFAULT_NONE
6409  && DB_IS_NULL (&db_attr->default_value.value))
6410  {
6411  continue;
6412  }
6413 
6414  for (attr = attr_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
6415  {
6416  if (pt_str_compare (name, attr->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
6417  {
6418  break;
6419  }
6420  }
6421  if (!attr)
6422  {
6423  /* create attribute & default value and update rest_lists */
6424  attr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_NAME);
6425  if (!attr)
6426  {
6427  PT_ERROR (parser, statement, "allocation error");
6428  goto error;
6429  }
6430  attr->info.name.original = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, name);
6431  if (attr->info.name.original == NULL)
6432  {
6433  PT_ERRORc (parser, statement, er_msg ());
6434  goto error;
6435  }
6436  if (rest_attrs)
6437  {
6438  rest_attrs = parser_append_node (attr, rest_attrs);
6439  }
6440  else
6441  {
6442  rest_attrs = attr;
6443  }
6444  if (is_values)
6445  {
6446  PT_NODE *val = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
6447  if (!val)
6448  {
6449  PT_ERROR (parser, statement, "allocation error");
6450  goto error;
6451  }
6452  val->info.expr.op = PT_DEFAULTF;
6453  if (rest_values)
6454  {
6455  rest_values = parser_append_node (val, rest_values);
6456  }
6457  else
6458  {
6459  rest_values = val;
6460  }
6461  }
6462  if (is_subqery)
6463  {
6464  PT_NODE *val = pt_sm_attribute_default_value_to_node (parser,
6465  db_attr);
6466  if (!val)
6467  {
6468  /* error was already handled */
6469  goto error;
6470  }
6471 
6472  if (rest_values)
6473  {
6474  rest_values = parser_append_node (val, rest_values);
6475  }
6476  else
6477  {
6478  rest_values = val;
6479  }
6480  }
6481  }
6482  }
6483 
6484  if (!rest_attrs || !rest_values)
6485  {
6486  /* nothing to do */
6487  return statement;
6488  }
6489 
6490  statement->info.insert.attr_list = parser_append_node (rest_attrs, attr_list);
6491  if (is_values)
6492  {
6493  for (crt_node = value_clauses; crt_node; crt_node = crt_node->next)
6494  {
6495  /* a different copy of rest_values is needed for each node in the node list */
6496  PT_NODE *new_rest_values = parser_copy_tree_list (parser,
6497  rest_values);
6498  if (!new_rest_values)
6499  {
6500  goto error;
6501  }
6502  crt_node->info.node_list.list = parser_append_node (new_rest_values, crt_node->info.node_list.list);
6503  }
6504  /* only copied of rest_values are used, has to be freed */
6505  parser_free_tree (parser, rest_values);
6506  }
6507  if (is_subqery)
6508  {
6509  statement->info.insert.value_clauses->info.node_list.list =
6510  pt_append_query_select_list (parser, value_list, rest_values);
6511  }
6512 
6513  return statement;
6514 
6515 error:
6516  if (rest_attrs)
6517  {
6518  parser_free_tree (parser, rest_attrs);
6519  }
6520  if (rest_values)
6521  {
6522  parser_free_tree (parser, rest_values);
6523  }
6524  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
6525  {
6526  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_GENERIC_ERROR));
6527  }
6528 
6529  return NULL;
6530 }
6531 
6532 /*
6533  * pt_resolve_hint_args () -
6534  * return: NO_ERROR on success, non-zero for ERROR
6535  * parser(in):
6536  * arg_list(in/out):
6537  * spec_list(in):
6538  * discard_no_match(in): remove unmatched node from arg_list
6539  */
6540 static int
6541 pt_resolve_hint_args (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE ** arg_list, PT_NODE * spec_list, bool discard_no_match)
6542 {
6543 
6544  PT_NODE *arg, *spec, *range, *prev, *tmp;
6545 
6546  prev = NULL;
6547  arg = *arg_list;
6548 
6549  while (arg != NULL)
6550  {
6551  if (arg->node_type != PT_NAME || arg->info.name.original == NULL)
6552  {
6553  goto exit_on_error;
6554  }
6555 
6556  /* check if the specified class name exists in spec list */
6557  for (spec = spec_list; spec; spec = spec->next)
6558  {
6559  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
6560  {
6561  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
6562  goto exit_on_error;
6563  }
6564 
6565  if ((range = spec->info.spec.range_var)
6566  && !pt_str_compare (range->info.name.original, arg->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
6567  {
6568  /* found match */
6569  arg->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
6570  arg->info.name.meta_class = PT_HINT_NAME;
6571  break;
6572  }
6573  }
6574 
6575  /* not found */
6576  if (spec == NULL)
6577  {
6578  if (discard_no_match)
6579  {
6580  tmp = arg;
6581  arg = arg->next;
6582  tmp->next = NULL;
6583  parser_free_node (parser, tmp);
6584 
6585  if (prev == NULL)
6586  {
6587  *arg_list = arg;
6588  }
6589  else
6590  {
6591  prev->next = arg;
6592  }
6593  }
6594  else
6595  {
6596  goto exit_on_error;
6597  }
6598  }
6599  else
6600  {
6601  prev = arg;
6602  arg = arg->next;
6603  }
6604  }
6605 
6606  return NO_ERROR;
6607 exit_on_error:
6608 
6609  return ER_FAILED;
6610 }
6611 
6612 /*
6613  * pt_resolve_hint () -
6614  * return:
6615  * parser(in):
6616  * node(in):
6617  */
6618 static int
6619 pt_resolve_hint (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
6620 {
6621  PT_HINT_ENUM hint;
6622  PT_NODE **ordered = NULL, **use_nl = NULL, **use_idx = NULL;
6623  PT_NODE **use_merge = NULL, **index_ss = NULL, **index_ls = NULL;
6624  PT_NODE *spec_list = NULL;
6625 
6626  switch (node->node_type)
6627  {
6628  case PT_SELECT:
6629  hint = node->info.query.q.select.hint;
6630  ordered = &node->info.query.q.select.ordered;
6631  use_nl = &node->info.query.q.select.use_nl;
6632  use_idx = &node->info.query.q.select.use_idx;
6633  index_ss = &node->info.query.q.select.index_ss;
6634  index_ls = &node->info.query.q.select.index_ls;
6635  use_merge = &node->info.query.q.select.use_merge;
6636  spec_list = node->info.query.q.select.from;
6637  break;
6638  case PT_DELETE:
6639  hint = node->info.delete_.hint;
6640  ordered = &node->info.delete_.ordered_hint;
6641  use_nl = &node->info.delete_.use_nl_hint;
6642  use_idx = &node->info.delete_.use_idx_hint;
6643  use_merge = &node->info.delete_.use_merge_hint;
6644  spec_list = node->info.delete_.spec;
6645  break;
6646  case PT_UPDATE:
6647  hint = node->info.update.hint;
6648  ordered = &node->info.update.ordered_hint;
6649  use_nl = &node->info.update.use_nl_hint;
6650  use_idx = &node->info.update.use_idx_hint;
6651  use_merge = &node->info.update.use_merge_hint;
6652  spec_list = node->info.update.spec;
6653  break;
6654  default:
6655  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Invalid statement in hints resolving");
6656  return ER_FAILED;
6657  }
6658 
6659  if (hint & PT_HINT_ORDERED)
6660  {
6661  if (pt_resolve_hint_args (parser, ordered, spec_list, REQUIRE_ALL_MATCH) != NO_ERROR)
6662  {
6663  goto exit_on_error;
6664  }
6665  }
6666 
6667 #if 0
6668  if (hint & PT_HINT_Y)
6669  { /* not used */
6670  }
6671 #endif /* 0 */
6672 
6673  if (hint & PT_HINT_USE_NL)
6674  {
6675  if (pt_resolve_hint_args (parser, use_nl, spec_list, REQUIRE_ALL_MATCH) != NO_ERROR)
6676  {
6677  goto exit_on_error;
6678  }
6679  }
6680 
6681  if (hint & PT_HINT_USE_IDX)
6682  {
6683  if (pt_resolve_hint_args (parser, use_idx, spec_list, REQUIRE_ALL_MATCH) != NO_ERROR)
6684  {
6685  goto exit_on_error;
6686  }
6687  }
6688 
6689  /* *index_ss == NULL means apply index skip scan to each table */
6690  if ((hint & PT_HINT_INDEX_SS) && *index_ss != NULL)
6691  {
6692  if (pt_resolve_hint_args (parser, index_ss, spec_list, DISCARD_NO_MATCH) != NO_ERROR)
6693  {
6694  goto exit_on_error;
6695  }
6696 
6697  /* clear hint if no matched any item */
6698  if (*index_ss == NULL)
6699  {
6700  node->info.query.q.select.hint = (PT_HINT_ENUM) (node->info.query.q.select.hint & ~PT_HINT_INDEX_SS);
6701  }
6702  }
6703 
6704  /* *index_ls == NULL means apply loose index scan to each table */
6705  if ((hint & PT_HINT_INDEX_LS) && *index_ls != NULL)
6706  {
6707  if (pt_resolve_hint_args (parser, index_ls, spec_list, DISCARD_NO_MATCH) != NO_ERROR)
6708  {
6709  goto exit_on_error;
6710  }
6711 
6712  /* clear hint if no matched any item */
6713  if (*index_ls == NULL)
6714  {
6715  node->info.query.q.select.hint = (PT_HINT_ENUM) (node->info.query.q.select.hint & ~PT_HINT_INDEX_LS);
6716  }
6717  }
6718 
6719  if (hint & PT_HINT_USE_MERGE)
6720  {
6721  if (pt_resolve_hint_args (parser, use_merge, spec_list, REQUIRE_ALL_MATCH) != NO_ERROR)
6722  {
6723  goto exit_on_error;
6724  }
6725  }
6726 
6727 #if 0
6728  if (hint & PT_HINT_USE_HASH)
6729  { /* not used */
6730  }
6731 #endif /* 0 */
6732 
6733  return NO_ERROR;
6734 exit_on_error:
6735 
6736  /* clear hint info */
6737  node->info.query.q.select.hint = PT_HINT_NONE;
6738  if (*ordered != NULL)
6739  {
6740  parser_free_tree (parser, *ordered);
6741  }
6742  if (*use_nl != NULL)
6743  {
6744  parser_free_tree (parser, *use_nl);
6745  }
6746  if (*use_idx != NULL)
6747  {
6748  parser_free_tree (parser, *use_idx);
6749  }
6750  if (index_ss != NULL && *index_ss != NULL)
6751  {
6752  parser_free_tree (parser, *index_ss);
6753  }
6754  if (index_ls != NULL && *index_ls != NULL)
6755  {
6756  parser_free_tree (parser, *index_ls);
6757  }
6758  if (*use_merge != NULL)
6759  {
6760  parser_free_tree (parser, *use_merge);
6761  }
6762 
6763  switch (node->node_type)
6764  {
6765  case PT_SELECT:
6766  node->info.query.q.select.ordered = NULL;
6767  node->info.query.q.select.use_nl = NULL;
6768  node->info.query.q.select.use_idx = NULL;
6769  node->info.query.q.select.index_ss = NULL;
6770  node->info.query.q.select.index_ls = NULL;
6771  node->info.query.q.select.use_merge = NULL;
6772  break;
6773  case PT_DELETE:
6774  node->info.delete_.ordered_hint = NULL;
6775  node->info.delete_.use_nl_hint = NULL;
6776  node->info.delete_.use_idx_hint = NULL;
6777  node->info.delete_.use_merge_hint = NULL;
6778  break;
6779  case PT_UPDATE:
6780  node->info.update.ordered_hint = NULL;
6781  node->info.update.use_nl_hint = NULL;
6782  node->info.update.use_idx_hint = NULL;
6783  node->info.update.use_merge_hint = NULL;
6784  break;
6785  default:
6786  break;
6787  }
6788 
6789  return ER_FAILED;
6790 }
6791 
6792 /*
6793  * pt_resolve_using_index () -
6794  * return:
6795  * parser(in):
6796  * index(in):
6797  * from(in):
6798  */
6799 PT_NODE *
6800 pt_resolve_using_index (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * index, PT_NODE * from)
6801 {
6802  PT_NODE *spec, *range, *entity;
6803  DB_OBJECT *classop;
6804  SM_CLASS *class_;
6805  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *cons;
6806  int found = 0;
6807  int errid;
6808 
6809  if (index == NULL || index->info.name.original == NULL)
6810  {
6811  if (index->etc != (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_CLASS_NONE)
6812  {
6813  /* the case of USING INDEX NONE */
6814  return index;
6815  }
6816  }
6817 
6818  assert (index != NULL);
6819 
6820  if (index->info.name.spec_id != 0) /* already resolved */
6821  {
6822  return index;
6823  }
6824  if (index->info.name.resolved != NULL)
6825  {
6826  /* index name is specified by class name as "class.index" */
6827 
6828  /* check if the specified class name exists in spec list */
6829  for (spec = from; spec; spec = spec->next)
6830  {
6831  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
6832  {
6833  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
6834  return NULL;
6835  }
6836 
6837  range = spec->info.spec.range_var;
6838  entity = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
6839  if (range && entity
6840  && !pt_str_compare (range->info.name.original, index->info.name.resolved, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
6841  {
6842  classop = db_find_class (entity->info.name.original);
6843  if (au_fetch_class (classop, &class_, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT) != NO_ERROR)
6844  {
6845  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6846  errid = er_errid ();
6847  if (errid == ER_AU_SELECT_FAILURE || errid == ER_AU_AUTHORIZATION_FAILURE)
6848  {
6849  PT_ERRORc (parser, entity, er_msg ());
6850  }
6851  else
6852  {
6853  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
6854  }
6855 
6856  return NULL;
6857  }
6858  if (index->info.name.original != NULL)
6859  {
6860  cons = classobj_find_class_index (class_, index->info.name.original);
6861  if (cons == NULL)
6862  {
6863  /* error; the index is not for the specified class */
6864  PT_ERRORmf (parser, index, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USING_INDEX_ERR_1,
6865  pt_short_print (parser, index));
6866  return NULL;
6867  }
6868  else if (cons->index_status == SM_ONLINE_INDEX_BUILDING_IN_PROGRESS)
6869  {
6870  // TODO: raise an error?
6871  return NULL; // unusable index
6872  }
6873  else if (cons->index_status == SM_INVISIBLE_INDEX)
6874  {
6875  // TODO: raise an error?
6876  return NULL; // unusable index
6877  }
6878  }
6879  index->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
6880  index->info.name.meta_class = PT_INDEX_NAME;
6881  /* "class.index" is valid */
6882  return index;
6883  }
6884  }
6885 
6886  /* the specified class in "class.index" does not exist in spec list */
6887  PT_ERRORmf (parser, index, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USING_INDEX_ERR_2,
6888  pt_short_print (parser, index));
6889  return NULL;
6890  }
6891  else
6892  { /* if (index->info.name.resolved != NULL) */
6893  /* index name without class name specification */
6894 
6895  /* find the class of the index from spec list */
6896  for (spec = from; spec; spec = spec->next)
6897  {
6898  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
6899  {
6900  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
6901  return NULL;
6902  }
6903 
6904  range = spec->info.spec.range_var;
6905  entity = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
6906  if (range != NULL && entity != NULL && entity->info.name.original != NULL)
6907  {
6908  classop = db_find_class (entity->info.name.original);
6909  if (classop == NULL)
6910  {
6911  break;
6912  }
6913  if (au_fetch_class (classop, &class_, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT) != NO_ERROR)
6914  {
6915  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6916  errid = er_errid ();
6917  if (errid == ER_AU_SELECT_FAILURE || errid == ER_AU_AUTHORIZATION_FAILURE)
6918  {
6919  PT_ERRORc (parser, entity, er_msg ());
6920  }
6921  else
6922  {
6923  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
6924  }
6925 
6926  return NULL;
6927  }
6928  cons = classobj_find_class_index (class_, index->info.name.original);
6929  if (cons != NULL
6930  && (cons->index_status == SM_NORMAL_INDEX || cons->index_status == SM_ONLINE_INDEX_BUILDING_DONE))
6931  {
6932  /* found the class; resolve index name */
6933  found++;
6934  index->info.name.resolved = range->info.name.original;
6935  index->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
6936  index->info.name.meta_class = PT_INDEX_NAME;
6937  }
6938  // TODO: raise an error for such indexes??
6939  }
6940  }
6941 
6942  if (found == 0)
6943  {
6944  /* error; can not find the class of the index */
6945  PT_ERRORmf (parser, index, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USING_INDEX_ERR_1,
6946  pt_short_print (parser, index));
6947  return NULL;
6948  }
6949  else if (found > 1)
6950  {
6951  index->info.name.resolved = NULL;
6952  /* we found more than one classes which have index of the same name */
6953  PT_ERRORmf (parser, index, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USING_INDEX_ERR_3,
6954  pt_short_print (parser, index));
6955  return NULL;
6956  }
6957 
6958  }
6959 
6960  return index;
6961 }
6962 
6963 /*
6964  * pt_str_compare () -
6965  * return: 0 if two strings are equal. 1 if not equal
6966  * p(in): A string
6967  * q(in): A string
6968  *
6969  * Note :
6970  * two NULL strings are considered a match.
6971  * two strings of length zero match
6972  * A NULL string does NOT match a zero length string
6973  */
6974 int
6975 pt_str_compare (const char *p, const char *q, CASE_SENSITIVENESS case_flag)
6976 {
6977  if (!p && !q)
6978  {
6979  return 0;
6980  }
6981  if (!p || !q)
6982  {
6983  return 1;
6984  }
6985 
6986  if (case_flag == CASE_INSENSITIVE)
6987  {
6988  return intl_identifier_casecmp (p, q);
6989  }
6990  else
6991  {
6992  return intl_identifier_cmp (p, q);
6993  }
6994 }
6995 
6996 /*
6997  * pt_get_unique_exposed_name () -
6998  * return:
6999  *
7000  * parser(in):
7001  * first_spec(in):
7002  */
7003 static const char *
7004 pt_get_unique_exposed_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * first_spec)
7005 {
7006  char name_buf[32];
7007  int i = 1;
7008 
7009  if (first_spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
7010  {
7011  assert (first_spec->node_type == PT_SPEC);
7012  return NULL;
7013  }
7014 
7015  while (1)
7016  {
7017  snprintf (name_buf, 32, "__t%u", i);
7018  if (pt_name_occurs_in_from_list (parser, name_buf, first_spec) == 0)
7019  {
7020  return pt_append_string (parser, NULL, name_buf);
7021  }
7022  i++;
7023  }
7024 
7025  return NULL;
7026 }
7027 
7028 /*
7029  * pt_quick_resolve_names () - resolve names in node_p based on the spec
7030  * spec_p
7031  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
7032  * parser (in) : parser context
7033  * spec_p (in/out) : PT_SPEC for the table containing the names in node_p
7034  * node_p (in/out) : the node to resolve
7035  * sc_info (in): semantic check info
7036  *
7037  * Note: Call this function to resolve the names in a node outside of a
7038  * statement context
7039  */
7040 int
7041 pt_quick_resolve_names (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE ** spec_p, PT_NODE ** node_p, SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO * sc_info)
7042 {
7043  PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG bind_arg;
7044  PT_NODE *spec = NULL, *node = NULL;
7045  int walk = 0;
7046  SCOPES scopestack;
7047  PT_EXTRA_SPECS_FRAME spec_frame;
7048  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO info;
7049 
7050  if (node_p == NULL || spec_p == NULL)
7051  {
7052  assert (false);
7053  return ER_FAILED;
7054  }
7055 
7056  spec = *spec_p;
7057  node = *node_p;
7058  if (spec == NULL || node == NULL)
7059  {
7060  assert (false);
7061  return ER_FAILED;
7062  }
7063 
7064  /* convert spec to a flat entity list */
7065  info.spec_parent = NULL;
7066  info.for_update = false;
7067  spec = pt_flat_spec_pre (parser, spec, &info, &walk);
7068 
7069  /* bind spec in scope */
7070  bind_arg.scopes = NULL;
7071  bind_arg.spec_frames = NULL;
7072  bind_arg.sc_info = sc_info;
7073 
7074  scopestack.next = bind_arg.scopes;
7075  scopestack.specs = spec;
7076  scopestack.correlation_level = 0;
7077  scopestack.location = 0;
7078 
7079  bind_arg.scopes = &scopestack;
7080  spec_frame.next = bind_arg.spec_frames;
7081  spec_frame.extra_specs = NULL;
7082  bind_arg.spec_frames = &spec_frame;
7083 
7084  *spec_p = spec;
7085  node = *node_p;
7086  /* resolve expression */
7087  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_bind_names, &bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, &bind_arg);
7088 
7089  node_p = &node;
7090  return NO_ERROR;
7091 }
7092 
7093 /*
7094  * natural_join_equal_attr () - If the two attributes have same name,
7095  * the function return true. We don't consider the type there.
7096  * Whether the join can be executed is dependent on whether the
7097  * two types are compatible. If not, the error will be threw by
7098  * subsequent process.
7099  * return:
7100  * lhs(in):
7101  * rhs(in):
7102  */
7103 static bool
7104 natural_join_equal_attr (NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO * lhs, NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO * rhs)
7105 {
7106  const char *lhs_name;
7107  const char *rhs_name;
7108 
7109  assert (lhs != NULL && rhs != NULL);
7110 
7111  lhs_name = lhs->name;
7112  rhs_name = rhs->name;
7113 
7114  if (lhs_name == NULL || rhs_name == NULL)
7115  {
7116  return false;
7117  }
7118 
7119  if (intl_identifier_casecmp (lhs_name, rhs_name) == 0)
7120  {
7121  return true;
7122  }
7123 
7124  return false;
7125 }
7126 
7127 /*
7128  * free_natural_join_attrs () -
7129  * return:
7130  * attrs(in):
7131  */
7132 static void
7133 free_natural_join_attrs (NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO * attrs)
7134 {
7135  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_cur;
7136  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_cur_next;
7137 
7138  attr_cur = attrs;
7139  while (attr_cur != NULL)
7140  {
7141  attr_cur_next = attr_cur->next;
7142  free (attr_cur);
7143  attr_cur = attr_cur_next;
7144  }
7145 }
7146 
7147 /*
7148  * generate_natural_join_attrs_from_subquery () -
7149  * return:
7150  * subquery_attrs_list(in):
7151  * attrs_p(out):
7152  */
7153 static int
7154 generate_natural_join_attrs_from_subquery (PT_NODE * subquery_attrs_list, NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO ** attrs_p)
7155 {
7156  PT_NODE *pt_cur;
7157  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_head = NULL;
7158  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_tail = NULL;
7159  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_cur;
7160 
7161  for (pt_cur = subquery_attrs_list; pt_cur != NULL; pt_cur = pt_cur->next)
7162  {
7163  /*
7164  * We just deal the attributes which have name. It means we just
7165  * deal PT_NAME or other's pt_node have alias_name. For example,
7166  * select 1 from t1. The '1' is impossible to be used in natural
7167  * join, so we skip it.
7168  */
7169 
7170  if (pt_cur->alias_print == NULL && pt_cur->node_type != PT_NAME)
7171  {
7172  continue;
7173  }
7174 
7175  attr_cur = (NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *) malloc (sizeof (NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO));
7176  if (attr_cur == NULL)
7177  {
7178  goto exit_on_error;
7179  }
7180 
7181  attr_cur->next = NULL;
7182 
7183  /*
7184  * Alias name have higher priority. select a as txx from ....
7185  * We consider txx as the attribute's name and ignore a.
7186  */
7187  if (pt_cur->alias_print)
7188  {
7189  attr_cur->name = (char *) pt_cur->alias_print;
7190  }
7191  else
7192  {
7193  if (pt_cur->node_type == PT_NAME)
7194  {
7195  attr_cur->name = (char *) pt_cur->info.name.original;
7196  }
7197  }
7198 
7199  attr_cur->type_enum = pt_cur->type_enum;
7200 
7201  attr_cur->meta_class = PT_NORMAL;
7202  if (pt_cur->node_type == PT_NAME)
7203  {
7204  attr_cur->meta_class = pt_cur->info.name.meta_class;
7205  }
7206 
7207  if (attr_head == NULL)
7208  {
7209  attr_head = attr_cur;
7210  attr_tail = attr_cur;
7211  }
7212  else
7213  {
7214  attr_tail->next = attr_cur;
7215  attr_tail = attr_cur;
7216  }
7217  }
7218 
7219  *attrs_p = attr_head;
7220  return NO_ERROR;
7221 
7222 exit_on_error:
7223  free_natural_join_attrs (attr_head);
7224  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
7225 }
7226 
7227 
7228 /*
7229  * generate_natural_join_attrs_from_db_attrs () -
7230  * return:
7231  * db_attrs(in):
7232  * attrs_p(out):
7233  */
7234 static int
7235 generate_natural_join_attrs_from_db_attrs (DB_ATTRIBUTE * db_attrs, NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO ** attrs_p)
7236 {
7237  DB_ATTRIBUTE *db_attr_cur;
7238  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_head = NULL;
7239  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_tail = NULL;
7240  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *attr_cur;
7241 
7242  for (db_attr_cur = db_attrs; db_attr_cur != NULL; db_attr_cur = db_attribute_next (db_attr_cur))
7243  {
7244  attr_cur = (NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *) malloc (sizeof (NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO));
7245  if (attr_cur == NULL)
7246  {
7247  goto exit_on_error;
7248  }
7249 
7250  attr_cur->next = NULL;
7251  attr_cur->name = (char *) db_attribute_name (db_attr_cur);
7252  attr_cur->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (db_attribute_type (db_attr_cur));
7253  attr_cur->meta_class = (db_attribute_is_shared (db_attr_cur) ? PT_SHARED : PT_NORMAL);
7254 
7255  if (attr_head == NULL)
7256  {
7257  attr_head = attr_cur;
7258  attr_tail = attr_cur;
7259  }
7260  else
7261  {
7262  attr_tail->next = attr_cur;
7263  attr_tail = attr_cur;
7264  }
7265  }
7266 
7267  *attrs_p = attr_head;
7268  return NO_ERROR;
7269 
7270 exit_on_error:
7271  free_natural_join_attrs (attr_head);
7272  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
7273 }
7274 
7275 /*
7276  * get_natural_join_attrs_from_pt_spec () - Get all attributes from a pt_spec
7277  * node that indicates an table or a subquery.
7278  * return:
7279  * parser(in):
7280  * node(in):
7281  */
7282 static NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *
7283 get_natural_join_attrs_from_pt_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
7284 {
7285  DB_OBJECT *cls;
7286  DB_ATTRIBUTE *db_attrs;
7287  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *natural_join_attrs;
7288  PT_NODE *derived_table;
7289  PT_NODE *subquery_attrs_list;
7290 
7291  assert (node != NULL && node->node_type == PT_SPEC);
7292 
7293  cls = NULL;
7294  db_attrs = NULL;
7295  natural_join_attrs = NULL;
7296 
7297  if (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (node))
7298  {
7299  /* This is a table. */
7300  cls = node->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object;
7301  if (cls == NULL)
7302  {
7303  return NULL;
7304  }
7305 
7306  db_attrs = db_get_attributes (cls);
7307  if (db_attrs == NULL)
7308  {
7309  return NULL;
7310  }
7311 
7312  if (generate_natural_join_attrs_from_db_attrs (db_attrs, &natural_join_attrs) != NO_ERROR)
7313  {
7314  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7315  goto exit_on_error;
7316  }
7317  }
7318  else if (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (node) || PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (node))
7319  {
7320  /* This is a subquery or a CTE. */
7321  if (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (node) && node->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY)
7322  {
7323  derived_table = node->info.spec.derived_table;
7324 
7325  if (node->info.spec.as_attr_list != NULL)
7326  {
7327  subquery_attrs_list = node->info.spec.as_attr_list;
7328  }
7329  else if (derived_table->node_type == PT_SELECT)
7330  {
7331  subquery_attrs_list = derived_table->info.query.q.select.list;
7332  }
7333  else
7334  {
7335  subquery_attrs_list = NULL;
7336  }
7337  }
7338  else
7339  {
7340  subquery_attrs_list = node->info.spec.as_attr_list;
7341  }
7342 
7343  if (subquery_attrs_list == NULL)
7344  {
7345  return NULL;
7346  }
7347 
7348  if (generate_natural_join_attrs_from_subquery (subquery_attrs_list, &natural_join_attrs) != NO_ERROR)
7349  {
7350  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7351  goto exit_on_error;
7352  }
7353 
7354  }
7355  else
7356  {
7357  assert (false);
7358  }
7359 
7360  return natural_join_attrs;
7361 
7362 exit_on_error:
7363  return NULL;
7364 }
7365 
7366 /*
7367  * pt_create_pt_expr_equal_node () - The function creates the PT_expr
7368  * for natural join. The operator is " = ".
7369  * return:
7370  * parser(in):
7371  * arg1(in):
7372  * arg2(in):
7373  */
7374 static PT_NODE *
7375 pt_create_pt_expr_equal_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * arg1, PT_NODE * arg2)
7376 {
7377  PT_NODE *expr = NULL;
7378 
7379  expr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
7380  if (expr == NULL)
7381  {
7382  return NULL;
7383  }
7384 
7385  parser_init_node (expr);
7386  expr->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
7387  expr->info.expr.op = PT_EQ;
7388  expr->info.expr.arg1 = arg1;
7389  expr->info.expr.arg2 = arg2;
7390 
7391  return expr;
7392 }
7393 
7394 /*
7395  * pt_create_pt_name () - The function creates the PT_NAME name for natural
7396  * join. The pt_name node indicates an attribute in a table/subquery.
7397  * The spec indicates the table/subquery.
7398  * return:
7399  * parser(in):
7400  * spec(in):
7401  * attr(in):
7402  */
7403 static PT_NODE *
7404 pt_create_pt_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO * attr)
7405 {
7406  PT_NODE *name;
7407 
7408  assert (attr != NULL);
7409  assert (spec != NULL);
7410 
7411  name = parser_new_node (parser, PT_NAME);
7412  if (name == NULL)
7413  {
7414  return NULL;
7415  }
7416 
7417  parser_init_node (name);
7418  name->info.name.original = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, attr->name);
7419  name->type_enum = attr->type_enum;
7420  name->info.name.meta_class = attr->meta_class;
7421  if (PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (spec))
7422  {
7423  name->info.name.resolved = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original);
7424  }
7425  else if (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (spec))
7426  {
7427  PT_NODE *cte = spec->info.spec.cte_pointer->info.pointer.node;
7428  name->info.name.resolved = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, cte->info.cte.name->info.name.original);
7429  }
7430  else
7431  {
7432  assert (PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED (spec));
7433  }
7434 
7435  if (PT_IS_SPEC_REAL_TABLE (spec))
7436  {
7437  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (name, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
7438  }
7439 
7440  name->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
7441 
7442  return name;
7443 
7444 }
7445 
7446 /*
7447  * pt_create_pt_expr_and_node () - The function create the PT_expr for natural
7448  * join. The operator is AND.
7449  * return:
7450  * parser(in):
7451  * arg1(in):
7452  * arg2(in):
7453  */
7454 static PT_NODE *
7455 pt_create_pt_expr_and_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * arg1, PT_NODE * arg2)
7456 {
7457  PT_NODE *expr = NULL;
7458 
7459  expr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
7460  if (expr == NULL)
7461  {
7462  return NULL;
7463  }
7464 
7465  parser_init_node (expr);
7466  expr->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
7467  expr->info.expr.op = PT_AND;
7468  expr->info.expr.arg1 = arg1;
7469  expr->info.expr.arg2 = arg2;
7470 
7471  return expr;
7472 }
7473 
7474 /*
7475  * pt_resolve_natural_join_internal () - Resolve natural join into inner/outer join actually.
7476  * For t1 natural join t2, join_lhs is t1 and join_rhs is t2. The function adds on_cond
7477  * into t2. After the process, the join will become an inner/outer join.
7478  * return:
7479  * parser(in):
7480  * join_lhs(in):
7481  * join_rhs(in/out):
7482  */
7483 static void
7484 pt_resolve_natural_join_internal (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * join_lhs, PT_NODE * join_rhs)
7485 {
7486  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *lhs_attrs;
7487  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *rhs_attrs;
7488  NATURAL_JOIN_ATTR_INFO *lhs_attrs_cur, *rhs_attrs_cur;
7489  PT_NODE *on_cond_tail;
7490  PT_NODE *join_cond_expr;
7491  PT_NODE *join_cond_arg1;
7492  PT_NODE *join_cond_arg2;
7493  PT_NODE *on_cond_new;
7494 
7495  assert (join_lhs != NULL);
7496  assert (join_rhs != NULL);
7497 
7498  on_cond_tail = join_rhs->info.spec.on_cond;
7499 
7500  lhs_attrs = get_natural_join_attrs_from_pt_spec (parser, join_lhs);
7501  rhs_attrs = get_natural_join_attrs_from_pt_spec (parser, join_rhs);
7502 
7503  for (lhs_attrs_cur = lhs_attrs; lhs_attrs_cur != NULL; lhs_attrs_cur = lhs_attrs_cur->next)
7504  {
7505  for (rhs_attrs_cur = rhs_attrs; rhs_attrs_cur; rhs_attrs_cur = rhs_attrs_cur->next)
7506  {
7507  if (!natural_join_equal_attr (lhs_attrs_cur, rhs_attrs_cur))
7508  {
7509  continue;
7510  }
7511 
7512  /* step 1: we create pt_name for the first attribute */
7513  join_cond_arg1 = pt_create_pt_name (parser, join_lhs, lhs_attrs_cur);
7514  if (join_cond_arg1 == NULL)
7515  {
7516  PT_ERRORm (parser, join_rhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7517  goto exit_on_create_node_error;
7518  }
7519 
7520  /* step 2: we create pt_name for the second attribute */
7521  join_cond_arg2 = pt_create_pt_name (parser, join_rhs, rhs_attrs_cur);
7522  if (join_cond_arg2 == NULL)
7523  {
7524  PT_ERRORm (parser, join_rhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7525  goto exit_on_create_node_error;
7526  }
7527 
7528  /* step 3: we create the equal pt_expr node. like "join_cond_arg1 = join_cond_arg2" */
7529  join_cond_expr = pt_create_pt_expr_equal_node (parser, join_cond_arg1, join_cond_arg2);
7530  if (join_cond_expr == NULL)
7531  {
7532  PT_ERRORm (parser, join_rhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7533  goto exit_on_create_node_error;
7534  }
7535 
7536  /*
7537  * step4: If there is no on_cond, the new expr we created will be on_cond.
7538  * If not, it means there is old on_conds. So we will create a new expr
7539  * like "(old on_cond) and (new on_cond)".
7540  */
7541  if (on_cond_tail == NULL)
7542  {
7543  on_cond_tail = join_cond_expr;
7544  }
7545  else
7546  {
7547  on_cond_new = pt_create_pt_expr_and_node (parser, on_cond_tail, join_cond_expr);
7548  if (on_cond_new == NULL)
7549  {
7550  PT_ERRORm (parser, join_rhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7551  goto exit_on_create_node_error;
7552  }
7553 
7554  on_cond_tail = on_cond_new;
7555  }
7556  }
7557  }
7558 
7559  join_rhs->info.spec.on_cond = on_cond_tail;
7560 
7561  if (lhs_attrs != NULL)
7562  {
7563  free_natural_join_attrs (lhs_attrs);
7564  }
7565 
7566  if (rhs_attrs != NULL)
7567  {
7568  free_natural_join_attrs (rhs_attrs);
7569  }
7570 
7571  return;
7572 
7573 exit_on_create_node_error:
7574  if (lhs_attrs != NULL)
7575  {
7576  free_natural_join_attrs (lhs_attrs);
7577  }
7578 
7579  if (rhs_attrs != NULL)
7580  {
7581  free_natural_join_attrs (rhs_attrs);
7582  }
7583 
7584  return;
7585 }
7586 
7587 /*
7588  * pt_resolve_natural_join () - Resolve natural join into inner/outer join.
7589  * return:
7590  * parser(in):
7591  * node(in/out):
7592  * chk_parent(in):
7593  * continue_walk(in/out):
7594  */
7595 static PT_NODE *
7596 pt_resolve_natural_join (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *chk_parent, int *continue_walk)
7597 {
7598  PT_NODE *join_lhs, *join_rhs;
7599 
7600  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
7601 
7602  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_SPEC)
7603  {
7604  return node;
7605  }
7606 
7607  join_lhs = node;
7608  join_rhs = node->next;
7609 
7610  /* there is a natural join */
7611  if (join_rhs != NULL && join_rhs->node_type == PT_SPEC && join_rhs->info.spec.natural == true)
7612  {
7613  pt_resolve_natural_join_internal (parser, join_lhs, join_rhs);
7614  }
7615 
7616  return node;
7617 }
7618 
7619 /*
7620  * is_pt_name_in_group_having () -
7621  * return:
7622  * node(in):
7623  */
7624 static bool
7625 is_pt_name_in_group_having (PT_NODE * node)
7626 {
7627  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_NAME || node->etc == NULL)
7628  {
7629  return false;
7630  }
7631 
7632  if (intl_identifier_casecmp ((char *) node->etc, CPTR_PT_NAME_IN_GROUP_HAVING) == 0)
7633  {
7634  return true;
7635  }
7636 
7637  return false;
7638 }
7639 
7640 /*
7641  * pt_mark_pt_name () -
7642  * return:
7643  * parser(in):
7644  * node(in/out):
7645  * chk_parent(in):
7646  * continue_walk(in/out):
7647  */
7648 static PT_NODE *
7649 pt_mark_pt_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *chk_parent, int *continue_walk)
7650 {
7651  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
7652 
7653  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_NAME)
7654  {
7655  return node;
7656  }
7657  node->etc = (void *) pt_append_string (parser, NULL, CPTR_PT_NAME_IN_GROUP_HAVING);
7658 
7659  return node;
7660 }
7661 
7662 /*
7663  * pt_mark_group_having_pt_name () - Mark the PT_NAME in group by / having.
7664  * return:
7665  * parser(in):
7666  * node(in/out):
7667  * chk_parent(in):
7668  * continue_walk(in/out):
7669  */
7670 static PT_NODE *
7671 pt_mark_group_having_pt_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *chk_parent, int *continue_walk)
7672 {
7673  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
7674 
7675  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_SELECT)
7676  {
7677  return node;
7678  }
7679 
7680  if (node->info.query.q.select.group_by != NULL)
7681  {
7682  node->info.query.q.select.group_by =
7683  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.group_by, pt_mark_pt_name, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7684  }
7685 
7686  if (node->info.query.q.select.having != NULL)
7687  {
7688  node->info.query.q.select.having =
7689  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.having, pt_mark_pt_name, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7690  }
7691 
7692  return node;
7693 }

7695 /*
7696  * pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_sort_spec () -
7697  * return:
7698  * parser(in):
7699  * node(in/out):
7700  * select_list(in):
7701  */
7702 static void
7703 pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_sort_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_NODE * select_list)
7704 {
7705  if (node != NULL && node->node_type == PT_SORT_SPEC)
7706  {
7707  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_internal (parser, &(node->info.sort_spec.expr), select_list);
7708  }
7709 }
