7711 /*
7712  * pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_name () -
7713  * return:
7714  * parser(in):
7715  * node_p(in/out):
7716  * select_list(in):
7717  */
7718 static void
7719 pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE ** node_p, PT_NODE * select_list)
7720 {
7721  PT_NODE *col;
7722  char *n_str;
7723  PT_NODE *node;
7724 
7725  assert (node_p != NULL);
7726 
7727  node = *node_p;
7728 
7729  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_NAME)
7730  {
7731  return;
7732  }
7733 
7734  /* It have been resolved. */
7735  if (node->info.name.resolved != NULL)
7736  {
7737  return;
7738  }
7739 
7740  n_str = (char *) node->info.name.original;
7741 
7742  for (col = select_list; col != NULL; col = col->next)
7743  {
7744  if (col->alias_print != NULL && intl_identifier_casecmp (n_str, col->alias_print) == 0)
7745  {
7746  parser_free_node (parser, *node_p);
7747  *node_p = parser_copy_tree (parser, col);
7748  if ((*node_p) != NULL)
7749  {
7750  (*node_p)->next = NULL;
7751  }
7752  break;
7753  }
7754  }
7755 
7756  /* We can not resolve the pt_name. */
7757  if (col == NULL)
7758  {
7759  PT_ERRORmf (parser, (*node_p), MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED,
7760  pt_short_print (parser, (*node_p)));
7761  }
7762 }
7763 
7764 /*
7765  * pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_expr () -
7766  * return:
7767  * parser(in):
7768  * node(in/out):
7769  * select_list(in):
7770  */
7771 static void
7772 pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_NODE * select_list)
7773 {
7774  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_EXPR)
7775  {
7776  return;
7777  }
7778 
7779  /* Resolve arg1 */
7780  if (node->info.expr.arg1 != NULL && node->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_NAME)
7781  {
7782  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_name (parser, &node->info.expr.arg1, select_list);
7783  }
7784  else if (node->info.expr.arg1 != NULL && node->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
7785  {
7786  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_expr (parser, node->info.expr.arg1, select_list);
7787  }
7788  else
7789  {
7790 
7791  }
7792 
7793  /* Resolve arg2 */
7794  if (node->info.expr.arg2 != NULL && node->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_NAME)
7795  {
7796  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_name (parser, &node->info.expr.arg2, select_list);
7797  }
7798  else if (node->info.expr.arg2 != NULL && node->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
7799  {
7800  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_expr (parser, node->info.expr.arg2, select_list);
7801  }
7802  else
7803  {
7804 
7805  }
7806 
7807  /* Resolve arg3 */
7808  if (node->info.expr.arg3 != NULL && node->info.expr.arg3->node_type == PT_NAME)
7809  {
7810  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_name (parser, &node->info.expr.arg3, select_list);
7811  }
7812  else if (node->info.expr.arg3 != NULL && node->info.expr.arg3->node_type == PT_EXPR)
7813  {
7814  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_expr (parser, node->info.expr.arg3, select_list);
7815  }
7816  else
7817  {
7818 
7819  }
7820 }
7821 
7822 /*
7823  * pt_resolve_group_having_alias_internal () - Rosolve alias name in groupby and having clause.
7824  * return:
7825  * parser(in):
7826  * node_p(in/out):
7827  * select_list(in):
7828  */
7829 static void
7830 pt_resolve_group_having_alias_internal (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE ** node_p, PT_NODE * select_list)
7831 {
7832  assert (node_p != NULL);
7833  assert ((*node_p) != NULL);
7834 
7835  switch ((*node_p)->node_type)
7836  {
7837  case PT_NAME:
7838  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_name (parser, node_p, select_list);
7839  break;
7840  case PT_EXPR:
7841  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_expr (parser, *node_p, select_list);
7842  break;
7843  case PT_SORT_SPEC:
7844  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_pt_sort_spec (parser, *node_p, select_list);
7845  break;
7846  default:
7847  return;
7848  }
7849  return;
7850 }
7851 
7852 /*
7853  * pt_resolve_group_having_alias () - Resolve alias name in groupby and having clause. We
7854  * resolve groupby/having alias after bind_name, it means when the alias name is same
7855  * with table attribute, we choose table attribute firstly.
7856  * return:
7857  * parser(in):
7858  * node(in/out):
7859  * chk_parent(in):
7860  * continue_walk(in/out):
7861  */
7862 static PT_NODE *
7863 pt_resolve_group_having_alias (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *chk_parent, int *continue_walk)
7864 {
7865  PT_NODE *pt_cur;
7866 
7867  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
7868 
7869  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_SELECT)
7870  {
7871  return node;
7872  }
7873 
7874  /* support for alias in GROUP BY */
7875  pt_cur = node->info.query.q.select.group_by;
7876  while (pt_cur != NULL)
7877  {
7878  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_internal (parser, &pt_cur, node->info.query.q.select.list);
7879  pt_cur = pt_cur->next;
7880  }
7881 
7882  /* support for alias in HAVING */
7883  pt_cur = node->info.query.q.select.having;
7884  while (pt_cur != NULL)
7885  {
7886  pt_resolve_group_having_alias_internal (parser, &pt_cur, node->info.query.q.select.list);
7887  pt_cur = pt_cur->next;
7888  }
7889  return node;
7890 }
7891 
7892 /*
7893  * pt_resolve_names () -
7894  * return:
7895  * parser(in):
7896  * statement(in):
7897  * sc_info(in):
7898  */
7899 PT_NODE *
7900 pt_resolve_names (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO * sc_info)
7901 {
7902  PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG bind_arg;
7903  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO info;
7904 
7905  bind_arg.scopes = NULL;
7906  bind_arg.spec_frames = NULL;
7907  bind_arg.sc_info = sc_info;
7908 
7909  assert (sc_info != NULL);
7910 
7911  if (statement != NULL && statement->node_type == PT_MERGE && statement->info.merge.into != NULL)
7912  {
7913  /* chain merge specs for flat name resolving */
7914  statement->info.merge.into->next = statement->info.merge.using_clause;
7915  statement->info.merge.using_clause = NULL;
7916  }
7917 
7918  /* Replace each Entity Spec with an Equivalent flat list */
7919  info.spec_parent = NULL;
7920  info.for_update = false;
7921  statement = parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, pt_flat_spec_pre, &info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
7922 
7923  if (statement != NULL && statement->node_type == PT_MERGE && statement->info.merge.into != NULL)
7924  {
7925  /* unchain merge specs */
7926  statement->info.merge.using_clause = statement->info.merge.into->next;
7927  statement->info.merge.into->next = NULL;
7928  }
7929 
7930  /* resolve names in search conditions, assignments, and assignations */
7931  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
7932  {
7933  PT_NODE *idx_name = NULL;
7934  if (statement->node_type == PT_CREATE_INDEX || statement->node_type == PT_ALTER_INDEX
7935  || statement->node_type == PT_DROP_INDEX)
7936  {
7937  /* backup the name of the index because it is not part of the table spec yet */
7938  idx_name = statement->info.index.index_name;
7939  statement->info.index.index_name = NULL;
7940  }
7941 
7942  /* Before pt_bind_name, we mark PT_NAME in group by/ having. */
7943  statement = parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, pt_mark_group_having_pt_name, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7944  if (pt_has_error (parser))
7945  {
7946  return NULL;
7947  }
7948 
7949  statement = parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, pt_bind_names, &bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, &bind_arg);
7950  if (pt_has_error (parser))
7951  {
7952  return NULL;
7953  }
7954 
7955  if (statement
7956  && (statement->node_type == PT_CREATE_INDEX || statement->node_type == PT_ALTER_INDEX
7957  || statement->node_type == PT_DROP_INDEX))
7958  {
7959  statement->info.index.index_name = idx_name;
7960  }
7961 
7962  /* Resolve alias in group by/having. */
7963  statement = parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, pt_resolve_group_having_alias, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7964  if (pt_has_error (parser))
7965  {
7966  return NULL;
7967  }
7968 
7969  /*
7970  * The process converts natural join to inner/outer join.
7971  * The on_cond is added there.
7972  */
7973  statement = parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, NULL, NULL, pt_resolve_natural_join, NULL);
7974  if (pt_has_error (parser))
7975  {
7976  return NULL;
7977  }
7978  }
7979 
7980  /* Flag specs from FOR UPDATE clause with PT_SPEC_FLAG_FOR_UPDATE_CLAUSE and clear the for_update list. From now on
7981  * the specs from FOR UPDATE clause can be determined using this flag together with PT_SELECT_INFO_FOR_UPDATE flag */
7982  if (statement != NULL && statement->node_type == PT_SELECT
7983  && PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (statement, PT_SELECT_INFO_FOR_UPDATE))
7984  {
7985  PT_NODE *node = statement->info.query.q.select.for_update;
7986  PT_NODE *spec = NULL;
7987 
7988  if (statement->info.query.q.select.for_update != NULL)
7989  {
7990  /* Flag only the specified specs */
7991  for (; node != NULL; node = node->next)
7992  {
7993  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, statement->info.query.q.select.from, node);
7994  if (spec == NULL)
7995  {
7996  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_EXIST,
7997  node->info.name.original);
7998  return NULL;
7999  }
8000  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_FOR_UPDATE_CLAUSE);
8001  }
8002  parser_free_tree (parser, statement->info.query.q.select.for_update);
8003  statement->info.query.q.select.for_update = NULL;
8004  }
8005  else
8006  {
8007  /* Flag all specs */
8008  for (spec = statement->info.query.q.select.from; spec != NULL; spec = spec->next)
8009  {
8010  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_FOR_UPDATE_CLAUSE);
8011  }
8012  }
8013  }
8014 
8015  return statement;
8016 }
8017 
8018 /* pt_resolve_spec_to_cte - search for matches of node spec in each CTE from cte_defs list
8019  *
8020  * return:
8021  * parser(in):
8022  * node(in/out):
8023  * arg(in): cte_defs ( only the CTEs that can be referenced )
8024  * continue_walk(in/out):
8025  */
8026 static PT_NODE *
8027 pt_resolve_spec_to_cte (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
8028 {
8029  PT_NODE *cte_defs = (PT_NODE *) arg;
8030  PT_NODE *cte = NULL;
8031 
8032  if (node == NULL)
8033  {
8034  assert (false);
8035  return NULL;
8036  }
8037 
8038  if (node->node_type != PT_SPEC || !PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (node))
8039  {
8040  /* not interested in non-entity-specs */
8041  return node;
8042  }
8043 
8044  for (cte = cte_defs; cte != NULL; cte = cte->next)
8045  {
8046  PT_NODE *cte_name = cte->info.cte.name;
8047  assert (cte_name != NULL);
8048 
8049  if (pt_name_equal (parser, cte_name, node->info.spec.entity_name))
8050  {
8051  node->info.spec.cte_name = node->info.spec.entity_name;
8052  node->info.spec.entity_name = NULL;
8053  node->info.spec.cte_pointer = pt_point (parser, cte);
8054  node->info.spec.cte_pointer->info.pointer.do_walk = false;
8055  break;
8056  }
8057  }
8058 
8059  return node;
8060 }
8061 
8062 /* pt_resolve_spec_to_cte_and_count - search for matches of spec in each CTE from cte_defs list
8063  * and sets node->etc as counter if found
8064  *
8065  * return:
8066  * parser(in):
8067  * node(in/out):
8068  * arg(in): cte_defs ( only the CTEs that can be referenced )
8069  * continue_walk(in/out):
8070  *
8071  * Note: Must be paired with pt_count_ctes_post to ensure node->etc cleanup
8072  */
8073 static PT_NODE *
8074 pt_resolve_spec_to_cte_and_count (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
8075 {
8076  if (node == NULL)
8077  {
8078  assert (false);
8079  return NULL;
8080  }
8081 
8082  /* we are interested only in entity-specs that are transformed into cte-specs after pt_resolve_spec_to_cte */
8083  if (node->node_type != PT_SPEC || !PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (node))
8084  {
8085  return node;
8086  }
8087 
8088  node = pt_resolve_spec_to_cte (parser, node, arg, continue_walk);
8089  if (node == NULL || !PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (node))
8090  {
8091  /* spec was not found | error occured */
8092  return node;
8093  }
8094 
8095  /* spec was transformed into a CTE pointer spec */
8096  assert (node->node_type == PT_SPEC && PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (node));
8097 
8098  /* set node->etc to the number of occurences (one) */
8099  node->etc = malloc (sizeof (char));
8100  *((char *) node->etc) = 1;
8101 
8102  return node;
8103 }
8104 
8105 /* pt_count_ctes_post () - increase counter with current node cte occurrences
8106 * return:
8107 * parser(in):
8108 * node(in): the node to check, leave node unchanged except of node->etc
8109 * arg(out): count of CTEs
8110 * continue_walk(in):
8111 */
8112 static PT_NODE *
8113 pt_count_ctes_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
8114 {
8115  int *cnt = (int *) arg;
8116 
8117  /* check if node is a CTE SPEC with node->etc set */
8118  if (node != NULL && node->node_type == PT_SPEC && PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (node) && pt_node_etc (node) != NULL)
8119  {
8120  /* increment cnt argument and free etc */
8121  assert (*((char *) pt_node_etc (node)) == 1);
8122  (*cnt)++;
8123 
8124  /* cte_matches counter is no longer needed; pt_resolve_spec_to_cte expects to clean it here */
8125  free (pt_node_etc (node));
8126  pt_null_etc (node);
8127  }
8128 
8129  return node;
8130 }
8131 
8132 /* pt_resolve_cte_specs () - resolves all CTEs involved in a query
8133 * return:
8134 * parser(in):
8135 * node(in):
8136 * arg(out):
8137 * continue_walk(in):
8138 */
8139 PT_NODE *
8140 pt_resolve_cte_specs (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
8141 {
8142  PT_NODE *cte_list, *with = NULL, *saved_with = NULL;
8143  PT_NODE **with_p;
8144  PT_NODE *curr_cte, *previous_cte;
8145  PT_NODE *saved_curr_cte_next;
8146  int nested_with_count = 0;
8147 
8148  assert (parser != NULL);
8149  assert (node != NULL);
8150 
8151  switch (node->node_type)
8152  {
8153  case PT_SELECT:
8154  case PT_UNION:
8155  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
8156  case PT_INTERSECTION:
8157  with = node->info.query.with;
8158  with_p = &node->info.query.with;
8159  break;
8160  case PT_UPDATE:
8161  with = node->info.update.with;
8162  with_p = &node->info.update.with;
8163  break;
8164  case PT_DELETE:
8165  with = node->info.delete_.with;
8166  with_p = &node->info.delete_.with;
8167  break;
8168 
8169  default:
8170  return node;
8171  }
8172 
8173  if (with == NULL)
8174  {
8175  /* nothing to resolve to */
8176  return node;
8177  }
8178 
8179  cte_list = with->info.with_clause.cte_definition_list;
8180  if (cte_list == NULL)
8181  {
8182  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "expecting cte definitions");
8183  return NULL;
8184  }
8185 
8186  /* check ambiguity in the names of CTEs */
8187  for (previous_cte = cte_list; previous_cte != NULL; previous_cte = previous_cte->next)
8188  {
8189  for (curr_cte = previous_cte->next; curr_cte != NULL; curr_cte = curr_cte->next)
8190  {
8191  if (pt_name_equal (parser, previous_cte->info.cte.name, curr_cte->info.cte.name))
8192  {
8193  /* ambiguity, two CTEs with the same name */
8194  PT_ERRORmf (parser, with, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CTE_NAME_AMBIGUITY,
8195  curr_cte->info.cte.name->info.name.original);
8196  return NULL;
8197  }
8198  }
8199  }
8200 
8201  /* check if there are nested WITHs */
8202  cte_list = parser_walk_tree (parser, cte_list, pt_count_with_clauses, &nested_with_count, NULL, NULL);
8203  if (nested_with_count > 0)
8204  {
8205  PT_ERRORm (parser, with, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NESTED_WITH);
8206  return NULL;
8207  }
8208 
8209  /* STEP 1: Check if CTE is recursive - find if CTE definition contains self references and resolve them */
8210  for (curr_cte = cte_list; curr_cte != NULL; curr_cte = curr_cte->next)
8211  {
8212  if ((curr_cte->info.cte.non_recursive_part->node_type == PT_UNION) && (!curr_cte->info.cte.recursive_part))
8213  {
8214  PT_NODE *recursive_part = curr_cte->info.cte.non_recursive_part->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
8215  PT_NODE *non_recursive_part = curr_cte->info.cte.non_recursive_part->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
8216  PT_MISC_TYPE all_distinct = curr_cte->info.cte.non_recursive_part->info.query.all_distinct;
8217  PT_NODE *from;
8218  int curr_cte_count = 0;
8219 
8220  if (recursive_part->node_type != PT_SELECT)
8221  {
8222  /* SELECT only */
8223  continue;
8224  }
8225 
8226  /* isolate curr_cte to prevent resolving next CTEs in current recursive part */
8227  saved_curr_cte_next = curr_cte->next;
8228  curr_cte->next = NULL;
8229 
8230  /* look for self references in recursive query FROM */
8231  for (from = recursive_part->info.query.q.select.from; from != NULL; from = from->next)
8232  {
8233  if (from->node_type == PT_SPEC && PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (from))
8234  {
8235  (void) pt_resolve_spec_to_cte (parser, from, curr_cte, NULL);
8236  if (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (from))
8237  {
8238  curr_cte_count++;
8239  }
8240  }
8241  }
8242 
8243  if (curr_cte_count == 0 && non_recursive_part->node_type == PT_SELECT)
8244  {
8245  /* no self references were found in arg2 from union; search in arg1 also, syntax allows this case */
8246  for (from = non_recursive_part->info.query.q.select.from; from != NULL; from = from->next)
8247  {
8248  if (from->node_type == PT_SPEC && PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY (from))
8249  {
8250  (void) pt_resolve_spec_to_cte (parser, from, curr_cte, NULL);
8251  if (PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (from))
8252  {
8253  curr_cte_count++;
8254  }
8255  }
8256  }
8257 
8258  if (curr_cte_count > 0)
8259  {
8260  /* curr_cte is recursive but it was found in non-recursive part; swap non-recursive, recursive */
8261  PT_NODE *tmp = non_recursive_part;
8262  non_recursive_part = recursive_part;
8263  recursive_part = tmp;
8264  }
8265  }
8266 
8267  if (curr_cte_count > 0)
8268  {
8269  curr_cte->info.cte.non_recursive_part = non_recursive_part;
8270  curr_cte->info.cte.recursive_part = recursive_part;
8271  curr_cte->info.cte.only_all = all_distinct;
8272  if (curr_cte->info.cte.only_all != PT_ALL)
8273  {
8274  PT_ERRORmf (parser, curr_cte, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INCORRECT_UNION_IN_CTE,
8275  curr_cte->info.cte.name->info.name.original);
8276  return NULL;
8277  }
8278  }
8279 
8280  /* check if there are any unresolved self references of the cte, it would be incorrect */
8281  curr_cte_count = 0;
8282  curr_cte = parser_walk_tree (parser, curr_cte, pt_resolve_spec_to_cte_and_count, curr_cte,
8283  pt_count_ctes_post, &curr_cte_count);
8284  if (curr_cte == NULL)
8285  {
8286  /* error in walk */
8287  return NULL;
8288  }
8289  if (curr_cte_count > 0)
8290  {
8291  PT_ERRORmf (parser, curr_cte, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INCORRECT_RECURSIVE_CTE,
8292  curr_cte->info.cte.name->info.name.original);
8293  return NULL;
8294  }
8295 
8296  /* restore next link */
8297  curr_cte->next = saved_curr_cte_next;
8298  }
8299 
8300  curr_cte->info.cte.non_recursive_part->info.query.is_subquery = PT_IS_CTE_NON_REC_SUBQUERY;
8301  if (curr_cte->info.cte.recursive_part)
8302  {
8303  assert (curr_cte->info.cte.recursive_part->node_type == PT_SELECT);
8304  curr_cte->info.cte.recursive_part->info.query.is_subquery = PT_IS_CTE_REC_SUBQUERY;
8305  }
8306  }
8307 
8308  /* STEP 2: Resolve CTEs references within CTEs */
8309  for (previous_cte = cte_list, curr_cte = previous_cte->next; curr_cte != NULL;
8310  previous_cte = previous_cte->next, curr_cte = curr_cte->next)
8311  {
8312  /* disconect curr_cte from the list of CTEs that can be referenced in curr_cte */
8313  previous_cte->next = NULL;
8314 
8315  /* avoid following next links in parser_walk_tree */
8316  saved_curr_cte_next = curr_cte->next;
8317  curr_cte->next = NULL;
8318 
8319  /* cte_list keeps only the CTEs that precede curr_cte; resolve their references in curr_cte */
8320  curr_cte = parser_walk_tree (parser, curr_cte, pt_resolve_spec_to_cte, cte_list, NULL, NULL);
8321  if (curr_cte == NULL)
8322  {
8323  /* we expect error to be set */
8324  return NULL;
8325  }
8326 
8327  /* reconnect list, previous->next was curr_cte */
8328  previous_cte->next = curr_cte;
8329 
8330  /* restore next node */
8331  curr_cte->next = saved_curr_cte_next;
8332  }
8333 
8334  /* STEP 3: Resolve CTEs in the actual query */
8335  saved_with = *with_p;
8336  *with_p = NULL;
8337  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_resolve_spec_to_cte, cte_list, NULL, NULL);
8338  *with_p = saved_with;
8339 
8340  /* all ok */
8341  return node;
8342 }
8343 
8344 /*
8345  * pt_copy_data_type_entity () -
8346  * return: A copy of the entity name represented by the data type
8347  * parser(in): parser environment
8348  * data_type(in): data type node
8349  */
8350 static PT_NODE *
8351 pt_copy_data_type_entity (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * data_type)
8352 {
8353  PT_NODE *entity = NULL;
8354  if (data_type->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE)
8355  {
8356  if (data_type->info.data_type.virt_object)
8357  {
8358  entity = pt_name (parser, db_get_class_name (data_type->info.data_type.virt_object));
8359  entity->info.name.db_object = data_type->info.data_type.virt_object;
8360  }
8361  else
8362  {
8363  entity = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, data_type->info.data_type.entity);
8364  }
8365  }
8366 
8367  return entity;
8368 }
8369 
8370 /*
8371  * pt_insert_entity() -
8372  * return: pointer to the entity spec, the parse tree is augmented with
8373  * the new entity spec if one is created.
8374  * parser(in): parser environment
8375  * path(in): expression that caused the generation of this entity_spec
8376  * prev_entity(in): the previous entity in the path expression
8377  * correlation_entity(in):
8378  */
8379 
8380 PT_NODE *
8381 pt_insert_entity (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * path, PT_NODE * prev_entity, PT_NODE * correlation_entity)
8382 {
8383  PT_NODE *entity = NULL;
8384  PT_NODE *res = NULL, *res1;
8385  PT_NODE *arg1;
8386  PT_NODE *arg1_name = NULL;
8387  PT_NODE *node;
8388 
8389  assert (path != NULL && prev_entity != NULL && path->node_type == PT_DOT_ && prev_entity->node_type == PT_SPEC);
8390 
8391  entity = pt_lookup_entity (parser, prev_entity->info.spec.path_entities, path);
8392  /* compute res */
8393  arg1 = path->info.dot.arg1;
8394  if ((arg1->node_type == PT_NAME) || (arg1->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL))
8395  {
8396  res = arg1->data_type;
8397  arg1_name = arg1; /* what about method calls with selectors? */
8398  res1 = NULL;
8399  }
8400  else
8401  {
8402  res = arg1->info.dot.arg2->data_type;
8403  arg1_name = arg1->info.dot.arg2;
8404  res1 = arg1->data_type;
8405  }
8406 
8407  if (!res || !(res->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE) || !res->info.data_type.entity)
8408  {
8409  /* if we have a path, it must be from a known entity list */
8410  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
8411  return NULL;
8412  }
8413 
8414  if (entity == NULL)
8415  {
8416  /* create new entity spec if we have a correlation spec, use it. Otherwise, make a new one */
8417  if (correlation_entity)
8418  {
8419  entity = parser_copy_tree (parser, correlation_entity);
8420  entity->info.spec.derived_table_type = (PT_MISC_TYPE) 0;
8421  entity->info.spec.meta_class = PT_PATH_INNER;
8422  parser_free_tree (parser, correlation_entity->info.spec.path_entities);
8423  correlation_entity->info.spec.path_entities = NULL;
8424  }
8425  else
8426  {
8427  if (!(entity = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SPEC)))
8428  {
8429  PT_ERROR (parser, path,
8430  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
8431  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY));
8432  return NULL;
8433  }
8434 
8435  /* use addr as entity_spec_id per convention */
8436  entity->info.spec.id = (UINTPTR) entity;
8437  entity->line_number = path->info.dot.arg2->line_number;
8438  entity->column_number = path->info.dot.arg2->column_number;
8439 
8440  /* mark if it is a pseudo entity for a method */
8441  if (arg1->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL)
8442  {
8443  entity->info.spec.flavor = PT_METHOD_ENTITY;
8444  }
8445 
8446  entity->info.spec.entity_name = pt_copy_data_type_entity (parser, res);
8447 
8448  if (entity->info.spec.entity_name)
8449  {
8450  entity->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
8451  entity->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_CLASS;
8452  entity->info.spec.only_all = PT_ALL;
8453  entity->info.spec.range_var = parser_copy_tree (parser, entity->info.spec.entity_name);
8454  entity->info.spec.range_var->info.name.resolved = NULL;
8455  entity->info.spec.flat_entity_list = pt_make_flat_list_from_data_types (parser, res, entity);
8456  }
8457 
8458  /* We need to resolve the data type list to the newly created spec. */
8459  for (node = res; node; node = node->next)
8460  {
8461  if (node->info.data_type.entity)
8462  {
8463  node->info.data_type.entity->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
8464  }
8465  }
8466 
8467  /* The type of the DOT node is the same as the type of arg2 and so it must be resolved as well. */
8468  for (node = res1; node; node = node->next)
8469  {
8470  if (node->info.data_type.entity)
8471  {
8472  node->info.data_type.entity->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
8473  }
8474  }
8475  }
8476 
8477  /* add entity into path_entities list */
8478  entity->next = prev_entity->info.spec.path_entities;
8479  prev_entity->info.spec.path_entities = entity;
8480  entity = mq_regenerate_if_ambiguous (parser, entity, entity, entity);
8481  /* add the implicit conjunct */
8482  (void) pt_insert_conjunct (parser, path, entity);
8483  }
8484  if (correlation_entity && entity->info.spec.id != correlation_entity->info.spec.id)
8485  {
8486  const char *root = ""; /* safety net */
8487  if (arg1_name && arg1_name->node_type == PT_NAME)
8488  {
8489  root = arg1_name->info.name.original;
8490  }
8491 
8492  PT_ERRORmf3 (parser, path, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INCONSISTENT_PATH,
8493  pt_short_print (parser, path), pt_short_print (parser, correlation_entity->info.spec.range_var),
8494  root);
8495  }
8496 
8497  /* Make sure the arg2 points to the correct entity */
8498  path->info.dot.arg2->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
8499  path->info.dot.arg2->info.name.meta_class = PT_NORMAL;
8500  return entity;
8501 }
8502 
8503 
8504 /*
8505  * pt_insert_conjunct() -
8506  * return: parse tree that is augmented with the new conjunct
8507  * parser(in): parser environment
8508  * path_dot(in): path expression that caused this implicit conjunct
8509  * prev_entity(in): the previous entity in the path expression on which
8510  * we'll hang the new conjunct
8511  */
8512 
8513 static PT_NODE *
8514 pt_insert_conjunct (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * path_dot, PT_NODE * prev_entity)
8515 {
8516  PT_NODE *conjunct;
8517  PT_NODE *arg1;
8518  PT_NODE *conj_name;
8519  PT_NODE *conj_res = NULL;
8520 
8521  assert (path_dot != NULL && path_dot->node_type == PT_DOT_ && prev_entity != NULL
8522  && prev_entity->node_type == PT_SPEC);
8523 
8524  arg1 = path_dot->info.dot.arg1;
8525  if ((arg1->node_type == PT_NAME) || (arg1->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL))
8526  {
8527  conj_name = arg1;
8528  }
8529  else
8530  {
8531  conj_name = arg1->info.dot.arg2;
8532  /* comput conj_res to get exposed name from class data type of arg1 */
8533  arg1 = arg1->info.dot.arg1;
8534  if ((arg1->node_type == PT_NAME) || (arg1->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL))
8535  {
8536  conj_res = arg1->data_type;
8537  }
8538  else
8539  {
8540  conj_res = arg1->info.dot.arg2->data_type;
8541  }
8542  if (conj_res)
8543  {
8544  conj_res = conj_res->info.data_type.entity;
8545  }
8546  }
8547 
8548  /* create new conjunct */
8549  if (!(conjunct = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR)))
8550  {
8551  PT_ERROR (parser, path_dot,
8552  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY));
8553  return NULL;
8554  }
8555  conjunct->info.expr.op = PT_EQ;
8556  conjunct->info.expr.arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, conj_name);
8557  if (conjunct->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
8558  {
8559  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
8560  return NULL;
8561  }
8562 
8563  if (conj_name->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL)
8564  {
8565  conjunct->info.expr.arg1->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id = 0;
8566  }
8567  if (conj_res)
8568  {
8569  conjunct->info.expr.arg1->info.name.resolved = conj_res->info.name.original;
8570  }
8571 
8572  conjunct->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, prev_entity->info.spec.flat_entity_list);
8573  if (conjunct->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
8574  {
8575  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
8576  return NULL;
8577  }
8578 
8579  conjunct->info.expr.arg2->info.name.resolved = conjunct->info.expr.arg2->info.name.original;
8580  conjunct->info.expr.arg2->info.name.original = "";
8581  conjunct->info.expr.arg2->info.name.meta_class = PT_OID_ATTR;
8582  conjunct->info.expr.arg2->info.name.db_object = NULL;
8583  conjunct->info.expr.arg2->type_enum = conjunct->info.expr.arg1->type_enum;
8584  conjunct->info.expr.arg2->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, conjunct->info.expr.arg1->data_type);
8585  conjunct->line_number = path_dot->line_number;
8586  conjunct->column_number = path_dot->column_number;
8587  /* add conjunct into path_conjuncts list */
8588  conjunct->next = prev_entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts;
8589  prev_entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts = conjunct;
8590  return conjunct;
8591 } /* pt_insert_conjunct */
8592 
8593 
8594 /*
8595  * pt_lookup_entity () -
8596  * return: entity we are looking for
8597  * parser(in):
8598  * path_entities(in): entity list to look for entity
8599  * expr(in):
8600  */
8601 static PT_NODE *
8602 pt_lookup_entity (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * path_entities, PT_NODE * expr)
8603 {
8604  PT_NODE *entity;
8605  int found = false;
8606  PT_NODE *arg1_of_conj;
8607  const char *name = NULL, *cname;
8608 
8609  for (entity = path_entities; (entity != NULL && !found);)
8610  { /* do nothing during increment step */
8611 
8612  arg1_of_conj = entity->info.spec.path_conjuncts->info.expr.arg1;
8613  if (expr->info.dot.arg1->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL)
8614  {
8615  return NULL;
8616  }
8617  else
8618  {
8619  if (expr->info.dot.arg1->node_type == PT_DOT_)
8620  {
8621  name = expr->info.dot.arg1->info.dot.arg2->info.name.original;
8622  }
8623  else if (expr->info.dot.arg1->node_type == PT_NAME)
8624  {
8625  name = expr->info.dot.arg1->info.name.original;
8626  }
8627 
8628  if (arg1_of_conj->node_type == PT_NAME)
8629  {
8630  cname = arg1_of_conj->info.name.original;
8631  if (name != NULL && intl_identifier_casecmp (name, cname) == 0)
8632  {
8633  found = true;
8634  }
8635  }
8636  }
8637 
8638  if (!found)
8639  {
8640  entity = entity->next;
8641  }
8642  }
8643 
8644  return entity;
8645 }
8646 
8647 
8648 
8649 /*
8650  * pt_resolve_object () - gets the object to update either from a host var
8651  * or from a parameter. Once it has the object it creates an entity for
8652  * the object
8653  * return: none
8654  * parser(in):
8655  * node(in): an PT_UPDATE_INFO node representing an UPDATE OBJECT.. statement
8656  */
8657 void
8658 pt_resolve_object (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8659 {
8660  DB_VALUE *val = NULL;
8661  PT_NODE *entity;
8662  DB_OBJECT *class_op = NULL;
8663  PT_NODE *obj_param = node->info.update.object_parameter;
8664  assert (obj_param != NULL);
8665  if (obj_param->node_type == PT_NAME)
8666  {
8667  if (obj_param->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER)
8668  {
8669  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
8670  return;
8671  }
8672 
8673  /* look it up as an interpreter parameter reference */
8674  val = pt_find_value_of_label (obj_param->info.name.original);
8675  if (!val) /* parameter not found */
8676  {
8677  PT_ERRORmf (parser, obj_param, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED,
8678  obj_param->info.name.original);
8679  return;
8680  }
8681  }
8682  else if (obj_param->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR)
8683  {
8684  val = pt_value_to_db (parser, obj_param);
8685  }
8686 
8687  if (val == NULL) /* parameter not found */
8688  {
8689  PT_ERRORm (parser, obj_param, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNDEFINED_ARGUMENT);
8690  return;
8691  }
8692 
8693  if (DB_VALUE_TYPE (val) != DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
8694  {
8695  PT_ERRORm (parser, obj_param, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ARG_IS_NOT_AN_OBJECT);
8696  return;
8697  }
8698  node->info.update.object = db_get_object (val);
8699  class_op = db_get_class (node->info.update.object);
8700  if (class_op == NULL)
8701  {
8702  PT_ERRORm (parser, obj_param, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNDEFINED_ARGUMENT);
8703  return;
8704  }
8705 
8706  /* create an entity */
8707  entity = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SPEC);
8708  if (entity == NULL)
8709  {
8710  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
8711  return;
8712  }
8713 
8714  entity->info.spec.id = (UINTPTR) entity;
8715  entity->line_number = node->line_number;
8716  entity->column_number = node->column_number;
8717  entity->info.spec.entity_name = parser_new_node (parser, PT_NAME);
8718  if (entity->info.spec.entity_name == NULL)
8719  {
8720  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
8721  return;
8722  }
8723 
8724  entity->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
8725  entity->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_CLASS;
8726  entity->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original = db_get_class_name (class_op);
8727  entity->info.spec.only_all = PT_ONLY;
8728  entity->info.spec.range_var = parser_copy_tree (parser, entity->info.spec.entity_name);
8729  if (entity->info.spec.range_var == NULL)
8730  {
8731  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
8732  return;
8733  }
8734 
8735  entity->info.spec.range_var->info.name.resolved = NULL;
8736  node->info.update.spec = entity;
8737 }
8738 
8739 
8740 /*
8741  * pt_resolve_method_type () - resolves the return type of the method call
8742  * and creates a data_type for it if it is needed
8743  * return:
8744  * parser(in):
8745  * node(in): an PT_METHOD_CALL node
8746  */
8747 static bool
8748 pt_resolve_method_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8749 {
8750  PT_NODE *target;
8751  const char *method_name;
8752  DB_OBJECT *class_op;
8753  DB_METHOD *method = NULL;
8754  DB_DOMAIN *dom = NULL;
8755  if ((!node->info.method_call.method_name) || (!(target = node->info.method_call.on_call_target))
8756  || (!target->data_type) || (!target->data_type->info.data_type.entity)
8757  || (!(class_op = target->data_type->info.data_type.entity->info.name.db_object)))
8758  {
8759  return false; /* not a method */
8760  }
8761  method_name = node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original;
8762  method = NULL;
8763  method = db_get_method (class_op, method_name);
8764  if (method == NULL)
8765  {
8766  /* need to check if it is a class method */
8767  if (er_errid () == ER_OBJ_INVALID_METHOD)
8768  {
8769  er_clear ();
8770  }
8771  method = db_get_class_method (class_op, method_name);
8772  if (method == NULL)
8773  {
8774  return false; /* not a method */
8775  }
8776  node->info.method_call.class_or_inst = PT_IS_CLASS_MTHD;
8777  }
8778  else
8779  {
8780  node->info.method_call.class_or_inst = PT_IS_INST_MTHD;
8781  }
8782 
8783  /* look up the domain of the method's return type */
8784  if ((dom = db_method_arg_domain (method, 0)) == NULL)
8785  {
8786  /* only give error if it is a method expression */
8787  if (node->info.method_call.call_or_expr != PT_IS_CALL_STMT)
8788  {
8789  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_NOT_TYPED, method_name);
8790  }
8791  return false;
8792  }
8793 
8794  node->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (dom));
8795  switch (node->type_enum)
8796  {
8797  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
8798  case PT_TYPE_SET:
8799  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
8800  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
8801  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
8802  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
8803  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
8804  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
8805  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
8806  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
8807  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
8808  node->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, dom);
8809  break;
8810  default:
8811  break;
8812  }
8813 
8814  /* finally resolve method id */
8815  node->info.method_call.method_id = (UINTPTR) node;
8816  return true;
8817 } /* pt_resolve_method_type */
8818 
8819 
8820 
8821 /*
8822  * pt_make_method_call () - determines if the function call is really a
8823  * method call and if so, creates a PT_METHOD_CALL to replace the node
8824  * resolves the method call
8825  * return:
8826  * parser(in):
8827  * node(in): an PT_FUNCTION node that may really be a method call
8828  * bind_arg(in):
8829  */
8830 static PT_NODE *
8831 pt_make_method_call (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg)
8832 {
8833  PT_NODE *new_node;
8834  int error = NO_ERROR;
8835 
8836  /* initialize the new node with the corresponding fields from the PT_FUNCTION node. */
8837  new_node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_METHOD_CALL);
8838  if (new_node == NULL)
8839  {
8840  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
8841  return NULL;
8842  }
8843 
8844  new_node->info.method_call.method_name = parser_new_node (parser, PT_NAME);
8845  if (new_node->info.method_call.method_name == NULL)
8846  {
8847  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
8848  return NULL;
8849  }
8850 
8851  PT_NODE_COPY_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (new_node, node);
8852 
8853  new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original = node->info.function.generic_name;
8854 
8855  new_node->info.method_call.arg_list = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, node->info.function.arg_list);
8856 
8857  new_node->info.method_call.call_or_expr = PT_IS_MTHD_EXPR;
8858 
8859  if (jsp_is_exist_stored_procedure (new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original))
8860  {
8861  TP_DOMAIN *d = NULL;
8862 
8863  new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id = (UINTPTR) new_node->info.method_call.method_name;
8864 
8865  new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_METHOD;
8866 
8867  parser_walk_leaves (parser, new_node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
8868 
8869  /* returns either error or DB_TYPE... */
8870  error = jsp_get_return_type (new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original);
8871  if (error < 0)
8872  {
8873  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "jsp_get_return_type");
8874  return NULL;
8875  }
8876  new_node->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum ((DB_TYPE) error);
8877 
8878  d = pt_type_enum_to_db_domain (new_node->type_enum);
8879  d = tp_domain_cache (d);
8880  new_node->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, d);
8881 
8882  new_node->info.method_call.method_id = (UINTPTR) new_node;
8883 
8884  return new_node;
8885  }
8886  else
8887  {
8888  /* The first argument (which must be present), is the target of the method. Move it to the on_call_target. */
8889  if (!new_node->info.method_call.arg_list)
8890  {
8891  return node; /* return the function since it is not a method */
8892  }
8893  new_node->info.method_call.on_call_target = new_node->info.method_call.arg_list;
8894  new_node->info.method_call.arg_list = new_node->info.method_call.arg_list->next;
8895  new_node->info.method_call.on_call_target->next = NULL;
8896 
8897  /* make method name look resolved */
8898  new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id = (UINTPTR) new_node->info.method_call.method_name;
8899  new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.meta_class = PT_METHOD;
8900 
8901  /* bind the names in the method arguments and target, their scope will be the same as the method node's scope */
8902  parser_walk_leaves (parser, new_node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
8903 
8904  /* find the type of the method here */
8905  if (!pt_resolve_method_type (parser, new_node))
8906  {
8907  return node; /* not a method call */
8908  }
8909  else
8910  {
8911  /* if scopes is NULL we assume this came from an evaluate call and we treat it like a call statement, that
8912  * is, we don't resolve method name. */
8913  if (bind_arg->scopes == NULL)
8914  {
8915  return new_node;
8916  }
8917  /* resolve method name to entity where expansion will take place */
8918  if ((new_node->info.method_call.on_call_target->node_type == PT_NAME)
8919  && (new_node->info.method_call.on_call_target->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER))
8920  {
8921  PT_NODE *entity, *spec;
8922  entity = NULL; /* init */
8923  if (new_node->info.method_call.class_or_inst == PT_IS_CLASS_MTHD)
8924  {
8925  for (spec = bind_arg->spec_frames->extra_specs; spec != NULL; spec = spec->next)
8926  {
8927  if (spec->node_type == PT_SPEC
8928  && (spec->info.spec.id == new_node->info.method_call.on_call_target->info.name.spec_id))
8929  {
8930  entity = spec;
8931  break;
8932  }
8933  }
8934  }
8935  else
8936  {
8937  entity =
8938  pt_find_entity_in_scopes (parser, bind_arg->scopes,
8939  new_node->info.method_call.on_call_target->info.name.spec_id);
8940  }
8941  /* no entity found will be caught as an error later. Probably an unresolvable target. */
8942  if (entity)
8943  {
8944  new_node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
8945  }
8946  }
8947 
8948  return new_node; /* it is a method call */
8949  }
8950  }
8951 } /* pt_make_method_call */
8952 
8953 
8954 /*
8955  * pt_find_entity_in_scopes () - looks up an entity spec in a scope list
8956  * return:
8957  * parser(in):
8958  * scopes(in):
8959  * spec_id(in):
8960  */
8961 static PT_NODE *
8962 pt_find_entity_in_scopes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, SCOPES * scopes, UINTPTR spec_id)
8963 {
8964  SCOPES *scope;
8965  PT_NODE *entity = NULL;
8966  for (scope = scopes; scope != NULL; scope = scope->next)
8967  {
8968  entity = pt_find_entity (parser, scope->specs, spec_id);
8969  if (entity)
8970  {
8971  break;
8972  }
8973  }
8974 
8975  return entity;
8976 }
8977 
8978 /*
8979  * pt_find_outer_entity_in_scopes () -
8980  * return:
8981  * parser(in):
8982  * scopes(in):
8983  * spec_id(in):
8984  * scope_location(in):
8985  */
8986 static PT_NODE *
8987 pt_find_outer_entity_in_scopes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, SCOPES * scopes, UINTPTR spec_id, short *scope_location)
8988 {
8989  PT_NODE *spec, *temp;
8990  int location = 0;
8991  if (scopes == NULL)
8992  {
8993  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
8994  return NULL;
8995  }
8996 
8997 
8998  for (spec = scopes->specs; spec; spec = spec->next)
8999  {
9000  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
9001  {
9002  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
9003  return NULL;
9004  }
9005  if (spec->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE)
9006  {
9007  location = spec->info.spec.location;
9008  }
9009  if (spec->info.spec.id == spec_id)
9010  {
9011  for (temp = spec; temp && temp->info.spec.location < *scope_location; temp = temp->next)
9012  {
9013  if (temp->info.spec.join_type == PT_JOIN_NONE)
9014  location = temp->info.spec.location;
9015  }
9016  *scope_location = location;
9017  return spec;
9018  }
9019  }
9020 
9021  return NULL;
9022 }
9023 
9024 
9025 /*
9026  * pt_make_flat_list_from_data_types
9027  *
9028  * description: For each node in the res_list, this routine appends that node's
9029  * entity list onto the flat list that is being created. The resulting
9030  * flat list is then normalized (correct spec_id, etc.)
9031  */
9032 
9033 /*
9034  * pt_make_flat_list_from_data_types () - For each node in the res_list,
9035  * this routine appends that node's entity list onto the flat list that
9036  * is being created. The resulting flat list is then normalized
9037  * return:
9038  * parser(in):
9039  * res_list(in):
9040  * entity(in):
9041  */
9042 static PT_NODE *
9043 pt_make_flat_list_from_data_types (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * res_list, PT_NODE * entity)
9044 {
9045  PT_NODE *node, *temp, *flat_list = NULL;
9046  for (node = res_list; node; node = node->next)
9047  {
9048  temp = pt_copy_data_type_entity (parser, node);
9049  flat_list = pt_name_list_union (parser, flat_list, temp);
9050  }
9051 
9052  /* set all ids on flat list */
9053  for (node = flat_list; node != NULL; node = node->next)
9054  {
9055  node->info.name.spec_id = entity->info.spec.id;
9056  node->info.name.resolved = entity->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.original;
9057  if (PT_IS_SPEC_REAL_TABLE (entity))
9058  {
9059  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
9060  }
9061  node->info.name.meta_class = PT_CLASS;
9062  }
9063 
9064  return flat_list;
9065 }
9066 
9067 /*
9068  * pt_op_type_from_default_expr_type () - returns the corresponding PT_OP_TYPE
9069  * for the given default expression
9070  * return: a PT_OP_TYPE (the desired operation)
9071  * expr_type(in): a DB_DEFAULT_EXPR_TYPE (the default expression)
9072  */
9073 PT_OP_TYPE
9074 pt_op_type_from_default_expr_type (DB_DEFAULT_EXPR_TYPE expr_type)
9075 {
9076  switch (expr_type)
9077  {
9078  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSTIME:
9079  return PT_SYS_TIME;
9080 
9081  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSDATE:
9082  return PT_SYS_DATE;
9083 
9084  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSDATETIME:
9085  return PT_SYS_DATETIME;
9086 
9087  case DB_DEFAULT_SYSTIMESTAMP:
9088  return PT_SYS_TIMESTAMP;
9089 
9090  case DB_DEFAULT_UNIX_TIMESTAMP:
9091  return PT_UNIX_TIMESTAMP;
9092 
9093  case DB_DEFAULT_USER:
9094  return PT_USER;
9095 
9096  case DB_DEFAULT_CURR_USER:
9097  return PT_CURRENT_USER;
9098 
9099  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTDATETIME:
9100  return PT_CURRENT_DATETIME;
9101 
9102  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTTIMESTAMP:
9103  return PT_CURRENT_TIMESTAMP;
9104 
9105  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTTIME:
9106  return PT_CURRENT_TIME;
9107 
9108  case DB_DEFAULT_CURRENTDATE:
9109  return PT_CURRENT_DATE;
9110 
9111  default:
9112  return (PT_OP_TYPE) 0;
9113  }
9114 }
9115 
9116 DB_OBJECT *
9117 pt_resolve_serial (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * serial_name_node)
9118 {
9119  char *serial_name, *t;
9120  DB_OBJECT *serial_class_mop, *serial_mop;
9121  DB_IDENTIFIER serial_obj_id;
9122 
9123  if (serial_name_node == NULL || serial_name_node->node_type != PT_NAME)
9124  {
9125  return NULL;
9126  }
9127 
9128  serial_name = (char *) serial_name_node->info.name.original;
9129  t = strchr (serial_name, '.'); /* FIXME */
9130  serial_name = (t != NULL) ? (t + 1) : serial_name;
9131 
9132  serial_class_mop = sm_find_class (CT_SERIAL_NAME);
9133  serial_mop = do_get_serial_obj_id (&serial_obj_id, serial_class_mop, serial_name);
9134  if (serial_mop == NULL)
9135  {
9136  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_SERIAL_NOT_FOUND, 1, serial_name);
9137  }
9138 
9139  return serial_mop;
9140 }
9141 
9142 /*
9143  * pt_function_name_is_spec_attr () - checks if a generic function name is
9144  * actually an attribute name. It is used to distinguish between an error
9145  * caused by the wrong usage of a prefix length index or an function
9146  * index.
9147  *
9148  * return: NO_ERROR on success, non-zero for ERROR
9149  * parser(in): parser context
9150  * node(in): PT_FUNCTION node holding the function name to be searched
9151  * bind_arg(in): list of scopes
9152  * is_spec_attr(out): 1 if it is actually an attribute name, 0 otherwise
9153  */
9154 static int
9155 pt_function_name_is_spec_attr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg, int *is_spec_attr)
9156 {
9157  SCOPES *scope = NULL;
9158  PT_NODE *spec = NULL;
9159  PT_NODE *attr = NULL;
9160 
9161  assert (node->node_type == PT_FUNCTION);
9162 
9163  *is_spec_attr = 0;
9164  attr = pt_name (parser, node->info.function.generic_name);
9165  if (attr == NULL)
9166  {
9167  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
9168  return ER_FAILED;
9169  }
9170 
9171  /* walk scopes (might be unnecessary) */
9172  for (scope = bind_arg->scopes; scope; scope = scope->next)
9173  {
9174  /* walk specs */
9175  for (spec = scope->specs; spec; spec = spec->next)
9176  {
9177  if (pt_find_name_in_spec (parser, spec, attr) > 0)
9178  {
9179  *is_spec_attr = 1;
9180  break;
9181  }
9182  }
9183  if (*is_spec_attr == 1)
9184  {
9185  /* no need to continue */
9186  break;
9187  }
9188  }
9189 
9190  if (attr != NULL)
9191  {
9192  parser_free_node (parser, attr);
9193  }
9194 
9195  return NO_ERROR;
9196 }
9197 
9198 /*
9199  * pt_mark_function_index_expression () - mark function index expression
9200  * return:
9201  * parser(in): parser context
9202  * node(in): PT_EXPR node
9203  * bind_arg(in): list of scopes
9204  */
9205 static void
9206 pt_mark_function_index_expression (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * expr, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg)
9207 {
9208  SCOPES *scope = NULL;
9209  PT_NODE *spec = NULL;
9210  MOP cls;
9211  SM_CLASS_CONSTRAINT *constraints;
9212  char *expr_str = NULL;
9213  PT_NODE *flat = NULL;
9214 
9215  if (expr->node_type != PT_EXPR)
9216  {
9217  return;
9218  }
9219 
9220  /* walk scopes */
9221  for (scope = bind_arg->scopes; scope; scope = scope->next)
9222  {
9223  /* walk specs */
9224  for (spec = scope->specs; spec; spec = spec->next)
9225  {
9226  if (spec->info.spec.meta_class == PT_CLASS && !spec->info.spec.derived_table
9227  && spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list)
9228  {
9229  flat = spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list;
9230  while (flat)
9231  {
9232  if (flat->node_type != PT_NAME)
9233  {
9234  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
9235  return;
9236  }
9237 
9238  /* Get the object */
9239  cls = flat->info.name.db_object;
9240  if (!cls)
9241  {
9242  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
9243  return;
9244  }
9245 
9246  constraints = sm_class_constraints (cls);
9247  while (constraints != NULL)
9248  {
9249  if (constraints->func_index_info)
9250  {
9251  if (expr_str == NULL)
9252  {
9253  expr_str = parser_print_function_index_expr (parser, expr);
9254  }
9255 
9256  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (expr_str, constraints->func_index_info->expr_str))
9257  {
9258  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_FUNCTION_INDEX);
9259  return;
9260  }
9261  }
9262  constraints = constraints->next;
9263  }
9264 
9265  flat = flat->next;
9266  }
9267  }
9268  }
9269  }
9270 }
9271 
9272 /*
9273  * pt_bind_names_merge_insert () -
9274  * return:
9275  * parser(in):
9276  * node(in):
9277  * bind_arg(in):
9278  * scopestack(in):
9279  * spec_frame(in):
9280  */
9281 static void
9282 pt_bind_names_merge_insert (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg, SCOPES * scopestack,
9283  PT_EXTRA_SPECS_FRAME * spec_frame)
9284 {
9285  PT_NODE *temp_node, *node_list, *save_next, *prev_node = NULL;
9286  bool is_first_node;
9287 
9288  assert (node->node_type == PT_MERGE);
9289 
9290  /* bind names for insert attributes list */
9291  scopestack->specs = node->info.merge.into;
9292  bind_arg->scopes = scopestack;
9293  spec_frame->next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
9294  spec_frame->extra_specs = NULL;
9295  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame;
9296  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
9297  node->info.merge.insert.attr_list =
9298  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.merge.insert.attr_list, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
9299  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9300  {
9301  return;
9302  }
9303 
9304  /* bind names for default function in insert values list */
9305  node_list = node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses->info.node_list.list;
9306  for (temp_node = node_list, is_first_node = true; temp_node != NULL;
9307  temp_node = temp_node->next, is_first_node = false)
9308  {
9309  if (temp_node->node_type == PT_EXPR && temp_node->info.expr.op == PT_DEFAULTF)
9310  {
9311  scopestack->specs = node->info.merge.into;
9312  bind_arg->scopes = scopestack;
9313  spec_frame->next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
9314  spec_frame->extra_specs = NULL;
9315  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame;
9316  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
9317 
9318  save_next = temp_node->next;
9319  temp_node->next = NULL;
9320  temp_node = parser_walk_tree (parser, temp_node, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
9321  temp_node->next = save_next;
9322 
9323  if (is_first_node)
9324  {
9325  node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses->info.node_list.list = temp_node;
9326  }
9327  else
9328  {
9329  prev_node->next = temp_node;
9330  }
9331  }
9332  prev_node = temp_node;
9333  }
9334 
9335  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9336  {
9337  return;
9338  }
9339 
9340  /* bind names for the rest of insert values list */
9341  scopestack->specs = node->info.merge.using_clause;
9342  bind_arg->scopes = scopestack;
9343  spec_frame->next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
9344  spec_frame->extra_specs = NULL;
9345  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame;
9346  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
9347  node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses =
9348  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post,
9349  bind_arg);
9350 
9351  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9352  {
9353  return;
9354  }
9355 
9356  /* bind names for insert search condition */
9357  scopestack->specs = node->info.merge.using_clause;
9358  bind_arg->scopes = scopestack;
9359  spec_frame->next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
9360  spec_frame->extra_specs = NULL;
9361  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame;
9362  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
9363  node->info.merge.insert.search_cond =
9364  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.merge.insert.search_cond, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post,
9365  bind_arg);
9366 }
9367 
9368 /*
9369  * pt_bind_names_merge_update () -
9370  * return:
9371  * parser(in):
9372  * node(in):
9373  * bind_arg(in):
9374  * scopestack(in):
9375  * spec_frame(in):
9376  */
9377 static void
9378 pt_bind_names_merge_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg, SCOPES * scopestack,
9379  PT_EXTRA_SPECS_FRAME * spec_frame)
9380 {
9381  PT_NODE *assignment;
9382 
9383  /* resolve lhs with target spec only */
9384  scopestack->specs = node->info.merge.into;
9385  bind_arg->scopes = scopestack;
9386  spec_frame->next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
9387  spec_frame->extra_specs = NULL;
9388  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame;
9389  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
9390  for (assignment = node->info.merge.update.assignment; assignment; assignment = assignment->next)
9391  {
9392  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (assignment->info.expr.arg1))
9393  {
9394  assignment->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.arg1 =
9395  parser_walk_tree (parser, assignment->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.arg1, pt_bind_names, bind_arg,
9396  pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
9397  if (assignment->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
9398  {
9399  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
9400  return;
9401  }
9402  }
9403  else
9404  {
9405  assignment->info.expr.arg1 =
9406  parser_walk_tree (parser, assignment->info.expr.arg1, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post,
9407  bind_arg);
9408  if (assignment->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
9409  {
9410  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
9411  return;
9412  }
9413  }
9414  }
9415 
9416  /* resolve rhs with both source and target specs */
9417  scopestack->specs = node->info.merge.into;
9418  node->info.merge.into->next = node->info.merge.using_clause;
9419  bind_arg->scopes = scopestack;
9420  spec_frame->next = bind_arg->spec_frames;
9421  spec_frame->extra_specs = NULL;
9422  bind_arg->spec_frames = spec_frame;
9423  pt_bind_scope (parser, bind_arg);
9424  for (assignment = node->info.merge.update.assignment; assignment; assignment = assignment->next)
9425  {
9426  assignment->info.expr.arg2 =
9427  parser_walk_tree (parser, assignment->info.expr.arg2, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
9428  if (assignment->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
9429  {
9430  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
9431  return;
9432  }
9433  }
9434  node->info.merge.into->next = NULL;
9435 }
9436 
9437 /*
9438  * pt_resolve_partition_spec - resolve a spec specified with PARTITION keyword
9439  * to the actual partition spec
9440  * return: partition spec
9441  * parser (in) : parser context
9442  * spec (in) : spec
9443  * spec_parent (in) : spec parent
9444  * for_update (in): is update purpose?
9445  */
9446 static PT_NODE *
9447 pt_resolve_partition_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * spec_parent, bool for_update)
9448 {
9449  const char *partition_suffix = NULL;
9450  const char *partition_name = NULL;
9451  DB_OBJECT *root_op, *partition_op = NULL;
9452  SM_CLASS *class_ = NULL;
9453  PT_NODE *entity_name = NULL, *partition_node = NULL;
9454  const char *root_name = NULL;
9455  AU_FETCHMODE fetchmode;
9456 
9457  if (spec == NULL || spec->info.spec.partition == NULL)
9458  {
9459  return spec;
9460  }
9461 
9462  entity_name = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
9463  root_name = entity_name->info.name.original;
9464  partition_node = spec->info.spec.partition;
9465  partition_suffix = partition_node->info.name.original;
9466  partition_name = pt_partition_name (parser, root_name, partition_suffix);
9467  if (partition_name == NULL)
9468  {
9469  return NULL;
9470  }
9471 
9472  /* set the actual partition name to the partition node */
9473  partition_node->info.name.original = partition_name;
9474 
9475  /* use partition name to make flat list */
9476  spec->info.spec.entity_name = partition_node;
9477  spec->info.spec.partition = NULL;
9478  spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list = pt_make_flat_name_list (parser, spec, spec_parent, for_update);
9479  if (spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list == NULL)
9480  {
9481  return NULL;
9482  }
9483 
9484  /* Verify if current spec is a partition of the saved entity name */
9485  root_op = db_find_class_with_purpose (root_name, for_update);
9486  if (root_op == NULL)
9487  {
9488  PT_ERRORc (parser, spec, er_msg ());
9489  return NULL;
9490  }
9491 
9492  partition_op = spec->info.spec.entity_name->info.name.db_object;
9493  if (partition_op == NULL)
9494  {
9495  /* We have successfully resolved it, it should not be null */
9496  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
9497  return NULL;
9498  }
9499 
9500  fetchmode = for_update ? AU_FETCH_UPDATE : AU_FETCH_READ;
9501 
9502  /* do not check authorization here */
9503  if (au_fetch_class_force (partition_op, &class_, fetchmode) != NO_ERROR)
9504  {
9505  PT_ERRORc (parser, spec, er_msg ());
9506  return NULL;
9507  }
9508 
9509  if (class_->partition == NULL)
9510  {
9511  /* no partition information */
9512  PT_ERRORmf (parser, spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_DOES_NOT_EXIST, partition_suffix);
9513  return NULL;
9514  }
9515 
9516  if (class_->users != NULL)
9517  {
9518  /* this is a partitioned class, it cannot be a partition of the specified class */
9519  PT_ERRORmf (parser, spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_DOES_NOT_EXIST, partition_suffix);
9520  return NULL;
9521  }
9522 
9523  /* class_ is a partition, we only have to verify that its superclass is root_op */
9524  if (class_->inheritance->op != root_op)
9525  {
9526  /* class_ is a partition of a different class */
9527  PT_ERRORmf (parser, spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_DOES_NOT_EXIST, partition_suffix);
9528  return NULL;
9529  }
9530 
9531  /* set root class name as alias for this spec */
9532  if (spec->info.spec.range_var == NULL)
9533  {
9534  spec->info.spec.range_var = entity_name;
9535  entity_name = NULL;
9536  }
9537 
9538  if (entity_name != NULL)
9539  {
9540  parser_free_tree (parser, entity_name);
9541  }
9542 
9543  return spec;
9544 }
9545 
9546 /*
9547  * pt_set_reserved_name_key_type () - When scanning for index key and node
9548  * info, keys are selected from index.
9549  * This function is supposed to resolve
9550  * data type for such attributes.
9551  *
9552  * return : Original node with updated type_enum.
9553  * parser (in) : Parser context.
9554  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
9555  * arg (in) : Index key data type.
9556  * continue_walk (in) : Continue walk.
9557  */
9558 static PT_NODE *
9559 pt_set_reserved_name_key_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
9560 {
9561  PT_BIND_NAMES_DATA_TYPE *key_type = (PT_BIND_NAMES_DATA_TYPE *) arg;
9562 
9563  if (node != NULL && node->node_type == PT_NAME && node->info.name.meta_class == PT_RESERVED
9564  && (node->info.name.reserved_id == RESERVED_KEY_KEY || node->info.name.reserved_id == RESERVED_BT_NODE_FIRST_KEY
9565  || node->info.name.reserved_id == RESERVED_BT_NODE_LAST_KEY))
9566  {
9567  /* Set key type */
9568  node->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, key_type->data_type);
9569  if (node->data_type == NULL)
9570  {
9571  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
9572  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
9573  }
9574  node->type_enum = key_type->type_enum;
9575  }
9576  return node;
9577 }
9578 
9579 /*
9580  * pt_bind_names_in_with_clause () - resolve names in with clause of node
9581  *
9582  * return : void
9583  * parser (in) : Parser context.
9584  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
9585  * bind_arg (in) : Bind names arg.
9586  *
9587  * Note: The names from the with clause should be resolved before resolving the actual query;
9588  * Since CTEs may be referenced multiple times in a query, better resolve them separately
9589  * instead of resolving each occurence
9590  */
9591 static void
9592 pt_bind_names_in_with_clause (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg)
9593 {
9594  PT_NODE *with = NULL;
9595  PT_NODE *curr_cte;
9596 
9597  switch (node->node_type)
9598  {
9599  case PT_SELECT:
9600  case PT_UNION:
9601  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
9602  case PT_INTERSECTION:
9603  with = node->info.query.with;
9604  break;
9605  case PT_UPDATE:
9606  with = node->info.update.with;
9607  break;
9608  case PT_DELETE:
9609  with = node->info.delete_.with;
9610  break;
9611  default:
9612  assert (false);
9613  }
9614 
9615  if (with == NULL)
9616  {
9617  /* nothing to do */
9618  return;
9619  }
9620 
9621  for (curr_cte = with->info.with_clause.cte_definition_list; curr_cte != NULL; curr_cte = curr_cte->next)
9622  {
9623  /* isolate curr_cte and apply resolve names */
9624  PT_NODE *save_next_cte = curr_cte->next;
9625  curr_cte->next = NULL;
9626 
9627  pt_bind_names_in_cte (parser, curr_cte, bind_arg);
9628 
9629  curr_cte->next = save_next_cte;
9630  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9631  {
9632  return;
9633  }
9634  }
9635 }
9636 
9637 
9638 /*
9639  * pt_resolve_names_in_cte - resolve names in cte definition
9640  *
9641  * return : void
9642  * parser (in) : Parser context.
9643  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
9644  * bind_arg (in) : Bind names arg.
9645  */
9646 static void
9647 pt_bind_names_in_cte (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * cte_def, PT_BIND_NAMES_ARG * bind_arg)
9648 {
9649  PT_NODE *save_next_cte_def;
9650  PT_NODE *non_recursive_cte = cte_def->info.cte.non_recursive_part;
9651  PT_NODE *recursive_cte = cte_def->info.cte.recursive_part;
9652  bool save_donot_fold;
9653 
9654  assert (cte_def->node_type == PT_CTE);
9655 
9656  if (non_recursive_cte == NULL)
9657  {
9658  /* something went wrong, this shouldn't be possible */
9659  assert (0);
9660  return;
9661  }
9662 
9663  /* Evaluate the non-recursive part:
9664  * bind the names and the types from the non-recursive part and set cte->as_attr_list accordingly;
9665  * the recursive part(if it exists) will use the as_attr_list to bind its own names and types;
9666  */
9667  non_recursive_cte = parser_walk_tree (parser, non_recursive_cte, pt_bind_names, bind_arg,
9668  pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
9669 
9670  /* must bind any expr types in non recursive part; required for types binding */
9671  save_donot_fold = bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold; /* save */
9672  bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold = true; /* skip folding */
9673  non_recursive_cte = pt_semantic_type (parser, non_recursive_cte, bind_arg->sc_info);
9674  bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold = save_donot_fold; /* restore */
9675  if (non_recursive_cte == NULL)
9676  {
9677  goto end;
9678  }
9679 
9680  /* build the cte as_attr_list according to the non_recursive part */
9681  if (cte_def->info.cte.as_attr_list == NULL)
9682  {
9683  cte_def->info.cte.as_attr_list =
9684  pt_get_attr_list_of_derived_table (parser, PT_IS_SUBQUERY, non_recursive_cte, cte_def->info.cte.name);
9685  }
9686  pt_set_attr_list_types (parser, cte_def->info.cte.as_attr_list, PT_IS_SUBQUERY, non_recursive_cte, cte_def);
9687 
9688  /* done with the non_recursive_part */
9689  cte_def->info.cte.non_recursive_part = non_recursive_cte;
9690 
9691  /* Evaluate the recursive part:
9692  * bind the names and the types of the recursive part, and unify them with the ones of the non-recursive part
9693  * pt_semantic_type will unify the types of the two parts considering that there is a UNION between them
9694  * cte->as_attr_list will be overwritten with the unified types
9695  */
9696  if (recursive_cte != NULL)
9697  {
9698  recursive_cte = parser_walk_tree (parser, recursive_cte, pt_bind_names, bind_arg, pt_bind_names_post, bind_arg);
9699  if (recursive_cte == NULL)
9700  {
9701  goto end;
9702  }
9703 
9704  cte_def->info.cte.recursive_part = recursive_cte;
9705 
9706  /* must bind any expr types in cte; required for types binding */
9707  save_donot_fold = bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold;
9708  bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold = true;
9709  save_next_cte_def = cte_def->next;
9710  cte_def->next = NULL;
9711  cte_def = pt_semantic_type (parser, cte_def, bind_arg->sc_info);
9712  if (!cte_def)
9713  {
9714  return; /* error in pt_semantic_type */
9715  }
9716 
9717  bind_arg->sc_info->donot_fold = save_donot_fold; /* restore */
9718  cte_def->next = save_next_cte_def;
9719 
9720  /* set final CTE attributes types */
9721  pt_set_attr_list_types (parser, cte_def->info.cte.as_attr_list, PT_IS_SUBQUERY, recursive_cte, cte_def);
9722 
9723  /* the attributes of cte self references specs can now be computed correctly */
9724  recursive_cte = parser_walk_tree (parser, recursive_cte, pt_bind_cte_self_references_types, NULL, NULL, NULL);
9725  }
9726 
9727 end:
9728  cte_def->info.cte.non_recursive_part = non_recursive_cte;
9729  cte_def->info.cte.recursive_part = recursive_cte;
9730 }
9731 
9732 /*
9733  * pt_bind_cte_self_references_types () - used to bind types of self reference specs in recursive cte part;
9734  * this can be done only after bind_names is complete and
9735  * final cte attributes types are set
9736  * return:
9737  * parser(in):
9738  * node(in):
9739  * arg(in/out):
9740  * continue_walk(in/out):
9741  */
9742 static PT_NODE *
9743 pt_bind_cte_self_references_types (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
9744 {
9745  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_SPEC || !PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (node))
9746  {
9747  /* interested only in CTE specs */
9748  return node;
9749  }
9750 
9751  pt_bind_spec_attrs (parser, node);
9752 
9753  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9754 
9755  return node;
9756 }
9757 
9758 
9759 /*
9760  * pt_get_attr_list_of_derived_table - determine the list of aliases of a derived table
9761  *
9762  * return : Computed as_attr_list
9763  * parser (in) : Parser context.
9764  * derived_table_type (in) : Provided by the spec that contains the derived table.
9765  * derived_table (in) : Derived table to be processed.
9766  * derived_alias (in) : The alias of the derived table (also comes from the spec).
9767  */
9768 static PT_NODE *
9769 pt_get_attr_list_of_derived_table (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_MISC_TYPE derived_table_type, PT_NODE * derived_table,
9770  PT_NODE * derived_alias)
9771 {
9772  PT_NODE *as_attr_list = NULL, *select_list;
9773  int i, id;
9774 
9775  switch (derived_table_type)
9776  {
9777  case PT_IS_SET_EXPR:
9778  /* if derived from a set expression, it better have a set type */
9779  if (derived_table->node_type == PT_NAME && derived_table->info.name.original != NULL
9780  && derived_table->info.name.original[0] != '\0')
9781  {
9782  as_attr_list = pt_name (parser, derived_table->info.name.original);
9783  }
9784  else
9785  { /* generate column name */
9786  id = 0;
9787  as_attr_list = pt_name (parser, mq_generate_name (parser, derived_alias->info.name.original, &id));
9788  }
9789  break;
9790 
9791  case PT_IS_SHOWSTMT:
9792  as_attr_list = pt_get_all_showstmt_attributes_and_types (parser, derived_table);
9793  if (as_attr_list == NULL)
9794  {
9795  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
9796  return NULL;
9797  }
9798  break;
9799 
9800  case PT_IS_SUBQUERY:
9801  {
9802  /* must be a subquery derived table */
9803  /* select_list must have passed star expansion */
9804  PT_NODE *att, *col;
9805 
9806  select_list = pt_get_select_list (parser, derived_table);
9807  if (!select_list)
9808  {
9809  return NULL;
9810  }
9811 
9812  for (att = select_list, i = 0; att; att = att->next, i++)
9813  {
9814  if (att->alias_print)
9815  {
9816  col = pt_name (parser, att->alias_print);
9817  }
9818  else
9819  {
9820  if (att->node_type == PT_NAME && att->info.name.original != NULL && att->info.name.original[0] != '\0')
9821  {
9822  col = pt_name (parser, att->info.name.original);
9823  }
9824  else if (att->node_type == PT_VALUE && att->info.value.text != NULL && att->info.value.text[0] != '\0')
9825  {
9826  col = pt_name (parser, att->info.value.text);
9827  }
9828  else if (att->node_type == PT_EXPR || att->node_type == PT_FUNCTION)
9829  {
9830  PARSER_VARCHAR *alias;
9831  alias = pt_print_bytes (parser, att);
9832  col = pt_name (parser, (const char *) alias->bytes);
9833  }
9834  else
9835  { /* generate column name */
9836  id = i;
9837  col = pt_name (parser, mq_generate_name (parser, derived_alias->info.name.original, &id));
9838  }
9839  }
9840 
9841  col->type_enum = att->type_enum;
9842  if (att->data_type)
9843  {
9844  col->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, att->data_type);
9845  }
9846 
9847  as_attr_list = parser_append_node (col, as_attr_list);
9848  }
9849  break;
9850  }
9851 
9852  default:
9853  /* this can't happen since we removed MERGE/CSELECT from grammar */
9854  assert (derived_table_type == PT_IS_CSELECT);
9855  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
9856  return NULL;
9857  }
9858 
9859  return as_attr_list;
9860 }
9861 
9862 /*
9863  * pt_set_attr_list_types - identify and set the types of attributes
9864  *
9865  * return : void
9866  * parser (in) : Parser context.
9867  * as_attr_list(in/out) : attr list to be processed.
9868  * derived_table_type (in) : Provided by the spec that contains the derived table.
9869  * derived_table (in) : Derived table to be processed.
9870  * parent_spec (in) : The spec where derived table resides.
9871  */
9872 static void
9873 pt_set_attr_list_types (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * as_attr_list, PT_MISC_TYPE derived_table_type,
9874  PT_NODE * derived_table, PT_NODE * parent_spec)
9875 {
9876  PT_NODE *elt_type, *select_list;
9877  int col_cnt = pt_length_of_list (as_attr_list), attr_cnt;
9878 
9879  switch (derived_table_type)
9880  {
9881  case PT_IS_SET_EXPR:
9882  /* if derived from a set expression, it better have a set type */
9883  if (!pt_is_set_type (derived_table))
9884  {
9885  PT_ERRORmf (parser, parent_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_MUST_BE_SET_MSET_SEQ,
9886  pt_short_print (parser, derived_table));
9887  return;
9888  }
9889 
9890  elt_type = derived_table->data_type;
9891 
9892  /* Handle a derived table query on an empty set stored in a host variable (elt_type==NULL) the same way as a NULL
9893  * value. Note that derived table queries on sets of anything will also result in a null elt_type here */
9894  if (PT_IS_NULL_NODE (derived_table) || !elt_type)
9895  {
9896  /* this is to accept a NULL literal value consistently with NULL column values. Unfortunaltely, no type
9897  * information for the column may be deduced. */
9898  as_attr_list->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NULL;
9899  as_attr_list->data_type = NULL;
9900  }
9901  else
9902  {
9903  /*
9904  * Make sure that all elements on the data type list have the
9905  * same type_enum, e.g., that they all represent classes.
9906  */
9907  PT_TYPE_ENUM t = elt_type->type_enum;
9908  PT_NODE *p;
9909  for (p = elt_type->next; p; p = p->next)
9910  {
9911  if (p->type_enum != t)
9912  {
9913  elt_type = NULL;
9914  break;
9915  }
9916  }
9917  if (!elt_type)
9918  {
9919  PT_ERRORmf (parser, parent_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GT_1_SET_ELEM_TYPE,
9920  pt_short_print (parser, derived_table));
9921  return;
9922  }
9923 
9924  /* it should have exactly one derived column */
9925  if (col_cnt > 1)
9926  {
9927  PT_ERRORmf (parser, parent_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GT_1_DERIVED_COL_NAM,
9928  pt_short_print_l (parser, as_attr_list));
9929  return;
9930  }
9931  if (col_cnt < 1)
9932  {
9933  PT_ERRORmf (parser, parent_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_DERIVED_COL_NAM,
9934  pt_short_print (parser, derived_table));
9935  return;
9936  }
9937 
9938  /* derived column assumes the set's element type */
9939  as_attr_list->type_enum = elt_type->type_enum;
9940  as_attr_list->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, elt_type);
9941  }
9942 
9943  break;
9944 
9945 
9946  case PT_IS_SHOWSTMT:
9947  {
9948  /* types are already set in pt_get_all_showstmt_attributes_and_types; */
9949  PT_NODE *col = as_attr_list;
9950  while (col)
9951  {
9952  col->line_number = parent_spec->line_number;
9953  col->column_number = parent_spec->column_number;
9954  col = col->next;
9955  }
9956  return;
9957  }
9958 
9959  case PT_IS_SUBQUERY:
9960  /* must be a subquery derived table */
9961  /* select_list must have passed star expansion */
9962  select_list = pt_get_select_list (parser, derived_table);
9963  if (!select_list)
9964  {
9965  return;
9966  }
9967 
9968  /* select_list attributes must match derived columns in number */
9969  attr_cnt = pt_length_of_select_list (select_list, INCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
9970  if (col_cnt != attr_cnt)
9971  {
9972  PT_ERRORmf3 (parser, parent_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_CNT_NE_DERIVED_C,
9973  pt_short_print (parser, parent_spec), attr_cnt, col_cnt);
9974  return;
9975  }
9976  else
9977  {
9978  PT_NODE *col, *att;
9979  /* derived columns assume the type of their matching attributes */
9980  for (col = as_attr_list, att = select_list; col && att; col = col->next, att = att->next)
9981  {
9982  col->type_enum = att->type_enum;
9983  if (att->data_type)
9984  {
9985  col->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, att->data_type);
9986  }
9987  else
9988  {
9989  parser_free_tree (parser, col->data_type);
9990  col->data_type = NULL;
9991  }
9992  }
9993  }
9994  break;
9995 
9996  default:
9997  /* this can't happen since we removed MERGE/CSELECT from grammar */
9998  assert (derived_table_type == PT_IS_CSELECT);
9999  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
10000  return;
10001  }
10002 }
10003 
10004 /*
10005  * pt_count_with_clauses - find if node has WITH clause
10006  * return:
10007  * parser(in):
10008  * node(in): the node to check
10009  * arg(out): count of WITH clauses
10010  * continue_walk(in):
10011  */
10012 static PT_NODE *
10013 pt_count_with_clauses (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
10014 {
10015  int *cnt = (int *) arg;
10016 
10017  if (node != NULL && PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (node->node_type) && node->info.query.with != NULL)
10018  {
10019  /* node has WITH clause */
10020  (*cnt)++;
10021  }
10022 
10023  return node;
10024 }
